INSERT INTO verses (book_id, chapter, verse, text, version) VALUES
(7, 3, 4, 'Peter and John looked at him intently, and Peter said, "Look at us!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 5, 'The lame man looked at them eagerly, expecting a gift.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 6, 'But Peter said, "I don''t have any money for you. But I''ll give you what I have. In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, get up and walk!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 7, 'Then Peter took the lame man by the right hand and helped him up. And as he did, the man''s feet and anklebones were healed and strengthened.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 8, 'He jumped up, stood on his feet, and began to walk! Then, walking, leaping, and praising God, he went into the Temple with them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 9, 'All the people saw him walking and heard him praising God.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 10, 'When they realized he was the lame beggar they had seen so often at the Beautiful Gate, they were absolutely astounded!', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 11, 'They all rushed out to Solomon''s Colonnade, where he was holding tightly to Peter and John. Everyone stood there in awe of the wonderful thing that had happened.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 12, 'Peter saw his opportunity and addressed the crowd. "People of Israel," he said, "what is so astounding about this? And why look at us as though we had made this man walk by our own power and godliness?', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 13, 'For it is the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, the God of Jacob, the God of all our ancestors who has brought glory to his servant Jesus by doing this. This is the same Jesus whom you handed over and rejected before Pilate, despite Pilate''s decision to release him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 14, 'You rejected this holy, righteous one and instead demanded the release of a murderer.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 15, 'You killed the author of life, but God raised him to life. And we are witnesses of this fact!', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 16, '"The name of Jesus has healed this man--and you know how lame he was before. Faith in Jesus'' name has caused this healing before your very eyes.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 17, '"Friends, I realize that what you did to Jesus was done in ignorance; and the same can be said of your leaders.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 18, 'But God was fulfilling what all the prophets had declared about the Messiah beforehand--that he must suffer all these things.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 19, 'Now turn from your sins and turn to God, so you can be cleansed of your sins.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 20, 'Then wonderful times of refreshment will come from the presence of the Lord, and he will send Jesus your Messiah to you again.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 21, 'For he must remain in heaven until the time for the final restoration of all things, as God promised long ago through his prophets.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 22, 'Moses said, ''The Lord your God will raise up a Prophet like me from among your own people. Listen carefully to everything he tells you.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 23, 'Then Moses said, ''Anyone who will not listen to that Prophet will be cut off from God''s people and utterly destroyed.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 24, '"Starting with Samuel, every prophet spoke about what is happening today.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 25, 'You are the children of those prophets, and you are included in the covenant God promised to your ancestors. For God said to Abraham, ''Through your descendants all the families on earth will be blessed.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 26, 'When God raised up his servant, he sent him first to you people of Israel, to bless you by turning each of you back from your sinful ways."', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 1, 'While Peter and John were speaking to the people, the leading priests, the captain of the Temple guard, and some of the Sadducees came over to them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 2, 'They were very disturbed that Peter and John were claiming, on the authority of Jesus, that there is a resurrection of the dead.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 3, 'They arrested them and, since it was already evening, jailed them until morning.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 4, 'But many of the people who heard their message believed it, so that the number of believers totaled about five thousand men, not counting women and children.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 5, 'The next day the council of all the rulers and elders and teachers of religious law met in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 6, 'Annas the high priest was there, along with Caiaphas, John, Alexander, and other relatives of the high priest.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 7, 'They brought in the two disciples and demanded, "By what power, or in whose name, have you done this?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 8, 'Then Peter, filled with the Holy Spirit, said to them, "Leaders and elders of our nation,', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 9, 'are we being questioned because we''ve done a good deed for a crippled man? Do you want to know how he was healed?', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 10, 'Let me clearly state to you and to all the people of Israel that he was healed in the name and power of Jesus Christ from Nazareth, the man you crucified, but whom God raised from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 11, 'For Jesus is the one referred to in the Scriptures, where it says, ''The stone that you builders rejected has now become the cornerstone.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 12, 'There is salvation in no one else! There is no other name in all of heaven for people to call on to save them."', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 13, 'The members of the council were amazed when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, for they could see that they were ordinary men who had had no special training. They also recognized them as men who had been with Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 14, 'But since the man who had been healed was standing right there among them, the council had nothing to say.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 15, 'So they sent Peter and John out of the council chamber and conferred among themselves.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 16, '"What should we do with these men?" they asked each other. "We can''t deny they have done a miraculous sign, and everybody in Jerusalem knows about it.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 17, 'But perhaps we can stop them from spreading their propaganda. We''ll warn them not to speak to anyone in Jesus'' name again."', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 18, 'So they called the apostles back in and told them never again to speak or teach about Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 19, 'But Peter and John replied, "Do you think God wants us to obey you rather than him?', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 20, 'We cannot stop telling about the wonderful things we have seen and heard."', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 21, 'The council then threatened them further, but they finally let them go because they didn''t know how to punish them without starting a riot. For everyone was praising God', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 22, 'for this miraculous sign--the healing of a man who had been lame for more than forty years.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 23, 'As soon as they were freed, Peter and John found the other believers and told them what the leading priests and elders had said.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 24, 'Then all the believers were united as they lifted their voices in prayer: "O Sovereign Lord, Creator of heaven and earth, the sea, and everything in them--', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 25, 'you spoke long ago by the Holy Spirit through our ancestor King David, your servant, saying, ''Why did the nations rage? Why did the people waste their time with futile plans?', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 26, 'The kings of the earth prepared for battle; the rulers gathered together against the Lord and against his Messiah.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 27, '"That is what has happened here in this city! For Herod Antipas, Pontius Pilate the governor, the Gentiles, and the people of Israel were all united against Jesus, your holy servant, whom you anointed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 28, 'In fact, everything they did occurred according to your eternal will and plan.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 29, 'And now, O Lord, hear their threats, and give your servants great boldness in their preaching.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 30, 'Send your healing power; may miraculous signs and wonders be done through the name of your holy servant Jesus."', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 31, 'After this prayer, the building where they were meeting shook, and they were all filled with the Holy Spirit. And they preached God''s message with boldness.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 32, 'All the believers were of one heart and mind, and they felt that what they owned was not their own; they shared everything they had.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 33, 'And the apostles gave powerful witness to the resurrection of the Lord Jesus, and God''s great favor was upon them all.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 34, 'There was no poverty among them, because people who owned land or houses sold them', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 35, 'and brought the money to the apostles to give to others in need.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 36, 'For instance, there was Joseph, the one the apostles nicknamed Barnabas (which means "Son of Encouragement"). He was from the tribe of Levi and came from the island of Cyprus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 4, 37, 'He sold a field he owned and brought the money to the apostles for those in need.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 1, 'There was also a man named Ananias who, with his wife, Sapphira, sold some property.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 2, 'He brought part of the money to the apostles, but he claimed it was the full amount. His wife had agreed to this deception.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 3, 'Then Peter said, "Ananias, why has Satan filled your heart? You lied to the Holy Spirit, and you kept some of the money for yourself.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 4, 'The property was yours to sell or not sell, as you wished. And after selling it, the money was yours to give away. How could you do a thing like this? You weren''t lying to us but to God."', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 5, 'As soon as Ananias heard these words, he fell to the floor and died. Everyone who heard about it was terrified.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 6, 'Then some young men wrapped him in a sheet and took him out and buried him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 7, 'About three hours later his wife came in, not knowing what had happened.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 8, 'Peter asked her, "Was this the price you and your husband received for your land?Yes," she replied, "that was the price."', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 9, 'And Peter said, "How could the two of you even think of doing a thing like this--conspiring together to test the Spirit of the Lord? Just outside that door are the young men who buried your husband, and they will carry you out, too."', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 10, 'Instantly, she fell to the floor and died. When the young men came in and saw that she was dead, they carried her out and buried her beside her husband.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 11, 'Great fear gripped the entire church and all others who heard what had happened.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 12, 'Meanwhile, the apostles were performing many miraculous signs and wonders among the people. And the believers were meeting regularly at the Temple in the area known as Solomon''s Colonnade.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 13, 'No one else dared to join them, though everyone had high regard for them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 14, 'And more and more people believed and were brought to the Lord--crowds of both men and women.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 15, 'As a result of the apostles'' work, sick people were brought out into the streets on beds and mats so that Peter''s shadow might fall across some of them as he went by.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 16, 'Crowds came in from the villages around Jerusalem, bringing their sick and those possessed by evil spirits, and they were all healed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 17, 'The high priest and his friends, who were Sadducees, reacted with violent jealousy.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 18, 'They arrested the apostles and put them in the jail.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 19, 'But an angel of the Lord came at night, opened the gates of the jail, and brought them out. Then he told them,', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 20, '"Go to the Temple and give the people this message of life!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 21, 'So the apostles entered the Temple about daybreak and immediately began teaching. When the high priest and his officials arrived, they convened the high council, along with all the elders of Israel. Then they sent for the apostles to be brought for trial.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 22, 'But when the Temple guards went to the jail, the men were gone. So they returned to the council and reported,', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 23, '"The jail was locked, with the guards standing outside, but when we opened the gates, no one was there!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 24, 'When the captain of the Temple guard and the leading priests heard this, they were perplexed, wondering where it would all end.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 25, 'Then someone arrived with the news that the men they had jailed were out in the Temple, teaching the people.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 26, 'The captain went with his Temple guards and arrested them, but without violence, for they were afraid the people would kill them if they treated the apostles roughly.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 27, 'Then they brought the apostles in before the council.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 28, '"Didn''t we tell you never again to teach in this man''s name?" the high priest demanded. "Instead, you have filled all Jerusalem with your teaching about Jesus, and you intend to blame us for his death!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 29, 'But Peter and the apostles replied, "We must obey God rather than human authority.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 30, 'The God of our ancestors raised Jesus from the dead after you killed him by crucifying him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 31, 'Then God put him in the place of honor at his right hand as Prince and Savior. He did this to give the people of Israel an opportunity to turn from their sins and turn to God so their sins would be forgiven.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 32, 'We are witnesses of these things and so is the Holy Spirit, who is given by God to those who obey him."', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 33, 'At this, the high council was furious and decided to kill them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 34, 'But one member had a different perspective. He was a Pharisee named Gamaliel, who was an expert on religious law and was very popular with the people. He stood up and ordered that the apostles be sent outside the council chamber for a while.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 35, 'Then he addressed his colleagues as follows: "Men of Israel, take care what you are planning to do to these men!', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 36, 'Some time ago there was that fellow Theudas, who pretended to be someone great. About four hundred others joined him, but he was killed, and his followers went their various ways. The whole movement came to nothing.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 37, 'After him, at the time of the census, there was Judas of Galilee. He got some people to follow him, but he was killed, too, and all his followers were scattered.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 38, '"So my advice is, leave these men alone. If they are teaching and doing these things merely on their own, it will soon be overthrown.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 39, 'But if it is of God, you will not be able to stop them. You may even find yourselves fighting against God."', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 40, 'The council accepted his advice. They called in the apostles and had them flogged. Then they ordered them never again to speak in the name of Jesus, and they let them go.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 41, 'The apostles left the high council rejoicing that God had counted them worthy to suffer dishonor for the name of Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 5, 42, 'And every day, in the Temple and in their homes, they continued to teach and preach this message: "The Messiah you are looking for is Jesus."', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 1, 'But as the believers rapidly multiplied, there were rumblings of discontent. Those who spoke Greek complained against those who spoke Hebrew, saying that their widows were being discriminated against in the daily distribution of food.', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 2, 'So the Twelve called a meeting of all the believers. "We apostles should spend our time preaching and teaching the word of God, not administering a food program," they said.', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 3, '"Now look around among yourselves, brothers, and select seven men who are well respected and are full of the Holy Spirit and wisdom. We will put them in charge of this business.', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 4, 'Then we can spend our time in prayer and preaching and teaching the word."', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 5, 'This idea pleased the whole group, and they chose the following: Stephen (a man full of faith and the Holy Spirit), Philip, Procorus, Nicanor, Timon, Parmenas, and Nicolas of Antioch (a Gentile convert to the Jewish faith, who had now become a Christian).', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 6, 'These seven were presented to the apostles, who prayed for them as they laid their hands on them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 7, 'God''s message was preached in ever-widening circles. The number of believers greatly increased in Jerusalem, and many of the Jewish priests were converted, too.', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 8, 'Stephen, a man full of God''s grace and power, performed amazing miracles and signs among the people.', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 9, 'But one day some men from the Synagogue of Freed Slaves, as it was called, started to debate with him. They were Jews from Cyrene, Alexandria, Cilicia, and the province of Asia.', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 10, 'None of them was able to stand against the wisdom and Spirit by which Stephen spoke.', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 11, 'So they persuaded some men to lie about Stephen, saying, "We heard him blaspheme Moses, and even God."', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 12, 'Naturally, this roused the crowds, the elders, and the teachers of religious law. So they arrested Stephen and brought him before the high council.', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 13, 'The lying witnesses said, "This man is always speaking against the Temple and against the law of Moses.', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 14, 'We have heard him say that this Jesus of Nazareth will destroy the Temple and change the customs Moses handed down to us."', 'NLT'),
(7, 6, 15, 'At this point everyone in the council stared at Stephen because his face became as bright as an angel''s.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 1, 'Then the high priest asked Stephen, "Are these accusations true?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 2, 'This was Stephen''s reply: "Brothers and honorable fathers, listen to me. Our glorious God appeared to our ancestor Abraham in Mesopotamia before he moved to Haran.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 3, 'God told him, ''Leave your native land and your relatives, and come to the land that I will show you.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 4, 'So Abraham left the land of the Chaldeans and lived in Haran until his father died. Then God brought him here to the land where you now live.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 5, 'But God gave him no inheritance here, not even one square foot of land. God did promise, however, that eventually the whole country would belong to Abraham and his descendants--though he had no children yet.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 6, 'But God also told him that his descendants would live in a foreign country where they would be mistreated as slaves for four hundred years.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 7, '''But I will punish the nation that enslaves them,'' God told him, ''and in the end they will come out and worship me in this place.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 8, 'God also gave Abraham the covenant of circumcision at that time. And so Isaac, Abraham''s son, was circumcised when he was eight days old. Isaac became the father of Jacob, and Jacob was the father of the twelve patriarchs of the Jewish nation.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 9, '"These sons of Jacob were very jealous of their brother Joseph, and they sold him to be a slave in Egypt. But God was with him', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 10, 'and delivered him from his anguish. And God gave him favor before Pharaoh, king of Egypt. God also gave Joseph unusual wisdom, so that Pharaoh appointed him governor over all of Egypt and put him in charge of all the affairs of the palace.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 11, '"But a famine came upon Egypt and Canaan. There was great misery for our ancestors, as they ran out of food.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 12, 'Jacob heard that there was still grain in Egypt, so he sent his sons to buy some.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 13, 'The second time they went, Joseph revealed his identity to his brothers, and they were introduced to Pharaoh.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 14, 'Then Joseph sent for his father, Jacob, and all his relatives to come to Egypt, seventy-five persons in all.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 15, 'So Jacob went to Egypt. He died there, as did all his sons.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 16, 'All of them were taken to Shechem and buried in the tomb Abraham had bought from the sons of Hamor in Shechem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 17, '"As the time drew near when God would fulfill his promise to Abraham, the number of our people in Egypt greatly increased.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 18, 'But then a new king came to the throne of Egypt who knew nothing about Joseph.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 19, 'This king plotted against our people and forced parents to abandon their newborn babies so they would die.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 20, '"At that time Moses was born--a beautiful child in God''s eyes. His parents cared for him at home for three months.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 21, 'When at last they had to abandon him, Pharaoh''s daughter found him and raised him as her own son.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 22, 'Moses was taught all the wisdom of the Egyptians, and he became mighty in both speech and action.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 23, '"One day when he was forty years old, he decided to visit his relatives, the people of Israel.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 24, 'During this visit, he saw an Egyptian mistreating a man of Israel. So Moses came to his defense and avenged him, killing the Egyptian.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 25, 'Moses assumed his brothers would realize that God had sent him to rescue them, but they didn''t.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 26, '"The next day he visited them again and saw two men of Israel fighting. He tried to be a peacemaker. ''Men,'' he said, ''you are brothers. Why are you hurting each other?''', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 27, '"But the man in the wrong pushed Moses aside and told him to mind his own business. ''Who made you a ruler and judge over us?'' he asked.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 28, '''Are you going to kill me as you killed that Egyptian yesterday?''', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 29, 'When Moses heard that, he fled the country and lived as a foreigner in the land of Midian, where his two sons were born.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 30, '"Forty years later, in the desert near Mount Sinai, an angel appeared to Moses in the flame of a burning bush.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 31, 'Moses saw it and wondered what it was. As he went to see, the voice of the Lord called out to him,', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 32, '''I am the God of your ancestors--the God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.'' Moses shook with terror and dared not look.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 33, '"And the Lord said to him, ''Take off your sandals, for you are standing on holy ground.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 34, 'You can be sure that I have seen the misery of my people in Egypt. I have heard their cries. So I have come to rescue them. Now go, for I will send you to Egypt.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 35, 'And so God sent back the same man his people had previously rejected by demanding, ''Who made you a ruler and judge over us?'' Through the angel who appeared to him in the burning bush, Moses was sent to be their ruler and savior.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 36, 'And by means of many miraculous signs and wonders, he led them out of Egypt, through the Red Sea, and back and forth through the wilderness for forty years.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 37, '"Moses himself told the people of Israel, ''God will raise up a Prophet like me from among your own people.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 38, 'Moses was with the assembly of God''s people in the wilderness. He was the mediator between the people of Israel and the angel who gave him life-giving words on Mount Sinai to pass on to us.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 39, '"But our ancestors rejected Moses and wanted to return to Egypt.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 40, 'They told Aaron, ''Make us some gods who can lead us, for we don''t know what has become of this Moses, who brought us out of Egypt.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 41, 'So they made an idol shaped like a calf, and they sacrificed to it and rejoiced in this thing they had made.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 42, 'Then God turned away from them and gave them up to serve the sun, moon, and stars as their gods! In the book of the prophets it is written, ''Was it to me you were bringing sacrifices during those forty years in the wilderness, Israel?', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 43, 'No, your real interest was in your pagan gods--the shrine of Molech, the star god Rephan, and the images you made to worship them. So I will send you into captivity far away in Babylon.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 44, '"Our ancestors carried the Tabernacle with them through the wilderness. It was constructed in exact accordance with the plan shown to Moses by God.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 45, 'Years later, when Joshua led the battles against the Gentile nations that God drove out of this land, the Tabernacle was taken with them into their new territory. And it was used there until the time of King David.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 46, '"David found favor with God and asked for the privilege of building a permanent Temple for the God of Jacob.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 47, 'But it was Solomon who actually built it.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 48, 'However, the Most High doesn''t live in temples made by human hands. As the prophet says,', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 49, '''Heaven is my throne, and the earth is my footstool. Could you ever build me a temple as good as that?'' asks the Lord. ''Could you build a dwelling place for me?', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 50, 'Didn''t I make everything in heaven and earth?''', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 51, '"You stubborn people! You are heathen at heart and deaf to the truth. Must you forever resist the Holy Spirit? But your ancestors did, and so do you!', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 52, 'Name one prophet your ancestors didn''t persecute! They even killed the ones who predicted the coming of the Righteous One--the Messiah whom you betrayed and murdered.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 53, 'You deliberately disobeyed God''s law, though you received it from the hands of angels. "', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 54, 'The Jewish leaders were infuriated by Stephen''s accusation, and they shook their fists in rage.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 55, 'But Stephen, full of the Holy Spirit, gazed steadily upward into heaven and saw the glory of God, and he saw Jesus standing in the place of honor at God''s right hand.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 56, 'And he told them, "Look, I see the heavens opened and the Son of Man standing in the place of honor at God''s right hand!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 57, 'Then they put their hands over their ears, and drowning out his voice with their shouts, they rushed at him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 58, 'They dragged him out of the city and began to stone him. The official witnesses took off their coats and laid them at the feet of a young man named Saul.', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 59, 'And as they stoned him, Stephen prayed, "Lord Jesus, receive my spirit."', 'NLT'),
(7, 7, 60, 'And he fell to his knees, shouting, "Lord, don''t charge them with this sin!" And with that, he died.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 1, 'Saul was one of the official witnesses at the killing of Stephen. A great wave of persecution began that day, sweeping over the church in Jerusalem, and all the believers except the apostles fled into Judea and Samaria.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 2, '(Some godly men came and buried Stephen with loud weeping.)', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 3, 'Saul was going everywhere to devastate the church. He went from house to house, dragging out both men and women to throw them into jail.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 4, 'But the believers who had fled Jerusalem went everywhere preaching the Good News about Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 5, 'Philip, for example, went to the city of Samaria and told the people there about the Messiah.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 6, 'Crowds listened intently to what he had to say because of the miracles he did.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 7, 'Many evil spirits were cast out, screaming as they left their victims. And many who had been paralyzed or lame were healed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 8, 'So there was great joy in that city.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 9, 'A man named Simon had been a sorcerer there for many years, claiming to be someone great.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 10, 'The Samaritan people, from the least to the greatest, often spoke of him as "the Great One--the Power of God."', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 11, 'He was very influential because of the magic he performed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 12, 'But now the people believed Philip''s message of Good News concerning the Kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ. As a result, many men and women were baptized.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 13, 'Then Simon himself believed and was baptized. He began following Philip wherever he went, and he was amazed by the great miracles and signs Philip performed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 14, 'When the apostles back in Jerusalem heard that the people of Samaria had accepted God''s message, they sent Peter and John there.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 15, 'As soon as they arrived, they prayed for these new Christians to receive the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 16, 'The Holy Spirit had not yet come upon any of them, for they had only been baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 17, 'Then Peter and John laid their hands upon these believers, and they received the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 18, 'When Simon saw that the Holy Spirit was given when the apostles placed their hands upon people''s heads, he offered money to buy this power.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 19, '"Let me have this power, too," he exclaimed, "so that when I lay my hands on people, they will receive the Holy Spirit!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 20, 'But Peter replied, "May your money perish with you for thinking God''s gift can be bought!', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 21, 'You can have no part in this, for your heart is not right before God.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 22, 'Turn from your wickedness and pray to the Lord. Perhaps he will forgive your evil thoughts,', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 23, 'for I can see that you are full of bitterness and held captive by sin."', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 24, '"Pray to the Lord for me," Simon exclaimed, "that these terrible things won''t happen to me!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 25, 'After testifying and preaching the word of the Lord in Samaria, Peter and John returned to Jerusalem. And they stopped in many Samaritan villages along the way to preach the Good News to them, too.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 26, 'As for Philip, an angel of the Lord said to him, "Go south down the desert road that runs from Jerusalem to Gaza."', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 27, 'So he did, and he met the treasurer of Ethiopia, a eunuch of great authority under the queen of Ethiopia. The eunuch had gone to Jerusalem to worship,', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 28, 'and he was now returning. Seated in his carriage, he was reading aloud from the book of the prophet Isaiah.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 29, 'The Holy Spirit said to Philip, "Go over and walk along beside the carriage."', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 30, 'Philip ran over and heard the man reading from the prophet Isaiah; so he asked, "Do you understand what you are reading?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 31, 'The man replied, "How can I, when there is no one to instruct me?" And he begged Philip to come up into the carriage and sit with him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 32, 'The passage of Scripture he had been reading was this: "He was led as a sheep to the slaughter. And as a lamb is silent before the shearers, he did not open his mouth.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 33, 'He was humiliated and received no justice. Who can speak of his descendants? For his life was taken from the earth."', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 34, 'The eunuch asked Philip, "Was Isaiah talking about himself or someone else?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 35, 'So Philip began with this same Scripture and then used many others to tell him the Good News about Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 36, 'As they rode along, they came to some water, and the eunuch said, "Look! There''s some water! Why can''t I be baptized?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 37, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 38, 'He ordered the carriage to stop, and they went down into the water, and Philip baptized him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 39, 'When they came up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord caught Philip away. The eunuch never saw him again but went on his way rejoicing.', 'NLT'),
(7, 8, 40, 'Meanwhile, Philip found himself farther north at the city of Azotus! He preached the Good News there and in every city along the way until he came to Caesarea.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 1, 'Meanwhile, Saul was uttering threats with every breath. He was eager to destroy the Lord''s followers, so he went to the high priest.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 2, 'He requested letters addressed to the synagogues in Damascus, asking their cooperation in the arrest of any followers of the Way he found there. He wanted to bring them--both men and women--back to Jerusalem in chains.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 3, 'As he was nearing Damascus on this mission, a brilliant light from heaven suddenly beamed down upon him!', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 4, 'He fell to the ground and heard a voice saying to him, "Saul! Saul! Why are you persecuting me?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 5, '"Who are you, sir?" Saul asked. And the voice replied, "I am Jesus, the one you are persecuting!', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 6, 'Now get up and go into the city, and you will be told what you are to do."', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 7, 'The men with Saul stood speechless with surprise, for they heard the sound of someone''s voice, but they saw no one!', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 8, 'As Saul picked himself up off the ground, he found that he was blind.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 9, 'So his companions led him by the hand to Damascus. He remained there blind for three days. And all that time he went without food and water.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 10, 'Now there was a believer in Damascus named Ananias. The Lord spoke to him in a vision, calling, "Ananias!Yes, Lord!" he replied.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 11, 'The Lord said, "Go over to Straight Street, to the house of Judas. When you arrive, ask for Saul of Tarsus. He is praying to me right now.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 12, 'I have shown him a vision of a man named Ananias coming in and laying his hands on him so that he can see again."', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 13, '"But Lord," exclaimed Ananias, "I''ve heard about the terrible things this man has done to the believers in Jerusalem!', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 14, 'And we hear that he is authorized by the leading priests to arrest every believer in Damascus."', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 15, 'But the Lord said, "Go and do what I say. For Saul is my chosen instrument to take my message to the Gentiles and to kings, as well as to the people of Israel.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 16, 'And I will show him how much he must suffer for me."', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 17, 'So Ananias went and found Saul. He laid his hands on him and said, "Brother Saul, the Lord Jesus, who appeared to you on the road, has sent me so that you may get your sight back and be filled with the Holy Spirit."', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 18, 'Instantly something like scales fell from Saul''s eyes, and he regained his sight. Then he got up and was baptized.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 19, 'Afterward he ate some food and was strengthened. Saul stayed with the believers in Damascus for a few days.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 20, 'And immediately he began preaching about Jesus in the synagogues, saying, "He is indeed the Son of God!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 21, 'All who heard him were amazed. "Isn''t this the same man who persecuted Jesus'' followers with such devastation in Jerusalem?" they asked. "And we understand that he came here to arrest them and take them in chains to the leading priests."', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 22, 'Saul''s preaching became more and more powerful, and the Jews in Damascus couldn''t refute his proofs that Jesus was indeed the Messiah.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 23, 'After a while the Jewish leaders decided to kill him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 24, 'But Saul was told about their plot, and that they were watching for him day and night at the city gate so they could murder him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 25, 'So during the night, some of the other believers let him down in a large basket through an opening in the city wall.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 26, 'When Saul arrived in Jerusalem, he tried to meet with the believers, but they were all afraid of him. They thought he was only pretending to be a believer!', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 27, 'Then Barnabas brought him to the apostles and told them how Saul had seen the Lord on the way to Damascus. Barnabas also told them what the Lord had said to Saul and how he boldly preached in the name of Jesus in Damascus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 28, 'Then the apostles accepted Saul, and after that he was constantly with them in Jerusalem, preaching boldly in the name of the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 29, 'He debated with some Greek-speaking Jews, but they plotted to murder him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 30, 'When the believers heard about it, however, they took him to Caesarea and sent him on to his hometown of Tarsus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 31, 'The church then had peace throughout Judea, Galilee, and Samaria, and it grew in strength and numbers. The believers were walking in the fear of the Lord and in the comfort of the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 32, 'Peter traveled from place to place to visit the believers, and in his travels he came to the Lord''s people in the town of Lydda.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 33, 'There he met a man named Aeneas, who had been paralyzed and bedridden for eight years.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 34, 'Peter said to him, "Aeneas, Jesus Christ heals you! Get up and make your bed!" And he was healed instantly.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 35, 'Then the whole population of Lydda and Sharon turned to the Lord when they saw Aeneas walking around.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 36, 'There was a believer in Joppa named Tabitha (which in Greek is Dorcas ). She was always doing kind things for others and helping the poor.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 37, 'About this time she became ill and died. Her friends prepared her for burial and laid her in an upstairs room.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 38, 'But they had heard that Peter was nearby at Lydda, so they sent two men to beg him, "Please come as soon as possible!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 39, 'So Peter returned with them; and as soon as he arrived, they took him to the upstairs room. The room was filled with widows who were weeping and showing him the coats and other garments Dorcas had made for them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 40, 'But Peter asked them all to leave the room; then he knelt and prayed. Turning to the body he said, "Get up, Tabitha." And she opened her eyes! When she saw Peter, she sat up!', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 41, 'He gave her his hand and helped her up. Then he called in the widows and all the believers, and he showed them that she was alive.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 42, 'The news raced through the whole town, and many believed in the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(7, 9, 43, 'And Peter stayed a long time in Joppa, living with Simon, a leatherworker.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 1, 'In Caesarea there lived a Roman army officer named Cornelius, who was a captain of the Italian Regiment.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 2, 'He was a devout man who feared the God of Israel, as did his entire household. He gave generously to charity and was a man who regularly prayed to God.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 3, 'One afternoon about three o''clock, he had a vision in which he saw an angel of God coming toward him. "Cornelius!" the angel said.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 4, 'Cornelius stared at him in terror. "What is it, sir?" he asked the angel. And the angel replied, "Your prayers and gifts to the poor have not gone unnoticed by God!', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 5, 'Now send some men down to Joppa to find a man named Simon Peter.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 6, 'He is staying with Simon, a leatherworker who lives near the shore. Ask him to come and visit you."', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 7, 'As soon as the angel was gone, Cornelius called two of his household servants and a devout soldier, one of his personal attendants.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 8, 'He told them what had happened and sent them off to Joppa.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 9, 'The next day as Cornelius''s messengers were nearing the city, Peter went up to the flat roof to pray. It was about noon,', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 10, 'and he was hungry. But while lunch was being prepared, he fell into a trance.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 11, 'He saw the sky open, and something like a large sheet was let down by its four corners.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 12, 'In the sheet were all sorts of animals, reptiles, and birds.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 13, 'Then a voice said to him, "Get up, Peter; kill and eat them."', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 14, '"Never, Lord," Peter declared. "I have never in all my life eaten anything forbidden by our Jewish laws. "', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 15, 'The voice spoke again, "If God says something is acceptable, don''t say it isn''t."', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 16, 'The same vision was repeated three times. Then the sheet was pulled up again to heaven.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 17, 'Peter was very perplexed. What could the vision mean? Just then the men sent by Cornelius found the house and stood outside at the gate.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 18, 'They asked if this was the place where Simon Peter was staying.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 19, 'Meanwhile, as Peter was puzzling over the vision, the Holy Spirit said to him, "Three men have come looking for you.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 20, 'Go down and go with them without hesitation. All is well, for I have sent them."', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 21, 'So Peter went down and said, "I''m the man you are looking for. Why have you come?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 22, 'They said, "We were sent by Cornelius, a Roman officer. He is a devout man who fears the God of Israel and is well respected by all the Jews. A holy angel instructed him to send for you so you can go to his house and give him a message."', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 23, 'So Peter invited the men to be his guests for the night. The next day he went with them, accompanied by some other believers from Joppa.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 24, 'They arrived in Caesarea the following day. Cornelius was waiting for him and had called together his relatives and close friends to meet Peter.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 25, 'As Peter entered his home, Cornelius fell to the floor before him in worship.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 26, 'But Peter pulled him up and said, "Stand up! I''m a human being like you!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 27, 'So Cornelius got up, and they talked together and went inside where the others were assembled.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 28, 'Peter told them, "You know it is against the Jewish laws for me to come into a Gentile home like this. But God has shown me that I should never think of anyone as impure.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 29, 'So I came as soon as I was sent for. Now tell me why you sent for me."', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 30, 'Cornelius replied, "Four days ago I was praying in my house at three o''clock in the afternoon. Suddenly, a man in dazzling clothes was standing in front of me.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 31, 'He told me, ''Cornelius, your prayers have been heard, and your gifts to the poor have been noticed by God!', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 32, 'Now send some men to Joppa and summon Simon Peter. He is staying in the home of Simon, a leatherworker who lives near the shore.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 33, 'So I sent for you at once, and it was good of you to come. Now here we are, waiting before God to hear the message the Lord has given you."', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 34, 'Then Peter replied, "I see very clearly that God doesn''t show partiality.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 35, 'In every nation he accepts those who fear him and do what is right.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 36, 'I''m sure you have heard about the Good News for the people of Israel--that there is peace with God through Jesus Christ, who is Lord of all.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 37, 'You know what happened all through Judea, beginning in Galilee after John the Baptist began preaching.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 38, 'And no doubt you know that God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Spirit and with power. Then Jesus went around doing good and healing all who were oppressed by the Devil, for God was with him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 39, '"And we apostles are witnesses of all he did throughout Israel and in Jerusalem. They put him to death by crucifying him,', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 40, 'but God raised him to life three days later. Then God allowed him to appear,', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 41, 'not to the general public, but to us whom God had chosen beforehand to be his witnesses. We were those who ate and drank with him after he rose from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 42, 'And he ordered us to preach everywhere and to testify that Jesus is ordained of God to be the judge of all--the living and the dead.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 43, 'He is the one all the prophets testified about, saying that everyone who believes in him will have their sins forgiven through his name."', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 44, 'Even as Peter was saying these things, the Holy Spirit fell upon all who had heard the message.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 45, 'The Jewish believers who came with Peter were amazed that the gift of the Holy Spirit had been poured out upon the Gentiles, too.', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 46, 'And there could be no doubt about it, for they heard them speaking in tongues and praising God. Then Peter asked,', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 47, '"Can anyone object to their being baptized, now that they have received the Holy Spirit just as we did?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 10, 48, 'So he gave orders for them to be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ. Afterward Cornelius asked him to stay with them for several days.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 1, 'Soon the news reached the apostles and other believers in Judea that the Gentiles had received the word of God.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 2, 'But when Peter arrived back in Jerusalem, some of the Jewish believers criticized him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 3, '"You entered the home of Gentiles and even ate with them!" they said.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 4, 'Then Peter told them exactly what had happened.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 5, '"One day in Joppa," he said, "while I was praying, I went into a trance and saw a vision. Something like a large sheet was let down by its four corners from the sky. And it came right down to me.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 6, 'When I looked inside the sheet, I saw all sorts of small animals, wild animals, reptiles, and birds that we are not allowed to eat.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 7, 'And I heard a voice say, ''Get up, Peter; kill and eat them.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 8, '"''Never, Lord,'' I replied. ''I have never eaten anything forbidden by our Jewish laws. ''', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 9, '"But the voice from heaven came again, ''If God says something is acceptable, don''t say it isn''t.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 10, '"This happened three times before the sheet and all it contained was pulled back up to heaven.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 11, 'Just then three men who had been sent from Caesarea arrived at the house where I was staying.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 12, 'The Holy Spirit told me to go with them and not to worry about their being Gentiles. These six brothers here accompanied me, and we soon arrived at the home of the man who had sent for us.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 13, 'He told us how an angel had appeared to him in his home and had told him, ''Send messengers to Joppa to find Simon Peter.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 14, 'He will tell you how you and all your household will be saved!''', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 15, '"Well, I began telling them the Good News, but just as I was getting started, the Holy Spirit fell on them, just as he fell on us at the beginning.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 16, 'Then I thought of the Lord''s words when he said, ''John baptized with water, but you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 17, 'And since God gave these Gentiles the same gift he gave us when we believed in the Lord Jesus Christ, who was I to argue?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 18, 'When the others heard this, all their objections were answered and they began praising God. They said, "God has also given the Gentiles the privilege of turning from sin and receiving eternal life."', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 19, 'Meanwhile, the believers who had fled from Jerusalem during the persecution after Stephen''s death traveled as far as Phoenicia, Cyprus, and Antioch of Syria. They preached the Good News, but only to Jews.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 20, 'However, some of the believers who went to Antioch from Cyprus and Cyrene began preaching to Gentiles about the Lord Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 21, 'The power of the Lord was upon them, and large numbers of these Gentiles believed and turned to the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 22, 'When the church at Jerusalem heard what had happened, they sent Barnabas to Antioch.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 23, 'When he arrived and saw this proof of God''s favor, he was filled with joy, and he encouraged the believers to stay true to the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 24, 'Barnabas was a good man, full of the Holy Spirit and strong in faith. And large numbers of people were brought to the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 25, 'Then Barnabas went on to Tarsus to find Saul.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 26, 'When he found him, he brought him back to Antioch. Both of them stayed there with the church for a full year, teaching great numbers of people. (It was there at Antioch that the believers were first called Christians.)', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 27, 'During this time, some prophets traveled from Jerusalem to Antioch.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 28, 'One of them named Agabus stood up in one of the meetings to predict by the Spirit that a great famine was coming upon the entire Roman world. (This was fulfilled during the reign of Claudius.)', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 29, 'So the believers in Antioch decided to send relief to the brothers and sisters in Judea, everyone giving as much as they could.', 'NLT'),
(7, 11, 30, 'This they did, entrusting their gifts to Barnabas and Saul to take to the elders of the church in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 1, 'About that time King Herod Agrippa began to persecute some believers in the church.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 2, 'He had the apostle James (John''s brother) killed with a sword.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 3, 'When Herod saw how much this pleased the Jewish leaders, he arrested Peter during the Passover celebration', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 4, 'and imprisoned him, placing him under the guard of four squads of four soldiers each. Herod''s intention was to bring Peter out for public trial after the Passover.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 5, 'But while Peter was in prison, the church prayed very earnestly for him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 6, 'The night before Peter was to be placed on trial, he was asleep, chained between two soldiers, with others standing guard at the prison gate.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 7, 'Suddenly, there was a bright light in the cell, and an angel of the Lord stood before Peter. The angel tapped him on the side to awaken him and said, "Quick! Get up!" And the chains fell off his wrists.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 8, 'Then the angel told him, "Get dressed and put on your sandals." And he did. "Now put on your coat and follow me," the angel ordered.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 9, 'So Peter left the cell, following the angel. But all the time he thought it was a vision. He didn''t realize it was really happening.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 10, 'They passed the first and second guard posts and came to the iron gate to the street, and this opened to them all by itself. So they passed through and started walking down the street, and then the angel suddenly left him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 11, 'Peter finally realized what had happened. "It''s really true!" he said to himself. "The Lord has sent his angel and saved me from Herod and from what the Jews were hoping to do to me!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 12, 'After a little thought, he went to the home of Mary, the mother of John Mark, where many were gathered for prayer.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 13, 'He knocked at the door in the gate, and a servant girl named Rhoda came to open it.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 14, 'When she recognized Peter''s voice, she was so overjoyed that, instead of opening the door, she ran back inside and told everyone, "Peter is standing at the door!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 15, '"You''re out of your mind," they said. When she insisted, they decided, "It must be his angel."', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 16, 'Meanwhile, Peter continued knocking. When they finally went out and opened the door, they were amazed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 17, 'He motioned for them to quiet down and told them what had happened and how the Lord had led him out of jail. "Tell James and the other brothers what happened," he said. And then he went to another place.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 18, 'At dawn, there was a great commotion among the soldiers about what had happened to Peter.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 19, 'Herod Agrippa ordered a thorough search for him. When he couldn''t be found, Herod interrogated the guards and sentenced them to death. Afterward Herod left Judea to stay in Caesarea for a while.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 20, 'Now Herod was very angry with the people of Tyre and Sidon. So they sent a delegation to make peace with him because their cities were dependent upon Herod''s country for their food. They made friends with Blastus, Herod''s personal assistant,', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 21, 'and an appointment with Herod was granted. When the day arrived, Herod put on his royal robes, sat on his throne, and made a speech to them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 22, 'The people gave him a great ovation, shouting, "It is the voice of a god, not of a man!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 23, 'Instantly, an angel of the Lord struck Herod with a sickness, because he accepted the people''s worship instead of giving the glory to God. So he was consumed with worms and died.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 24, 'But God''s Good News was spreading rapidly, and there were many new believers.', 'NLT'),
(7, 12, 25, 'When Barnabas and Saul had finished their mission in Jerusalem, they returned to Antioch, taking John Mark with them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 1, 'Among the prophets and teachers of the church at Antioch of Syria were Barnabas, Simeon (called "the black man" ), Lucius (from Cyrene), Manaen (the childhood companion of King Herod Antipas ), and Saul.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 2, 'One day as these men were worshiping the Lord and fasting, the Holy Spirit said, "Dedicate Barnabas and Saul for the special work I have for them."', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 3, 'So after more fasting and prayer, the men laid their hands on them and sent them on their way.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 4, 'Sent out by the Holy Spirit, Saul and Barnabas went down to the seaport of Seleucia and then sailed for the island of Cyprus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 5, 'There, in the town of Salamis, they went to the Jewish synagogues and preached the word of God. (John Mark went with them as their assistant.)', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 6, 'Afterward they preached from town to town across the entire island until finally they reached Paphos, where they met a Jewish sorcerer, a false prophet named Bar-Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 7, 'He had attached himself to the governor, Sergius Paulus, a man of considerable insight and understanding. The governor invited Barnabas and Saul to visit him, for he wanted to hear the word of God.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 8, 'But Elymas, the sorcerer (as his name means in Greek), interfered and urged the governor to pay no attention to what Saul and Barnabas said. He was trying to turn the governor away from the Christian faith.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 9, 'Then Saul, also known as Paul, filled with the Holy Spirit, looked the sorcerer in the eye and said,', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 10, '"You son of the Devil, full of every sort of trickery and villainy, enemy of all that is good, will you never stop perverting the true ways of the Lord?', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 11, 'And now the Lord has laid his hand of punishment upon you, and you will be stricken awhile with blindness." Instantly mist and darkness fell upon him, and he began wandering around begging for someone to take his hand and lead him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 12, 'When the governor saw what had happened, he believed and was astonished at what he learned about the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 13, 'Now Paul and those with him left Paphos by ship for Pamphylia, landing at the port town of Perga. There John Mark left them and returned to Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 14, 'But Barnabas and Paul traveled inland to Antioch of Pisidia. On the Sabbath they went to the synagogue for the services.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 15, 'After the usual readings from the books of Moses and from the Prophets, those in charge of the service sent them this message: "Brothers, if you have any word of encouragement for us, come and give it!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 16, 'So Paul stood, lifted his hand to quiet them, and started speaking. "People of Israel," he said, "and you devout Gentiles who fear the God of Israel, listen to me.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 17, '"The God of this nation of Israel chose our ancestors and made them prosper in Egypt. Then he powerfully led them out of their slavery.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 18, 'He put up with them through forty years of wandering around in the wilderness.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 19, 'Then he destroyed seven nations in Canaan and gave their land to Israel as an inheritance.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 20, 'All this took about 450 years. After that, judges ruled until the time of Samuel the prophet.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 21, 'Then the people begged for a king, and God gave them Saul son of Kish, a man of the tribe of Benjamin, who reigned for forty years.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 22, 'But God removed him from the kingship and replaced him with David, a man about whom God said, ''David son of Jesse is a man after my own heart, for he will do everything I want him to.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 23, '"And it is one of King David''s descendants, Jesus, who is God''s promised Savior of Israel!', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 24, 'But before he came, John the Baptist preached the need for everyone in Israel to turn from sin and turn to God and be baptized.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 25, 'As John was finishing his ministry he asked, ''Do you think I am the Messiah? No! But he is coming soon--and I am not even worthy to be his slave. ''', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 26, '"Brothers--you sons of Abraham, and also all of you devout Gentiles who fear the God of Israel--this salvation is for us!', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 27, 'The people in Jerusalem and their leaders fulfilled prophecy by condemning Jesus to death. They didn''t recognize him or realize that he is the one the prophets had written about, though they hear the prophets'' words read every Sabbath.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 28, 'They found no just cause to execute him, but they asked Pilate to have him killed anyway.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 29, '"When they had fulfilled all the prophecies concerning his death, they took him down from the cross and placed him in a tomb.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 30, 'But God raised him from the dead!', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 31, 'And he appeared over a period of many days to those who had gone with him from Galilee to Jerusalem--these are his witnesses to the people of Israel.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 32, '"And now Barnabas and I are here to bring you this Good News. God''s promise to our ancestors has come true in our own time,', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 33, 'in that God raised Jesus. This is what the second psalm is talking about when it says concerning Jesus, ''You are my Son. Today I have become your Father. ''', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 34, 'For God had promised to raise him from the dead, never again to die. This is stated in the Scripture that says, ''I will give you the sacred blessings I promised to David.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 35, 'Another psalm explains more fully, saying, ''You will not allow your Holy One to rot in the grave.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 36, 'Now this is not a reference to David, for after David had served his generation according to the will of God, he died and was buried, and his body decayed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 37, 'No, it was a reference to someone else--someone whom God raised and whose body did not decay.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 38, '"Brothers, listen! In this man Jesus there is forgiveness for your sins.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 39, 'Everyone who believes in him is freed from all guilt and declared right with God--something the Jewish law could never do.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 40, 'Be careful! Don''t let the prophets'' words apply to you. For they said,', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 41, '''Look, you mockers, be amazed and die! For I am doing something in your own day, something you wouldn''t believe even if someone told you about it.''"', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 42, 'As Paul and Barnabas left the synagogue that day, the people asked them to return again and speak about these things the next week.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 43, 'Many Jews and godly converts to Judaism who worshiped at the synagogue followed Paul and Barnabas, and the two men urged them, "By God''s grace, remain faithful."', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 44, 'The following week almost the entire city turned out to hear them preach the word of the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 45, 'But when the Jewish leaders saw the crowds, they were jealous; so they slandered Paul and argued against whatever he said.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 46, 'Then Paul and Barnabas spoke out boldly and declared, "It was necessary that this Good News from God be given first to you Jews. But since you have rejected it and judged yourselves unworthy of eternal life--well, we will offer it to Gentiles.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 47, 'For this is as the Lord commanded us when he said, ''I have made you a light to the Gentiles, to bring salvation to the farthest corners of the earth.''"', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 48, 'When the Gentiles heard this, they were very glad and thanked the Lord for his message; and all who were appointed to eternal life became believers.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 49, 'So the Lord''s message spread throughout that region.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 50, 'Then the Jewish leaders stirred up both the influential religious women and the leaders of the city, and they incited a mob against Paul and Barnabas and ran them out of town.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 51, 'But they shook off the dust of their feet against them and went to the city of Iconium.', 'NLT'),
(7, 13, 52, 'And the believers were filled with joy and with the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 1, 'In Iconium, Paul and Barnabas went together to the synagogue and preached with such power that a great number of both Jews and Gentiles believed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 2, 'But the Jews who spurned God''s message stirred up distrust among the Gentiles against Paul and Barnabas, saying all sorts of evil things about them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 3, 'The apostles stayed there a long time, preaching boldly about the grace of the Lord. The Lord proved their message was true by giving them power to do miraculous signs and wonders.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 4, 'But the people of the city were divided in their opinion about them. Some sided with the Jews, and some with the apostles.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 5, 'A mob of Gentiles and Jews, along with their leaders, decided to attack and stone them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 6, 'When the apostles learned of it, they fled for their lives. They went to the region of Lycaonia, to the cities of Lystra and Derbe and the surrounding area,', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 7, 'and they preached the Good News there.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 8, 'While they were at Lystra, Paul and Barnabas came upon a man with crippled feet. He had been that way from birth, so he had never walked.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 9, 'He was listening as Paul preached, and Paul noticed him and realized he had faith to be healed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 10, 'So Paul called to him in a loud voice, "Stand up!" And the man jumped to his feet and started walking.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 11, 'When the listening crowd saw what Paul had done, they shouted in their local dialect, "These men are gods in human bodies!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 12, 'They decided that Barnabas was the Greek god Zeus and that Paul, because he was the chief speaker, was Hermes.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 13, 'The temple of Zeus was located on the outskirts of the city. The priest of the temple and the crowd brought oxen and wreaths of flowers, and they prepared to sacrifice to the apostles at the city gates.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 14, 'But when Barnabas and Paul heard what was happening, they tore their clothing in dismay and ran out among the people, shouting,', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 15, '"Friends, why are you doing this? We are merely human beings like yourselves! We have come to bring you the Good News that you should turn from these worthless things to the living God, who made heaven and earth, the sea, and everything in them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 16, 'In earlier days he permitted all the nations to go their own ways,', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 17, 'but he never left himself without a witness. There were always his reminders, such as sending you rain and good crops and giving you food and joyful hearts."', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 18, 'But even so, Paul and Barnabas could scarcely restrain the people from sacrificing to them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 19, 'Now some Jews arrived from Antioch and Iconium and turned the crowds into a murderous mob. They stoned Paul and dragged him out of the city, apparently dead.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 20, 'But as the believers stood around him, he got up and went back into the city. The next day he left with Barnabas for Derbe.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 21, 'After preaching the Good News in Derbe and making many disciples, Paul and Barnabas returned again to Lystra, Iconium, and Antioch of Pisidia,', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 22, 'where they strengthened the believers. They encouraged them to continue in the faith, reminding them that they must enter into the Kingdom of God through many tribulations.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 23, 'Paul and Barnabas also appointed elders in every church and prayed for them with fasting, turning them over to the care of the Lord, in whom they had come to trust.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 24, 'Then they traveled back through Pisidia to Pamphylia.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 25, 'They preached again in Perga, then went on to Attalia.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 26, 'Finally, they returned by ship to Antioch of Syria, where their journey had begun and where they had been committed to the grace of God for the work they had now completed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 27, 'Upon arriving in Antioch, they called the church together and reported about their trip, telling all that God had done and how he had opened the door of faith to the Gentiles, too.', 'NLT'),
(7, 14, 28, 'And they stayed there with the believers in Antioch for a long time.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 1, 'While Paul and Barnabas were at Antioch of Syria, some men from Judea arrived and began to teach the Christians: "Unless you keep the ancient Jewish custom of circumcision taught by Moses, you cannot be saved."', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 2, 'Paul and Barnabas, disagreeing with them, argued forcefully and at length. Finally, Paul and Barnabas were sent to Jerusalem, accompanied by some local believers, to talk to the apostles and elders about this question.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 3, 'The church sent the delegates to Jerusalem, and they stopped along the way in Phoenicia and Samaria to visit the believers. They told them--much to everyone''s joy--that the Gentiles, too, were being converted.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 4, 'When they arrived in Jerusalem, Paul and Barnabas were welcomed by the whole church, including the apostles and elders. They reported on what God had been doing through their ministry.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 5, 'But then some of the men who had been Pharisees before their conversion stood up and declared that all Gentile converts must be circumcised and be required to follow the law of Moses.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 6, 'So the apostles and church elders got together to decide this question.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 7, 'At the meeting, after a long discussion, Peter stood and addressed them as follows: "Brothers, you all know that God chose me from among you some time ago to preach to the Gentiles so that they could hear the Good News and believe.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 8, 'God, who knows people''s hearts, confirmed that he accepts Gentiles by giving them the Holy Spirit, just as he gave him to us.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 9, 'He made no distinction between us and them, for he also cleansed their hearts through faith.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 10, 'Why are you now questioning God''s way by burdening the Gentile believers with a yoke that neither we nor our ancestors were able to bear?', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 11, 'We believe that we are all saved the same way, by the special favor of the Lord Jesus."', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 12, 'There was no further discussion, and everyone listened as Barnabas and Paul told about the miraculous signs and wonders God had done through them among the Gentiles.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 13, 'When they had finished, James stood and said, "Brothers, listen to me.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 14, 'Peter has told you about the time God first visited the Gentiles to take from them a people for himself.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 15, 'And this conversion of Gentiles agrees with what the prophets predicted. For instance, it is written:', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 16, '''Afterward I will return, and I will restore the fallen kingdom of David. From the ruins I will rebuild it, and I will restore it,', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 17, 'so that the rest of humanity might find the Lord, including the Gentiles--all those I have called to be mine. This is what the Lord says,', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 18, 'he who made these things known long ago.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 19, 'And so my judgment is that we should stop troubling the Gentiles who turn to God,', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 20, 'except that we should write to them and tell them to abstain from eating meat sacrificed to idols, from sexual immorality, and from consuming blood or eating the meat of strangled animals.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 21, 'For these laws of Moses have been preached in Jewish synagogues in every city on every Sabbath for many generations."', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 22, 'Then the apostles and elders and the whole church in Jerusalem chose delegates, and they sent them to Antioch of Syria with Paul and Barnabas to report on this decision. The men chosen were two of the church leaders--Judas (also called Barsabbas) and Silas.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 23, 'This is the letter they took along with them: "This letter is from the apostles and elders, your brothers in Jerusalem. It is written to the Gentile believers in Antioch, Syria, and Cilicia. Greetings!', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 24, '"We understand that some men from here have troubled you and upset you with their teaching, but they had no such instructions from us.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 25, 'So it seemed good to us, having unanimously agreed on our decision, to send you these official representatives, along with our beloved Barnabas and Paul,', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 26, 'who have risked their lives for the sake of our Lord Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 27, 'So we are sending Judas and Silas to tell you what we have decided concerning your question.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 28, '"For it seemed good to the Holy Spirit and to us to lay no greater burden on you than these requirements:', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 29, 'You must abstain from eating food offered to idols, from consuming blood or eating the meat of strangled animals, and from sexual immorality. If you do this, you will do well. Farewell."', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 30, 'The four messengers went at once to Antioch, where they called a general meeting of the Christians and delivered the letter.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 31, 'And there was great joy throughout the church that day as they read this encouraging message.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 32, 'Then Judas and Silas, both being prophets, spoke extensively to the Christians, encouraging and strengthening their faith.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 33, 'They stayed for a while, and then Judas and Silas were sent back to Jerusalem, with the blessings of the Christians, to those who had sent them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 34, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 35, 'Paul and Barnabas stayed in Antioch to assist many others who were teaching and preaching the word of the Lord there.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 36, 'After some time Paul said to Barnabas, "Let''s return to each city where we previously preached the word of the Lord, to see how the new believers are getting along."', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 37, 'Barnabas agreed and wanted to take along John Mark.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 38, 'But Paul disagreed strongly, since John Mark had deserted them in Pamphylia and had not shared in their work.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 39, 'Their disagreement over this was so sharp that they separated. Barnabas took John Mark with him and sailed for Cyprus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 40, 'Paul chose Silas, and the believers sent them off, entrusting them to the Lord''s grace.', 'NLT'),
(7, 15, 41, 'So they traveled throughout Syria and Cilicia to strengthen the churches there.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 1, 'Paul and Silas went first to Derbe and then on to Lystra. There they met Timothy, a young disciple whose mother was a Jewish believer, but whose father was a Greek.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 2, 'Timothy was well thought of by the believers in Lystra and Iconium,', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 3, 'so Paul wanted him to join them on their journey. In deference to the Jews of the area, he arranged for Timothy to be circumcised before they left, for everyone knew that his father was a Greek.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 4, 'Then they went from town to town, explaining the decision regarding the commandments that were to be obeyed, as decided by the apostles and elders in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 5, 'So the churches were strengthened in their faith and grew daily in numbers.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 6, 'Next Paul and Silas traveled through the area of Phrygia and Galatia, because the Holy Spirit had told them not to go into the province of Asia at that time.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 7, 'Then coming to the borders of Mysia, they headed for the province of Bithynia, but again the Spirit of Jesus did not let them go.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 8, 'So instead, they went on through Mysia to the city of Troas.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 9, 'That night Paul had a vision. He saw a man from Macedonia in northern Greece, pleading with him, "Come over here and help us."', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 10, 'So we decided to leave for Macedonia at once, for we could only conclude that God was calling us to preach the Good News there.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 11, 'We boarded a boat at Troas and sailed straight across to the island of Samothrace, and the next day we landed at Neapolis.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 12, 'From there we reached Philippi, a major city of the district of Macedonia and a Roman colony; we stayed there several days.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 13, 'On the Sabbath we went a little way outside the city to a riverbank, where we supposed that some people met for prayer, and we sat down to speak with some women who had come together.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 14, 'One of them was Lydia from Thyatira, a merchant of expensive purple cloth. She was a worshiper of God. As she listened to us, the Lord opened her heart, and she accepted what Paul was saying.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 15, 'She was baptized along with other members of her household, and she asked us to be her guests. "If you agree that I am faithful to the Lord," she said, "come and stay at my home." And she urged us until we did.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 16, 'One day as we were going down to the place of prayer, we met a demon-possessed slave girl. She was a fortune-teller who earned a lot of money for her masters.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 17, 'She followed along behind us shouting, "These men are servants of the Most High God, and they have come to tell you how to be saved."', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 18, 'This went on day after day until Paul got so exasperated that he turned and spoke to the demon within her. "I command you in the name of Jesus Christ to come out of her," he said. And instantly it left her.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 19, 'Her masters'' hopes of wealth were now shattered, so they grabbed Paul and Silas and dragged them before the authorities at the marketplace.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 20, '"The whole city is in an uproar because of these Jews!" they shouted.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 21, '"They are teaching the people to do things that are against Roman customs."', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 22, 'A mob quickly formed against Paul and Silas, and the city officials ordered them stripped and beaten with wooden rods.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 23, 'They were severely beaten, and then they were thrown into prison. The jailer was ordered to make sure they didn''t escape.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 24, 'So he took no chances but put them into the inner dungeon and clamped their feet in the stocks.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 25, 'Around midnight, Paul and Silas were praying and singing hymns to God, and the other prisoners were listening.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 26, 'Suddenly, there was a great earthquake, and the prison was shaken to its foundations. All the doors flew open, and the chains of every prisoner fell off!', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 27, 'The jailer woke up to see the prison doors wide open. He assumed the prisoners had escaped, so he drew his sword to kill himself.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 28, 'But Paul shouted to him, "Don''t do it! We are all here!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 29, 'Trembling with fear, the jailer called for lights and ran to the dungeon and fell down before Paul and Silas.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 30, 'He brought them out and asked, "Sirs, what must I do to be saved?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 31, 'They replied, "Believe on the Lord Jesus and you will be saved, along with your entire household."', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 32, 'Then they shared the word of the Lord with him and all who lived in his household.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 33, 'That same hour the jailer washed their wounds, and he and everyone in his household were immediately baptized.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 34, 'Then he brought them into his house and set a meal before them. He and his entire household rejoiced because they all believed in God.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 35, 'The next morning the city officials sent the police to tell the jailer, "Let those men go!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 36, 'So the jailer told Paul, "You and Silas are free to leave. Go in peace."', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 37, 'But Paul replied, "They have publicly beaten us without trial and jailed us--and we are Roman citizens. So now they want us to leave secretly? Certainly not! Let them come themselves to release us!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 38, 'When the police made their report, the city officials were alarmed to learn that Paul and Silas were Roman citizens.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 39, 'They came to the jail and apologized to them. Then they brought them out and begged them to leave the city.', 'NLT'),
(7, 16, 40, 'Paul and Silas then returned to the home of Lydia, where they met with the believers and encouraged them once more before leaving town.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 1, 'Now Paul and Silas traveled through the towns of Amphipolis and Apollonia and came to Thessalonica, where there was a Jewish synagogue.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 2, 'As was Paul''s custom, he went to the synagogue service, and for three Sabbaths in a row he interpreted the Scriptures to the people.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 3, 'He was explaining and proving the prophecies about the sufferings of the Messiah and his rising from the dead. He said, "This Jesus I''m telling you about is the Messiah."', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 4, 'Some who listened were persuaded and became converts, including a large number of godly Greek men and also many important women of the city.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 5, 'But the Jewish leaders were jealous, so they gathered some worthless fellows from the streets to form a mob and start a riot. They attacked the home of Jason, searching for Paul and Silas so they could drag them out to the crowd.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 6, 'Not finding them there, they dragged out Jason and some of the other believers instead and took them before the city council. "Paul and Silas have turned the rest of the world upside down, and now they are here disturbing our city," they shouted.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 7, '"And Jason has let them into his home. They are all guilty of treason against Caesar, for they profess allegiance to another king, Jesus."', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 8, 'The people of the city, as well as the city officials, were thrown into turmoil by these reports.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 9, 'But the officials released Jason and the other believers after they had posted bail.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 10, 'That very night the believers sent Paul and Silas to Berea. When they arrived there, they went to the synagogue.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 11, 'And the people of Berea were more open-minded than those in Thessalonica, and they listened eagerly to Paul''s message. They searched the Scriptures day after day to check up on Paul and Silas, to see if they were really teaching the truth.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 12, 'As a result, many Jews believed, as did some of the prominent Greek women and many men.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 13, 'But when some Jews in Thessalonica learned that Paul was preaching the word of God in Berea, they went there and stirred up trouble.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 14, 'The believers acted at once, sending Paul on to the coast, while Silas and Timothy remained behind.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 15, 'Those escorting Paul went with him to Athens; then they returned to Berea with a message for Silas and Timothy to hurry and join him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 16, 'While Paul was waiting for them in Athens, he was deeply troubled by all the idols he saw everywhere in the city.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 17, 'He went to the synagogue to debate with the Jews and the God-fearing Gentiles, and he spoke daily in the public square to all who happened to be there.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 18, 'He also had a debate with some of the Epicurean and Stoic philosophers. When he told them about Jesus and his resurrection, they said, "This babbler has picked up some strange ideas." Others said, "He''s pushing some foreign religion."', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 19, 'Then they took him to the Council of Philosophers. "Come and tell us more about this new religion," they said.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 20, '"You are saying some rather startling things, and we want to know what it''s all about."', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 21, '(It should be explained that all the Athenians as well as the foreigners in Athens seemed to spend all their time discussing the latest ideas.)', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 22, 'So Paul, standing before the Council, addressed them as follows: "Men of Athens, I notice that you are very religious,', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 23, 'for as I was walking along I saw your many altars. And one of them had this inscription on it--''To an Unknown God.'' You have been worshiping him without knowing who he is, and now I wish to tell you about him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 24, '"He is the God who made the world and everything in it. Since he is Lord of heaven and earth, he doesn''t live in man-made temples,', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 25, 'and human hands can''t serve his needs--for he has no needs. He himself gives life and breath to everything, and he satisfies every need there is.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 26, 'From one man he created all the nations throughout the whole earth. He decided beforehand which should rise and fall, and he determined their boundaries.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 27, '"His purpose in all of this was that the nations should seek after God and perhaps feel their way toward him and find him--though he is not far from any one of us.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 28, 'For in him we live and move and exist. As one of your own poets says, ''We are his offspring.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 29, 'And since this is true, we shouldn''t think of God as an idol designed by craftsmen from gold or silver or stone.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 30, 'God overlooked people''s former ignorance about these things, but now he commands everyone everywhere to turn away from idols and turn to him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 31, 'For he has set a day for judging the world with justice by the man he has appointed, and he proved to everyone who this is by raising him from the dead."', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 32, 'When they heard Paul speak of the resurrection of a person who had been dead, some laughed, but others said, "We want to hear more about this later."', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 33, 'That ended Paul''s discussion with them,', 'NLT'),
(7, 17, 34, 'but some joined him and became believers. Among them were Dionysius, a member of the Council, a woman named Damaris, and others.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 1, 'Then Paul left Athens and went to Corinth.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 2, 'There he became acquainted with a Jew named Aquila, born in Pontus, who had recently arrived from Italy with his wife, Priscilla. They had been expelled from Italy as a result of Claudius Caesar''s order to deport all Jews from Rome.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 3, 'Paul lived and worked with them, for they were tentmakers just as he was.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 4, 'Each Sabbath found Paul at the synagogue, trying to convince the Jews and Greeks alike.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 5, 'And after Silas and Timothy came down from Macedonia, Paul spent his full time preaching and testifying to the Jews, telling them, "The Messiah you are looking for is Jesus."', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 6, 'But when the Jews opposed him and insulted him, Paul shook the dust from his robe and said, "Your blood be upon your own heads--I am innocent. From now on I will go to the Gentiles."', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 7, 'After that he stayed with Titius Justus, a Gentile who worshiped God and lived next door to the synagogue.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 8, 'Crispus, the leader of the synagogue, and all his household believed in the Lord. Many others in Corinth also became believers and were baptized.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 9, 'One night the Lord spoke to Paul in a vision and told him, "Don''t be afraid! Speak out! Don''t be silent!', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 10, 'For I am with you, and no one will harm you because many people here in this city belong to me."', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 11, 'So Paul stayed there for the next year and a half, teaching the word of God.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 12, 'But when Gallio became governor of Achaia, some Jews rose in concerted action against Paul and brought him before the governor for judgment.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 13, 'They accused Paul of "persuading people to worship God in ways that are contrary to the law."', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 14, 'But just as Paul started to make his defense, Gallio turned to Paul''s accusers and said, "Listen, you Jews, if this were a case involving some wrongdoing or a serious crime, I would be obliged to listen to you.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 15, 'But since it is merely a question of words and names and your Jewish laws, you take care of it. I refuse to judge such matters."', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 16, 'And he drove them out of the courtroom.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 17, 'The mob had grabbed Sosthenes, the leader of the synagogue, and had beaten him right there in the courtroom. But Gallio paid no attention.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 18, 'Paul stayed in Corinth for some time after that and then said good-bye to the brothers and sisters and sailed for the coast of Syria, taking Priscilla and Aquila with him. (Earlier, at Cenchrea, Paul had shaved his head according to Jewish custom, for he had taken a vow.)', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 19, 'When they arrived at the port of Ephesus, Paul left the others behind. But while he was there, he went to the synagogue to debate with the Jews.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 20, 'They asked him to stay longer, but he declined.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 21, 'So he left, saying, "I will come back later, God willing." Then he set sail from Ephesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 22, 'The next stop was at the port of Caesarea. From there he went up and visited the church at Jerusalem and then went back to Antioch.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 23, 'After spending some time in Antioch, Paul went back to Galatia and Phrygia, visiting all the believers, encouraging them and helping them to grow in the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 24, 'Meanwhile, a Jew named Apollos, an eloquent speaker who knew the Scriptures well, had just arrived in Ephesus from Alexandria in Egypt.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 25, 'He had been taught the way of the Lord and talked to others with great enthusiasm and accuracy about Jesus. However, he knew only about John''s baptism.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 26, 'When Priscilla and Aquila heard him preaching boldly in the synagogue, they took him aside and explained the way of God more accurately.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 27, 'Apollos had been thinking about going to Achaia, and the brothers and sisters in Ephesus encouraged him in this. They wrote to the believers in Achaia, asking them to welcome him. When he arrived there, he proved to be of great benefit to those who, by God''s grace, had believed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 18, 28, 'He refuted all the Jews with powerful arguments in public debate. Using the Scriptures, he explained to them, "The Messiah you are looking for is Jesus."', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 1, 'While Apollos was in Corinth, Paul traveled through the interior provinces. Finally, he came to Ephesus, where he found several believers.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 2, '"Did you receive the Holy Spirit when you believed?" he asked them. "No," they replied, "we don''t know what you mean. We haven''t even heard that there is a Holy Spirit."', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 3, '"Then what baptism did you experience?" he asked. And they replied, "The baptism of John."', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 4, 'Paul said, "John''s baptism was to demonstrate a desire to turn from sin and turn to God. John himself told the people to believe in Jesus, the one John said would come later."', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 5, 'As soon as they heard this, they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 6, 'Then when Paul laid his hands on them, the Holy Spirit came on them, and they spoke in other tongues and prophesied.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 7, 'There were about twelve men in all.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 8, 'Then Paul went to the synagogue and preached boldly for the next three months, arguing persuasively about the Kingdom of God.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 9, 'But some rejected his message and publicly spoke against the Way, so Paul left the synagogue and took the believers with him. Then he began preaching daily at the lecture hall of Tyrannus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 10, 'This went on for the next two years, so that people throughout the province of Asia--both Jews and Greeks--heard the Lord''s message.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 11, 'God gave Paul the power to do unusual miracles,', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 12, 'so that even when handkerchiefs or cloths that had touched his skin were placed on sick people, they were healed of their diseases, and any evil spirits within them came out.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 13, 'A team of Jews who were traveling from town to town casting out evil spirits tried to use the name of the Lord Jesus. The incantation they used was this: "I command you by Jesus, whom Paul preaches, to come out!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 14, 'Seven sons of Sceva, a leading priest, were doing this.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 15, 'But when they tried it on a man possessed by an evil spirit, the spirit replied, "I know Jesus, and I know Paul. But who are you?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 16, 'And he leaped on them and attacked them with such violence that they fled from the house, naked and badly injured.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 17, 'The story of what happened spread quickly all through Ephesus, to Jews and Greeks alike. A solemn fear descended on the city, and the name of the Lord Jesus was greatly honored.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 18, 'Many who became believers confessed their sinful practices.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 19, 'A number of them who had been practicing magic brought their incantation books and burned them at a public bonfire. The value of the books was several million dollars.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 20, 'So the message about the Lord spread widely and had a powerful effect.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 21, 'Afterward Paul felt impelled by the Holy Spirit to go over to Macedonia and Achaia before returning to Jerusalem. "And after that," he said, "I must go on to Rome!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 22, 'He sent his two assistants, Timothy and Erastus, on ahead to Macedonia while he stayed awhile longer in the province of Asia.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 23, 'But about that time, serious trouble developed in Ephesus concerning the Way.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 24, 'It began with Demetrius, a silversmith who had a large business manufacturing silver shrines of the Greek goddess Artemis. He kept many craftsmen busy.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 25, 'He called the craftsmen together, along with others employed in related trades, and addressed them as follows: "Gentlemen, you know that our wealth comes from this business.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 26, 'As you have seen and heard, this man Paul has persuaded many people that handmade gods aren''t gods at all. And this is happening not only here in Ephesus but throughout the entire province!', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 27, 'Of course, I''m not just talking about the loss of public respect for our business. I''m also concerned that the temple of the great goddess Artemis will lose its influence and that Artemis--this magnificent goddess worshiped throughout the province of Asia and all around the world--will be robbed of her prestige!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 28, 'At this their anger boiled, and they began shouting, "Great is Artemis of the Ephesians!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 29, 'A crowd began to gather, and soon the city was filled with confusion. Everyone rushed to the amphitheater, dragging along Gaius and Aristarchus, who were Paul''s traveling companions from Macedonia.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 30, 'Paul wanted to go in, but the believers wouldn''t let him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 31, 'Some of the officials of the province, friends of Paul, also sent a message to him, begging him not to risk his life by entering the amphitheater.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 32, 'Inside, the people were all shouting, some one thing and some another. Everything was in confusion. In fact, most of them didn''t even know why they were there.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 33, 'Alexander was thrust forward by some of the Jews, who encouraged him to explain the situation. He motioned for silence and tried to speak in defense.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 34, 'But when the crowd realized he was a Jew, they started shouting again and kept it up for two hours: "Great is Artemis of the Ephesians! Great is Artemis of the Ephesians!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 35, 'At last the mayor was able to quiet them down enough to speak. "Citizens of Ephesus," he said. "Everyone knows that Ephesus is the official guardian of the temple of the great Artemis, whose image fell down to us from heaven.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 36, 'Since this is an indisputable fact, you shouldn''t be disturbed, no matter what is said. Don''t do anything rash.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 37, 'You have brought these men here, but they have stolen nothing from the temple and have not spoken against our goddess.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 38, 'If Demetrius and the craftsmen have a case against them, the courts are in session and the judges can take the case at once. Let them go through legal channels.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 39, 'And if there are complaints about other matters, they can be settled in a legal assembly.', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 40, 'I am afraid we are in danger of being charged with rioting by the Roman government, since there is no cause for all this commotion. And if Rome demands an explanation, we won''t know what to say."', 'NLT'),
(7, 19, 41, 'Then he dismissed them, and they dispersed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 1, 'When it was all over, Paul sent for the believers and encouraged them. Then he said good-bye and left for Macedonia.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 2, 'Along the way, he encouraged the believers in all the towns he passed through. Then he traveled down to Greece,', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 3, 'where he stayed for three months. He was preparing to sail back to Syria when he discovered a plot by some Jews against his life, so he decided to return through Macedonia.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 4, 'Several men were traveling with him. They were Sopater of Berea, the son of Pyrrhus; Aristarchus and Secundus, from Thessalonica; Gaius, from Derbe; Timothy; and Tychicus and Trophimus, who were from the province of Asia.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 5, 'They went ahead and waited for us at Troas.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 6, 'As soon as the Passover season ended, we boarded a ship at Philippi in Macedonia and five days later arrived in Troas, where we stayed a week.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 7, 'On the first day of the week, we gathered to observe the Lord''s Supper. Paul was preaching; and since he was leaving the next day, he talked until midnight.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 8, 'The upstairs room where we met was lighted with many flickering lamps.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 9, 'As Paul spoke on and on, a young man named Eutychus, sitting on the windowsill, became very drowsy. Finally, he sank into a deep sleep and fell three stories to his death below.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 10, 'Paul went down, bent over him, and took him into his arms. "Don''t worry," he said, "he''s alive!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 11, 'Then they all went back upstairs and ate the Lord''s Supper together. And Paul continued talking to them until dawn; then he left.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 12, 'Meanwhile, the young man was taken home unhurt, and everyone was greatly relieved.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 13, 'Paul went by land to Assos, where he had arranged for us to join him, and we went on ahead by ship.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 14, 'He joined us there and we sailed together to Mitylene.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 15, 'The next day we passed the island of Kios. The following day, we crossed to the island of Samos. And a day later we arrived at Miletus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 16, 'Paul had decided against stopping at Ephesus this time because he didn''t want to spend further time in the province of Asia. He was hurrying to get to Jerusalem, if possible, for the Festival of Pentecost.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 17, 'But when we landed at Miletus, he sent a message to the elders of the church at Ephesus, asking them to come down to meet him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 18, 'When they arrived he declared, "You know that from the day I set foot in the province of Asia until now', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 19, 'I have done the Lord''s work humbly--yes, and with tears. I have endured the trials that came to me from the plots of the Jews.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 20, 'Yet I never shrank from telling you the truth, either publicly or in your homes.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 21, 'I have had one message for Jews and Gentiles alike--the necessity of turning from sin and turning to God, and of faith in our Lord Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 22, '"And now I am going to Jerusalem, drawn there irresistibly by the Holy Spirit, not knowing what awaits me,', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 23, 'except that the Holy Spirit has told me in city after city that jail and suffering lie ahead.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 24, 'But my life is worth nothing unless I use it for doing the work assigned me by the Lord Jesus--the work of telling others the Good News about God''s wonderful kindness and love.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 25, '"And now I know that none of you to whom I have preached the Kingdom will ever see me again.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 26, 'Let me say plainly that I have been faithful. No one''s damnation can be blamed on me,', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 27, 'for I didn''t shrink from declaring all that God wants for you.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 28, '"And now beware! Be sure that you feed and shepherd God''s flock--his church, purchased with his blood--over whom the Holy Spirit has appointed you as elders.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 29, 'I know full well that false teachers, like vicious wolves, will come in among you after I leave, not sparing the flock.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 30, 'Even some of you will distort the truth in order to draw a following.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 31, 'Watch out! Remember the three years I was with you--my constant watch and care over you night and day, and my many tears for you.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 32, '"And now I entrust you to God and the word of his grace--his message that is able to build you up and give you an inheritance with all those he has set apart for himself.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 33, '"I have never coveted anyone''s money or fine clothing.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 34, 'You know that these hands of mine have worked to pay my own way, and I have even supplied the needs of those who were with me.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 35, 'And I have been a constant example of how you can help the poor by working hard. You should remember the words of the Lord Jesus: ''It is more blessed to give than to receive.''"', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 36, 'When he had finished speaking, he knelt and prayed with them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 37, 'They wept aloud as they embraced him in farewell,', 'NLT'),
(7, 20, 38, 'sad most of all because he had said that they would never see him again. Then they accompanied him down to the ship.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 1, 'After saying farewell to the Ephesian elders, we sailed straight to the island of Cos. The next day we reached Rhodes and then went to Patara.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 2, 'There we boarded a ship sailing for the Syrian province of Phoenicia.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 3, 'We sighted the island of Cyprus, passed it on our left, and landed at the harbor of Tyre, in Syria, where the ship was to unload.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 4, 'We went ashore, found the local believers, and stayed with them a week. These disciples prophesied through the Holy Spirit that Paul should not go on to Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 5, 'When we returned to the ship at the end of the week, the entire congregation, including wives and children, came down to the shore with us. There we knelt, prayed,', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 6, 'and said our farewells. Then we went aboard, and they returned home.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 7, 'The next stop after leaving Tyre was Ptolemais, where we greeted the brothers and sisters but stayed only one day.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 8, 'Then we went on to Caesarea and stayed at the home of Philip the Evangelist, one of the seven men who had been chosen to distribute food.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 9, 'He had four unmarried daughters who had the gift of prophecy.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 10, 'During our stay of several days, a man named Agabus, who also had the gift of prophecy, arrived from Judea.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 11, 'When he visited us, he took Paul''s belt and bound his own feet and hands with it. Then he said, "The Holy Spirit declares, ''So shall the owner of this belt be bound by the Jewish leaders in Jerusalem and turned over to the Romans.''"', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 12, 'When we heard this, we who were traveling with him, as well as the local believers, begged Paul not to go on to Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 13, 'But he said, "Why all this weeping? You are breaking my heart! For I am ready not only to be jailed at Jerusalem but also to die for the sake of the Lord Jesus."', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 14, 'When it was clear that we couldn''t persuade him, we gave up and said, "The will of the Lord be done."', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 15, 'Shortly afterward we packed our things and left for Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 16, 'Some believers from Caesarea accompanied us, and they took us to the home of Mnason, a man originally from Cyprus and one of the early disciples.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 17, 'All the brothers and sisters in Jerusalem welcomed us cordially.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 18, 'The next day Paul went in with us to meet with James, and all the elders of the Jerusalem church were present.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 19, 'After greetings were exchanged, Paul gave a detailed account of the things God had accomplished among the Gentiles through his ministry.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 20, 'After hearing this, they praised God. But then they said, "You know, dear brother, how many thousands of Jews have also believed, and they all take the law of Moses very seriously.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 21, 'Our Jewish Christians here at Jerusalem have been told that you are teaching all the Jews living in the Gentile world to turn their backs on the laws of Moses. They say that you teach people not to circumcise their children or follow other Jewish customs.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 22, 'Now what can be done? For they will certainly hear that you have come.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 23, '"Here''s our suggestion. We have four men here who have taken a vow and are preparing to shave their heads.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 24, 'Go with them to the Temple and join them in the purification ceremony, and pay for them to have their heads shaved. Then everyone will know that the rumors are all false and that you yourself observe the Jewish laws.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 25, '"As for the Gentile Christians, all we ask of them is what we already told them in a letter: They should not eat food offered to idols, nor consume blood, nor eat meat from strangled animals, and they should stay away from all sexual immorality."', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 26, 'So Paul agreed to their request, and the next day he went through the purification ritual with the men and went to the Temple. Then he publicly announced the date when their vows would end and sacrifices would be offered for each of them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 27, 'The seven days were almost ended when some Jews from the province of Asia saw Paul in the Temple and roused a mob against him. They grabbed him,', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 28, 'yelling, "Men of Israel! Help! This is the man who teaches against our people and tells everybody to disobey the Jewish laws. He speaks against the Temple--and he even defiles it by bringing Gentiles in!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 29, '(For earlier that day they had seen him in the city with Trophimus, a Gentile from Ephesus, and they assumed Paul had taken him into the Temple.)', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 30, 'The whole population of the city was rocked by these accusations, and a great riot followed. Paul was dragged out of the Temple, and immediately the gates were closed behind him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 31, 'As they were trying to kill him, word reached the commander of the Roman regiment that all Jerusalem was in an uproar.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 32, 'He immediately called out his soldiers and officers and ran down among the crowd. When the mob saw the commander and the troops coming, they stopped beating Paul.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 33, 'The commander arrested him and ordered him bound with two chains. Then he asked the crowd who he was and what he had done.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 34, 'Some shouted one thing and some another. He couldn''t find out the truth in all the uproar and confusion, so he ordered Paul to be taken to the fortress.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 35, 'As they reached the stairs, the mob grew so violent the soldiers had to lift Paul to their shoulders to protect him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 36, 'And the crowd followed behind shouting, "Kill him, kill him!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 37, 'As Paul was about to be taken inside, he said to the commander, "May I have a word with you?Do you know Greek?" the commander asked, surprised.', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 38, '"Aren''t you the Egyptian who led a rebellion some time ago and took four thousand members of the Assassins out into the desert?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 39, '"No," Paul replied, "I am a Jew from Tarsus in Cilicia, which is an important city. Please, let me talk to these people."', 'NLT'),
(7, 21, 40, 'The commander agreed, so Paul stood on the stairs and motioned to the people to be quiet. Soon a deep silence enveloped the crowd, and he addressed them in their own language, Aramaic.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 1, '"Brothers and esteemed fathers," Paul said, "listen to me as I offer my defense."', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 2, 'When they heard him speaking in their own language, the silence was even greater.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 3, '"I am a Jew, born in Tarsus, a city in Cilicia, and I was brought up and educated here in Jerusalem under Gamaliel. At his feet I learned to follow our Jewish laws and customs very carefully. I became very zealous to honor God in everything I did, just as all of you are today.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 4, 'And I persecuted the followers of the Way, hounding some to death, binding and delivering both men and women to prison.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 5, 'The high priest and the whole council of leaders can testify that this is so. For I received letters from them to our Jewish brothers in Damascus, authorizing me to bring the Christians from there to Jerusalem, in chains, to be punished.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 6, '"As I was on the road, nearing Damascus, about noon a very bright light from heaven suddenly shone around me.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 7, 'I fell to the ground and heard a voice saying to me, ''Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting me?''', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 8, '"''Who are you, sir?'' I asked. And he replied, ''I am Jesus of Nazareth, the one you are persecuting.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 9, 'The people with me saw the light but didn''t hear the voice.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 10, '"I said, ''What shall I do, Lord?'' And the Lord told me, ''Get up and go into Damascus, and there you will be told all that you are to do.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 11, '"I was blinded by the intense light and had to be led into Damascus by my companions.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 12, 'A man named Ananias lived there. He was a godly man in his devotion to the law, and he was well thought of by all the Jews of Damascus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 13, 'He came to me and stood beside me and said, ''Brother Saul, receive your sight.'' And that very hour I could see him!', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 14, '"Then he told me, ''The God of our ancestors has chosen you to know his will and to see the Righteous One and hear him speak.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 15, 'You are to take his message everywhere, telling the whole world what you have seen and heard.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 16, 'And now, why delay? Get up and be baptized, and have your sins washed away, calling on the name of the Lord.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 17, '"One day after I returned to Jerusalem, I was praying in the Temple, and I fell into a trance.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 18, 'I saw a vision of Jesus saying to me, ''Hurry! Leave Jerusalem, for the people here won''t believe you when you give them your testimony about me.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 19, '"''But Lord,'' I argued, ''they certainly know that I imprisoned and beat those in every synagogue who believed on you.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 20, 'And when your witness Stephen was killed, I was standing there agreeing. I kept the coats they laid aside as they stoned him.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 21, '"But the Lord said to me, ''Leave Jerusalem, for I will send you far away to the Gentiles!''"', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 22, 'The crowd listened until Paul came to that word; then with one voice they shouted, "Away with such a fellow! Kill him! He isn''t fit to live!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 23, 'They yelled, threw off their coats, and tossed handfuls of dust into the air.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 24, 'The commander brought Paul inside and ordered him lashed with whips to make him confess his crime. He wanted to find out why the crowd had become so furious.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 25, 'As they tied Paul down to lash him, Paul said to the officer standing there, "Is it legal for you to whip a Roman citizen who hasn''t even been tried?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 26, 'The officer went to the commander and asked, "What are you doing? This man is a Roman citizen!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 27, 'So the commander went over and asked Paul, "Tell me, are you a Roman citizen?Yes, I certainly am," Paul replied.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 28, '"I am, too," the commander muttered, "and it cost me plenty!But I am a citizen by birth!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 29, 'The soldiers who were about to interrogate Paul quickly withdrew when they heard he was a Roman citizen, and the commander was frightened because he had ordered him bound and whipped.', 'NLT'),
(7, 22, 30, 'The next day the commander freed Paul from his chains and ordered the leading priests into session with the Jewish high council. He had Paul brought in before them to try to find out what the trouble was all about.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 1, 'Gazing intently at the high council, Paul began: "Brothers, I have always lived before God in all good conscience!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 2, 'Instantly Ananias the high priest commanded those close to Paul to slap him on the mouth.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 3, 'But Paul said to him, "God will slap you, you whitewashed wall! What kind of judge are you to break the law yourself by ordering me struck like that?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 4, 'Those standing near Paul said to him, "Is that the way to talk to God''s high priest?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 5, '"I''m sorry, brothers. I didn''t realize he was the high priest," Paul replied, "for the Scriptures say, ''Do not speak evil of anyone who rules over you.''"', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 6, 'Paul realized that some members of the high council were Sadducees and some were Pharisees, so he shouted, "Brothers, I am a Pharisee, as were all my ancestors! And I am on trial because my hope is in the resurrection of the dead!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 7, 'This divided the council--the Pharisees against the Sadducees--', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 8, 'for the Sadducees say there is no resurrection or angels or spirits, but the Pharisees believe in all of these.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 9, 'So a great clamor arose. Some of the teachers of religious law who were Pharisees jumped up to argue that Paul was all right. "We see nothing wrong with him," they shouted. "Perhaps a spirit or an angel spoke to him."', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 10, 'The shouting grew louder and louder, and the men were tugging at Paul from both sides, pulling him this way and that. Finally, the commander, fearing they would tear him apart, ordered his soldiers to take him away from them and bring him back to the fortress.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 11, 'That night the Lord appeared to Paul and said, "Be encouraged, Paul. Just as you have told the people about me here in Jerusalem, you must preach the Good News in Rome."', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 12, 'The next morning a group of Jews got together and bound themselves with an oath to neither eat nor drink until they had killed Paul.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 13, 'There were more than forty of them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 14, 'They went to the leading priests and other leaders and told them what they had done. "We have bound ourselves under oath to neither eat nor drink until we have killed Paul.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 15, 'You and the high council should tell the commander to bring Paul back to the council again," they requested. "Pretend you want to examine his case more fully. We will kill him on the way."', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 16, 'But Paul''s nephew heard of their plan and went to the fortress and told Paul.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 17, 'Paul called one of the officers and said, "Take this young man to the commander. He has something important to tell him."', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 18, 'So the officer did, explaining, "Paul, the prisoner, called me over and asked me to bring this young man to you because he has something to tell you."', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 19, 'The commander took him by the arm, led him aside, and asked, "What is it you want to tell me?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 20, 'Paul''s nephew told him, "Some Jews are going to ask you to bring Paul before the Jewish high council tomorrow, pretending they want to get some more information.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 21, 'But don''t do it! There are more than forty men hiding along the way ready to jump him and kill him. They have vowed not to eat or drink until they kill him. They are ready, expecting you to agree to their request."', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 22, '"Don''t let a soul know you told me this," the commander warned the young man as he sent him away.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 23, 'Then the commander called two of his officers and ordered, "Get two hundred soldiers ready to leave for Caesarea at nine o''clock tonight. Also take two hundred spearmen and seventy horsemen.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 24, 'Provide horses for Paul to ride, and get him safely to Governor Felix."', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 25, 'Then he wrote this letter to the governor:', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 26, '"From Claudius Lysias, to his Excellency, Governor Felix. Greetings!', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 27, 'This man was seized by some Jews, and they were about to kill him when I arrived with the troops. When I learned that he was a Roman citizen, I removed him to safety.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 28, 'Then I took him to their high council to try to find out what he had done.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 29, 'I soon discovered it was something regarding their religious law--certainly nothing worthy of imprisonment or death.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 30, 'But when I was informed of a plot to kill him, I immediately sent him on to you. I have told his accusers to bring their charges before you."', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 31, 'So that night, as ordered, the soldiers took Paul as far as Antipatris.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 32, 'They returned to the fortress the next morning, while the horsemen took him on to Caesarea.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 33, 'When they arrived in Caesarea, they presented Paul and the letter to Governor Felix.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 34, 'He read it and then asked Paul what province he was from. "Cilicia," Paul answered.', 'NLT'),
(7, 23, 35, '"I will hear your case myself when your accusers arrive," the governor told him. Then the governor ordered him kept in the prison at Herod''s headquarters.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 1, 'Five days later Ananias, the high priest, arrived with some of the Jewish leaders and the lawyer Tertullus, to press charges against Paul.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 2, 'When Paul was called in, Tertullus laid charges against Paul in the following address to the governor: "Your Excellency, you have given peace to us Jews and have enacted reforms for us.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 3, 'And for all of this we are very grateful to you.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 4, 'But lest I bore you, kindly give me your attention for only a moment as I briefly outline our case against this man.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 5, 'For we have found him to be a troublemaker, a man who is constantly inciting the Jews throughout the world to riots and rebellions against the Roman government. He is a ringleader of the sect known as the Nazarenes.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 6, 'Moreover he was trying to defile the Temple when we arrested him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 7, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 8, 'You can find out the truth of our accusations by examining him yourself."', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 9, 'Then the other Jews chimed in, declaring that everything Tertullus said was true.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 10, 'Now it was Paul''s turn. The governor motioned for him to rise and speak. Paul said, "I know, sir, that you have been a judge of Jewish affairs for many years, and this gives me confidence as I make my defense.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 11, 'You can quickly discover that it was no more than twelve days ago that I arrived in Jerusalem to worship at the Temple.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 12, 'I didn''t argue with anyone in the Temple, nor did I incite a riot in any synagogue or on the streets of the city.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 13, 'These men certainly cannot prove the things they accuse me of doing.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 14, '"But I admit that I follow the Way, which they call a sect. I worship the God of our ancestors, and I firmly believe the Jewish law and everything written in the books of prophecy.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 15, 'I have hope in God, just as these men do, that he will raise both the righteous and the ungodly.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 16, 'Because of this, I always try to maintain a clear conscience before God and everyone else.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 17, '"After several years away, I returned to Jerusalem with money to aid my people and to offer sacrifices to God.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 18, 'My accusers saw me in the Temple as I was completing a purification ritual. There was no crowd around me and no rioting.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 19, 'But some Jews from the province of Asia were there--and they ought to be here to bring charges if they have anything against me!', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 20, 'Ask these men here what wrongdoing the Jewish high council found in me,', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 21, 'except for one thing I said when I shouted out, ''I am on trial before you today because I believe in the resurrection of the dead!''"', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 22, 'Felix, who was quite familiar with the Way, adjourned the hearing and said, "Wait until Lysias, the garrison commander, arrives. Then I will decide the case."', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 23, 'He ordered an officer to keep Paul in custody but to give him some freedom and allow his friends to visit him and take care of his needs.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 24, 'A few days later Felix came with his wife, Drusilla, who was Jewish. Sending for Paul, they listened as he told them about faith in Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 25, 'As he reasoned with them about righteousness and self-control and the judgment to come, Felix was terrified. "Go away for now," he replied. "When it is more convenient, I''ll call for you again."', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 26, 'He also hoped that Paul would bribe him, so he sent for him quite often and talked with him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 24, 27, 'Two years went by in this way; then Felix was succeeded by Porcius Festus. And because Felix wanted to gain favor with the Jewish leaders, he left Paul in prison.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 1, 'Three days after Festus arrived in Caesarea to take over his new responsibilities, he left for Jerusalem,', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 2, 'where the leading priests and other Jewish leaders met with him and made their accusations against Paul.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 3, 'They asked Festus as a favor to transfer Paul to Jerusalem. (Their plan was to waylay and kill him.)', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 4, 'But Festus replied that Paul was at Caesarea and he himself would be returning there soon.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 5, 'So he said, "Those of you in authority can return with me. If Paul has done anything wrong, you can make your accusations."', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 6, 'Eight or ten days later he returned to Caesarea, and on the following day Paul''s trial began.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 7, 'On Paul''s arrival in court, the Jewish leaders from Jerusalem gathered around and made many serious accusations they couldn''t prove.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 8, 'Paul denied the charges. "I am not guilty," he said. "I have committed no crime against the Jewish laws or the Temple or the Roman government."', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 9, 'Then Festus, wanting to please the Jews, asked him, "Are you willing to go to Jerusalem and stand trial before me there?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 10, 'But Paul replied, "No! This is the official Roman court, so I ought to be tried right here. You know very well I am not guilty.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 11, 'If I have done something worthy of death, I don''t refuse to die. But if I am innocent, neither you nor anyone else has a right to turn me over to these men to kill me. I appeal to Caesar!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 12, 'Festus conferred with his advisers and then replied, "Very well! You have appealed to Caesar, and to Caesar you shall go!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 13, 'A few days later King Agrippa arrived with his sister, Bernice, to pay their respects to Festus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 14, 'During their stay of several days, Festus discussed Paul''s case with the king. "There is a prisoner here," he told him, "whose case was left for me by Felix.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 15, 'When I was in Jerusalem, the leading priests and other Jewish leaders pressed charges against him and asked me to sentence him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 16, 'Of course, I quickly pointed out to them that Roman law does not convict people without a trial. They are given an opportunity to defend themselves face to face with their accusers.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 17, '"When they came here for the trial, I called the case the very next day and ordered Paul brought in.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 18, 'But the accusations made against him weren''t at all what I expected.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 19, 'It was something about their religion and about someone called Jesus who died, but whom Paul insists is alive.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 20, 'I was perplexed as to how to conduct an investigation of this kind, and I asked him whether he would be willing to stand trial on these charges in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 21, 'But Paul appealed to the emperor. So I ordered him back to jail until I could arrange to send him to Caesar."', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 22, '"I''d like to hear the man myself," Agrippa said. And Festus replied, "You shall--tomorrow!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 23, 'So the next day Agrippa and Bernice arrived at the auditorium with great pomp, accompanied by military officers and prominent men of the city. Festus ordered that Paul be brought in.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 24, 'Then Festus said, "King Agrippa and all present, this is the man whose death is demanded both by the local Jews and by those in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 25, 'But in my opinion he has done nothing worthy of death. However, he appealed his case to the emperor, and I decided to send him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 26, 'But what shall I write the emperor? For there is no real charge against him. So I have brought him before all of you, and especially you, King Agrippa, so that after we examine him, I might have something to write.', 'NLT'),
(7, 25, 27, 'For it doesn''t seem reasonable to send a prisoner to the emperor without specifying the charges against him!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 1, 'Then Agrippa said to Paul, "You may speak in your defense." So Paul, with a gesture of his hand, started his defense:', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 2, '"I am fortunate, King Agrippa, that you are the one hearing my defense against all these accusations made by the Jewish leaders,', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 3, 'for I know you are an expert on Jewish customs and controversies. Now please listen to me patiently!', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 4, '"As the Jewish leaders are well aware, I was given a thorough Jewish training from my earliest childhood among my own people and in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 5, 'If they would admit it, they know that I have been a member of the Pharisees, the strictest sect of our religion.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 6, 'Now I am on trial because I am looking forward to the fulfillment of God''s promise made to our ancestors.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 7, 'In fact, that is why the twelve tribes of Israel worship God night and day, and they share the same hope I have. Yet, O king, they say it is wrong for me to have this hope!', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 8, 'Why does it seem incredible to any of you that God can raise the dead?', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 9, '"I used to believe that I ought to do everything I could to oppose the followers of Jesus of Nazareth.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 10, 'Authorized by the leading priests, I caused many of the believers in Jerusalem to be sent to prison. And I cast my vote against them when they were condemned to death.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 11, 'Many times I had them whipped in the synagogues to try to get them to curse Christ. I was so violently opposed to them that I even hounded them in distant cities of foreign lands.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 12, '"One day I was on such a mission to Damascus, armed with the authority and commission of the leading priests.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 13, 'About noon, Your Majesty, a light from heaven brighter than the sun shone down on me and my companions.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 14, 'We all fell down, and I heard a voice saying to me in Aramaic, ''Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting me? It is hard for you to fight against my will. ''', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 15, '"''Who are you, sir?'' I asked. "And the Lord replied, ''I am Jesus, the one you are persecuting.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 16, 'Now stand up! For I have appeared to you to appoint you as my servant and my witness. You are to tell the world about this experience and about other times I will appear to you.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 17, 'And I will protect you from both your own people and the Gentiles. Yes, I am going to send you to the Gentiles,', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 18, 'to open their eyes so they may turn from darkness to light, and from the power of Satan to God. Then they will receive forgiveness for their sins and be given a place among God''s people, who are set apart by faith in me.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 19, '"And so, O King Agrippa, I was not disobedient to that vision from heaven.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 20, 'I preached first to those in Damascus, then in Jerusalem and throughout all Judea, and also to the Gentiles, that all must turn from their sins and turn to God--and prove they have changed by the good things they do.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 21, 'Some Jews arrested me in the Temple for preaching this, and they tried to kill me.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 22, 'But God protected me so that I am still alive today to tell these facts to everyone, from the least to the greatest. I teach nothing except what the prophets and Moses said would happen--', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 23, 'that the Messiah would suffer and be the first to rise from the dead as a light to Jews and Gentiles alike."', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 24, 'Suddenly, Festus shouted, "Paul, you are insane. Too much study has made you crazy!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 25, 'But Paul replied, "I am not insane, Most Excellent Festus. I am speaking the sober truth.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 26, 'And King Agrippa knows about these things. I speak frankly, for I am sure these events are all familiar to him, for they were not done in a corner!', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 27, 'King Agrippa, do you believe the prophets? I know you do--"', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 28, 'Agrippa interrupted him. "Do you think you can make me a Christian so quickly?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 29, 'Paul replied, "Whether quickly or not, I pray to God that both you and everyone here in this audience might become the same as I am, except for these chains."', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 30, 'Then the king, the governor, Bernice, and all the others stood and left.', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 31, 'As they talked it over they agreed, "This man hasn''t done anything worthy of death or imprisonment."', 'NLT'),
(7, 26, 32, 'And Agrippa said to Festus, "He could be set free if he hadn''t appealed to Caesar!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 1, 'When the time came, we set sail for Italy. Paul and several other prisoners were placed in the custody of an army officer named Julius, a captain of the Imperial Regiment.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 2, 'And Aristarchus, a Macedonian from Thessalonica, was also with us. We left on a boat whose home port was Adramyttium; it was scheduled to make several stops at ports along the coast of the province of Asia.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 3, 'The next day when we docked at Sidon, Julius was very kind to Paul and let him go ashore to visit with friends so they could provide for his needs.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 4, 'Putting out to sea from there, we encountered headwinds that made it difficult to keep the ship on course, so we sailed north of Cyprus between the island and the mainland.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 5, 'We passed along the coast of the provinces of Cilicia and Pamphylia, landing at Myra, in the province of Lycia.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 6, 'There the officer found an Egyptian ship from Alexandria that was bound for Italy, and he put us on board.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 7, 'We had several days of rough sailing, and after great difficulty we finally neared Cnidus. But the wind was against us, so we sailed down to the leeward side of Crete, past the cape of Salmone.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 8, 'We struggled along the coast with great difficulty and finally arrived at Fair Havens, near the city of Lasea.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 9, 'We had lost a lot of time. The weather was becoming dangerous for long voyages by then because it was so late in the fall, and Paul spoke to the ship''s officers about it.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 10, '"Sirs," he said, "I believe there is trouble ahead if we go on--shipwreck, loss of cargo, injuries, and danger to our lives."', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 11, 'But the officer in charge of the prisoners listened more to the ship''s captain and the owner than to Paul.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 12, 'And since Fair Havens was an exposed harbor--a poor place to spend the winter--most of the crew wanted to go to Phoenix, farther up the coast of Crete, and spend the winter there. Phoenix was a good harbor with only a southwest and northwest exposure.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 13, 'When a light wind began blowing from the south, the sailors thought they could make it. So they pulled up anchor and sailed along close to shore.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 14, 'But the weather changed abruptly, and a wind of typhoon strength (a "northeaster," they called it) caught the ship and blew it out to sea.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 15, 'They couldn''t turn the ship into the wind, so they gave up and let it run before the gale.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 16, 'We sailed behind a small island named Cauda, where with great difficulty we hoisted aboard the lifeboat that was being towed behind us.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 17, 'Then we banded the ship with ropes to strengthen the hull. The sailors were afraid of being driven across to the sandbars of Syrtis off the African coast, so they lowered the sea anchor and were thus driven before the wind.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 18, 'The next day, as gale-force winds continued to batter the ship, the crew began throwing the cargo overboard.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 19, 'The following day they even threw out the ship''s equipment and anything else they could lay their hands on.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 20, 'The terrible storm raged unabated for many days, blotting out the sun and the stars, until at last all hope was gone.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 21, 'No one had eaten for a long time. Finally, Paul called the crew together and said, "Men, you should have listened to me in the first place and not left Fair Havens. You would have avoided all this injury and loss.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 22, 'But take courage! None of you will lose your lives, even though the ship will go down.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 23, 'For last night an angel of the God to whom I belong and whom I serve stood beside me,', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 24, 'and he said, ''Don''t be afraid, Paul, for you will surely stand trial before Caesar! What''s more, God in his goodness has granted safety to everyone sailing with you.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 25, 'So take courage! For I believe God. It will be just as he said.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 26, 'But we will be shipwrecked on an island."', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 27, 'About midnight on the fourteenth night of the storm, as we were being driven across the Sea of Adria, the sailors sensed land was near.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 28, 'They took soundings and found the water was only 120 feet deep. A little later they sounded again and found only 90 feet.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 29, 'At this rate they were afraid we would soon be driven against the rocks along the shore, so they threw out four anchors from the stern and prayed for daylight.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 30, 'Then the sailors tried to abandon the ship; they lowered the lifeboat as though they were going to put out anchors from the prow.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 31, 'But Paul said to the commanding officer and the soldiers, "You will all die unless the sailors stay aboard."', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 32, 'So the soldiers cut the ropes and let the boat fall off.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 33, 'As the darkness gave way to the early morning light, Paul begged everyone to eat. "You haven''t touched food for two weeks," he said.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 34, '"Please eat something now for your own good. For not a hair of your heads will perish."', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 35, 'Then he took some bread, gave thanks to God before them all, and broke off a piece and ate it.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 36, 'Then everyone was encouraged,', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 37, 'and all 276 of us began eating--for that is the number we had aboard.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 38, 'After eating, the crew lightened the ship further by throwing the cargo of wheat overboard.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 39, 'When morning dawned, they didn''t recognize the coastline, but they saw a bay with a beach and wondered if they could get between the rocks and get the ship safely to shore.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 40, 'So they cut off the anchors and left them in the sea. Then they lowered the rudders, raised the foresail, and headed toward shore.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 41, 'But the ship hit a shoal and ran aground. The bow of the ship stuck fast, while the stern was repeatedly smashed by the force of the waves and began to break apart.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 42, 'The soldiers wanted to kill the prisoners to make sure they didn''t swim ashore and escape.', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 43, 'But the commanding officer wanted to spare Paul, so he didn''t let them carry out their plan. Then he ordered all who could swim to jump overboard first and make for land,', 'NLT'),
(7, 27, 44, 'and he told the others to try for it on planks and debris from the broken ship. So everyone escaped safely ashore!', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 1, 'Once we were safe on shore, we learned that we were on the island of Malta.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 2, 'The people of the island were very kind to us. It was cold and rainy, so they built a fire on the shore to welcome us and warm us.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 3, 'As Paul gathered an armful of sticks and was laying them on the fire, a poisonous snake, driven out by the heat, fastened itself onto his hand.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 4, 'The people of the island saw it hanging there and said to each other, "A murderer, no doubt! Though he escaped the sea, justice will not permit him to live."', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 5, 'But Paul shook off the snake into the fire and was unharmed.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 6, 'The people waited for him to swell up or suddenly drop dead. But when they had waited a long time and saw no harm come to him, they changed their minds and decided he was a god.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 7, 'Near the shore where we landed was an estate belonging to Publius, the chief official of the island. He welcomed us courteously and fed us for three days.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 8, 'As it happened, Publius''s father was ill with fever and dysentery. Paul went in and prayed for him, and laying his hands on him, he healed him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 9, 'Then all the other sick people on the island came and were cured.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 10, 'As a result we were showered with honors, and when the time came to sail, people put on board all sorts of things we would need for the trip.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 11, 'It was three months after the shipwreck that we set sail on another ship that had wintered at the island--an Alexandrian ship with the twin gods as its figurehead.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 12, 'Our first stop was Syracuse, where we stayed three days.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 13, 'From there we sailed across to Rhegium. A day later a south wind began blowing, so the following day we sailed up the coast to Puteoli.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 14, 'There we found some believers, who invited us to stay with them seven days. And so we came to Rome.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 15, 'The brothers and sisters in Rome had heard we were coming, and they came to meet us at the Forum on the Appian Way. Others joined us at The Three Taverns. When Paul saw them, he thanked God and took courage.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 16, 'When we arrived in Rome, Paul was permitted to have his own private lodging, though he was guarded by a soldier.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 17, 'Three days after Paul''s arrival, he called together the local Jewish leaders. He said to them, "Brothers, I was arrested in Jerusalem and handed over to the Roman government, even though I had done nothing against our people or the customs of our ancestors.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 18, 'The Romans tried me and wanted to release me, for they found no cause for the death sentence.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 19, 'But when the Jewish leaders protested the decision, I felt it necessary to appeal to Caesar, even though I had no desire to press charges against my own people.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 20, 'I asked you to come here today so we could get acquainted and so I could tell you that I am bound with this chain because I believe that the hope of Israel--the Messiah--has already come."', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 21, 'They replied, "We have heard nothing against you. We have had no letters from Judea or reports from anyone who has arrived here.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 22, 'But we want to hear what you believe, for the only thing we know about these Christians is that they are denounced everywhere."', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 23, 'So a time was set, and on that day a large number of people came to Paul''s house. He told them about the Kingdom of God and taught them about Jesus from the Scriptures--from the five books of Moses and the books of the prophets. He began lecturing in the morning and went on into the evening.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 24, 'Some believed and some didn''t.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 25, 'But after they had argued back and forth among themselves, they left with this final word from Paul: "The Holy Spirit was right when he said to our ancestors through Isaiah the prophet,', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 26, '''Go and say to my people, You will hear my words, but you will not understand; you will see what I do, but you will not perceive its meaning.', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 27, 'For the hearts of these people are hardened, and their ears cannot hear, and they have closed their eyes--so their eyes cannot see, and their ears cannot hear, and their hearts cannot understand, and they cannot turn to me and let me heal them.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 28, 'So I want you to realize that this salvation from God is also available to the Gentiles, and they will accept it."', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 29, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 30, 'For the next two years, Paul lived in his own rented house. He welcomed all who visited him,', 'NLT'),
(7, 28, 31, 'proclaiming the Kingdom of God with all boldness and teaching about the Lord Jesus Christ. And no one tried to stop him.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, Jesus Christ''s slave, chosen by God to be an apostle and sent out to preach his Good News.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 2, 'This Good News was promised long ago by God through his prophets in the holy Scriptures.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 3, 'It is the Good News about his Son, Jesus, who came as a man, born into King David''s royal family line.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 4, 'And Jesus Christ our Lord was shown to be the Son of God when God powerfully raised him from the dead by means of the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 5, 'Through Christ, God has given us the privilege and authority to tell Gentiles everywhere what God has done for them, so that they will believe and obey him, bringing glory to his name.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 6, 'You are among those who have been called to belong to Jesus Christ,', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 7, 'dear friends in Rome. God loves you dearly, and he has called you to be his very own people. May grace and peace be yours from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 8, 'Let me say first of all that your faith in God is becoming known throughout the world. How I thank God through Jesus Christ for each one of you.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 9, 'God knows how often I pray for you. Day and night I bring you and your needs in prayer to God, whom I serve with all my heart by telling others the Good News about his Son.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 10, 'One of the things I always pray for is the opportunity, God willing, to come at last to see you.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 11, 'For I long to visit you so I can share a spiritual blessing with you that will help you grow strong in the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 12, 'I''m eager to encourage you in your faith, but I also want to be encouraged by yours. In this way, each of us will be a blessing to the other.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 13, 'I want you to know, dear brothers and sisters, that I planned many times to visit you, but I was prevented until now. I want to work among you and see good results, just as I have done among other Gentiles.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 14, 'For I have a great sense of obligation to people in our culture and to people in other cultures, to the educated and uneducated alike.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 15, 'So I am eager to come to you in Rome, too, to preach God''s Good News.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 16, 'For I am not ashamed of this Good News about Christ. It is the power of God at work, saving everyone who believes--Jews first and also Gentiles.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 17, 'This Good News tells us how God makes us right in his sight. This is accomplished from start to finish by faith. As the Scriptures say, "It is through faith that a righteous person has life."', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 18, 'But God shows his anger from heaven against all sinful, wicked people who push the truth away from themselves.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 19, 'For the truth about God is known to them instinctively. God has put this knowledge in their hearts.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 20, 'From the time the world was created, people have seen the earth and sky and all that God made. They can clearly see his invisible qualities--his eternal power and divine nature. So they have no excuse whatsoever for not knowing God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 21, 'Yes, they knew God, but they wouldn''t worship him as God or even give him thanks. And they began to think up foolish ideas of what God was like. The result was that their minds became dark and confused.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 22, 'Claiming to be wise, they became utter fools instead.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 23, 'And instead of worshiping the glorious, ever-living God, they worshiped idols made to look like mere people, or birds and animals and snakes.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 24, 'So God let them go ahead and do whatever shameful things their hearts desired. As a result, they did vile and degrading things with each other''s bodies.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 25, 'Instead of believing what they knew was the truth about God, they deliberately chose to believe lies. So they worshiped the things God made but not the Creator himself, who is to be praised forever. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 26, 'That is why God abandoned them to their shameful desires. Even the women turned against the natural way to have sex and instead indulged in sex with each other.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 27, 'And the men, instead of having normal sexual relationships with women, burned with lust for each other. Men did shameful things with other men and, as a result, suffered within themselves the penalty they so richly deserved.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 28, 'When they refused to acknowledge God, he abandoned them to their evil minds and let them do things that should never be done.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 29, 'Their lives became full of every kind of wickedness, sin, greed, hate, envy, murder, fighting, deception, malicious behavior, and gossip.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 30, 'They are backstabbers, haters of God, insolent, proud, and boastful. They are forever inventing new ways of sinning and are disobedient to their parents.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 31, 'They refuse to understand, break their promises, and are heartless and unforgiving.', 'NLT'),
(8, 1, 32, 'They are fully aware of God''s death penalty for those who do these things, yet they go right ahead and do them anyway. And, worse yet, they encourage others to do them, too.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 1, 'You may be saying, "What terrible people you have been talking about!" But you are just as bad, and you have no excuse! When you say they are wicked and should be punished, you are condemning yourself, for you do these very same things.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 2, 'And we know that God, in his justice, will punish anyone who does such things.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 3, 'Do you think that God will judge and condemn others for doing them and not judge you when you do them, too?', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 4, 'Don''t you realize how kind, tolerant, and patient God is with you? Or don''t you care? Can''t you see how kind he has been in giving you time to turn from your sin?', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 5, 'But no, you won''t listen. So you are storing up terrible punishment for yourself because of your stubbornness in refusing to turn from your sin. For there is going to come a day of judgment when God, the just judge of all the world,', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 6, 'will judge all people according to what they have done.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 7, 'He will give eternal life to those who persist in doing what is good, seeking after the glory and honor and immortality that God offers.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 8, 'But he will pour out his anger and wrath on those who live for themselves, who refuse to obey the truth and practice evil deeds.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 9, 'There will be trouble and calamity for everyone who keeps on sinning--for the Jew first and also for the Gentile.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 10, 'But there will be glory and honor and peace from God for all who do good--for the Jew first and also for the Gentile.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 11, 'For God does not show favoritism.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 12, 'God will punish the Gentiles when they sin, even though they never had God''s written law. And he will punish the Jews when they sin, for they do have the law.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 13, 'For it is not merely knowing the law that brings God''s approval. Those who obey the law will be declared right in God''s sight.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 14, 'Even when Gentiles, who do not have God''s written law, instinctively follow what the law says, they show that in their hearts they know right from wrong.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 15, 'They demonstrate that God''s law is written within them, for their own consciences either accuse them or tell them they are doing what is right.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 16, 'The day will surely come when God, by Jesus Christ, will judge everyone''s secret life. This is my message.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 17, 'If you are a Jew, you are relying on God''s law for your special relationship with him. You boast that all is well between yourself and God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 18, 'Yes, you know what he wants; you know right from wrong because you have been taught his law.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 19, 'You are convinced that you are a guide for the blind and a beacon light for people who are lost in darkness without God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 20, 'You think you can instruct the ignorant and teach children the ways of God. For you are certain that in God''s law you have complete knowledge and truth.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 21, 'Well then, if you teach others, why don''t you teach yourself? You tell others not to steal, but do you steal?', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 22, 'You say it is wrong to commit adultery, but do you do it? You condemn idolatry, but do you steal from pagan temples?', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 23, 'You are so proud of knowing the law, but you dishonor God by breaking it.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 24, 'No wonder the Scriptures say, "The world blasphemes the name of God because of you."', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 25, 'The Jewish ceremony of circumcision is worth something only if you obey God''s law. But if you don''t obey God''s law, you are no better off than an uncircumcised Gentile.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 26, 'And if the Gentiles obey God''s law, won''t God give them all the rights and honors of being his own people?', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 27, 'In fact, uncircumcised Gentiles who keep God''s law will be much better off than you Jews who are circumcised and know so much about God''s law but don''t obey it.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 28, 'For you are not a true Jew just because you were born of Jewish parents or because you have gone through the Jewish ceremony of circumcision.', 'NLT'),
(8, 2, 29, 'No, a true Jew is one whose heart is right with God. And true circumcision is not a cutting of the body but a change of heart produced by God''s Spirit. Whoever has that kind of change seeks praise from God, not from people.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 1, 'Then what''s the advantage of being a Jew? Is there any value in the Jewish ceremony of circumcision?', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 2, 'Yes, being a Jew has many advantages. First of all, the Jews were entrusted with the whole revelation of God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 3, 'True, some of them were unfaithful; but just because they broke their promises, does that mean God will break his promises?', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 4, 'Of course not! Though everyone else in the world is a liar, God is true. As the Scriptures say, "He will be proved right in what he says, and he will win his case in court."', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 5, '"But," some say, "our sins serve a good purpose, for people will see God''s goodness when he declares us sinners to be innocent. Isn''t it unfair, then, for God to punish us?" (That is actually the way some people talk.)', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 6, 'Of course not! If God is not just, how is he qualified to judge the world?', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 7, '"But," some might still argue, "how can God judge and condemn me as a sinner if my dishonesty highlights his truthfulness and brings him more glory?"', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 8, 'If you follow that kind of thinking, however, you might as well say that the more we sin the better it is! Those who say such things deserve to be condemned, yet some slander me by saying this is what I preach!', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 9, 'Well then, are we Jews better than others? No, not at all, for we have already shown that all people, whether Jews or Gentiles, are under the power of sin.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 10, 'As the Scriptures say, "No one is good--not even one.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 11, 'No one has real understanding; no one is seeking God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 12, 'All have turned away from God; all have gone wrong. No one does good, not even one."', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 13, '"Their talk is foul, like the stench from an open grave. Their speech is filled with lies.The poison of a deadly snake drips from their lips."', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 14, '"Their mouths are full of cursing and bitterness."', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 15, '"They are quick to commit murder.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 16, 'Wherever they go, destruction and misery follow them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 17, 'They do not know what true peace is."', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 18, '"They have no fear of God to restrain them."', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 19, 'Obviously, the law applies to those to whom it was given, for its purpose is to keep people from having excuses and to bring the entire world into judgment before God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 20, 'For no one can ever be made right in God''s sight by doing what his law commands. For the more we know God''s law, the clearer it becomes that we aren''t obeying it.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 21, 'But now God has shown us a different way of being right in his sight--not by obeying the law but by the way promised in the Scriptures long ago.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 22, 'We are made right in God''s sight when we trust in Jesus Christ to take away our sins. And we all can be saved in this same way, no matter who we are or what we have done.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 23, 'For all have sinned; all fall short of God''s glorious standard.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 24, 'Yet now God in his gracious kindness declares us not guilty. He has done this through Christ Jesus, who has freed us by taking away our sins.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 25, 'For God sent Jesus to take the punishment for our sins and to satisfy God''s anger against us. We are made right with God when we believe that Jesus shed his blood, sacrificing his life for us. God was being entirely fair and just when he did not punish those who sinned in former times.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 26, 'And he is entirely fair and just in this present time when he declares sinners to be right in his sight because they believe in Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 27, 'Can we boast, then, that we have done anything to be accepted by God? No, because our acquittal is not based on our good deeds. It is based on our faith.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 28, 'So we are made right with God through faith and not by obeying the law.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 29, 'After all, God is not the God of the Jews only, is he? Isn''t he also the God of the Gentiles? Of course he is.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 30, 'There is only one God, and there is only one way of being accepted by him. He makes people right with himself only by faith, whether they are Jews or Gentiles.', 'NLT'),
(8, 3, 31, 'Well then, if we emphasize faith, does this mean that we can forget about the law? Of course not! In fact, only when we have faith do we truly fulfill the law.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 1, 'Abraham was, humanly speaking, the founder of our Jewish nation. What were his experiences concerning this question of being saved by faith?', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 2, 'Was it because of his good deeds that God accepted him? If so, he would have had something to boast about. But from God''s point of view Abraham had no basis at all for pride.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 3, 'For the Scriptures tell us, "Abraham believed God, so God declared him to be righteous."', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 4, 'When people work, their wages are not a gift. Workers earn what they receive.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 5, 'But people are declared righteous because of their faith, not because of their work.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 6, 'King David spoke of this, describing the happiness of an undeserving sinner who is declared to be righteous:', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 7, '"Oh, what joy for those whose disobedience is forgiven, whose sins are put out of sight.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 8, 'Yes, what joy for those whose sin is no longer counted against them by the Lord."', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 9, 'Now then, is this blessing only for the Jews, or is it for Gentiles, too? Well, what about Abraham? We have been saying he was declared righteous by God because of his faith.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 10, 'But how did his faith help him? Was he declared righteous only after he had been circumcised, or was it before he was circumcised? The answer is that God accepted him first, and then he was circumcised later!', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 11, 'The circumcision ceremony was a sign that Abraham already had faith and that God had already accepted him and declared him to be righteous--even before he was circumcised. So Abraham is the spiritual father of those who have faith but have not been circumcised. They are made right with God by faith.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 12, 'And Abraham is also the spiritual father of those who have been circumcised, but only if they have the same kind of faith Abraham had before he was circumcised.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 13, 'It is clear, then, that God''s promise to give the whole earth to Abraham and his descendants was not based on obedience to God''s law, but on the new relationship with God that comes by faith.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 14, 'So if you claim that God''s promise is for those who obey God''s law and think they are "good enough" in God''s sight, then you are saying that faith is useless. And in that case, the promise is also meaningless.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 15, 'But the law brings punishment on those who try to obey it. (The only way to avoid breaking the law is to have no law to break!)', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 16, 'So that''s why faith is the key! God''s promise is given to us as a free gift. And we are certain to receive it, whether or not we follow Jewish customs, if we have faith like Abraham''s. For Abraham is the father of all who believe.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 17, 'That is what the Scriptures mean when God told him, "I have made you the father of many nations." This happened because Abraham believed in the God who brings the dead back to life and who brings into existence what didn''t exist before.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 18, 'When God promised Abraham that he would become the father of many nations, Abraham believed him. God had also said, "Your descendants will be as numerous as the stars," even though such a promise seemed utterly impossible!', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 19, 'And Abraham''s faith did not weaken, even though he knew that he was too old to be a father at the age of one hundred and that Sarah, his wife, had never been able to have children.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 20, 'Abraham never wavered in believing God''s promise. In fact, his faith grew stronger, and in this he brought glory to God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 21, 'He was absolutely convinced that God was able to do anything he promised.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 22, 'And because of Abraham''s faith, God declared him to be righteous.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 23, 'Now this wonderful truth--that God declared him to be righteous--wasn''t just for Abraham''s benefit.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 24, 'It was for us, too, assuring us that God will also declare us to be righteous if we believe in God, who brought Jesus our Lord back from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(8, 4, 25, 'He was handed over to die because of our sins, and he was raised from the dead to make us right with God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 1, 'Therefore, since we have been made right in God''s sight by faith, we have peace with God because of what Jesus Christ our Lord has done for us.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 2, 'Because of our faith, Christ has brought us into this place of highest privilege where we now stand, and we confidently and joyfully look forward to sharing God''s glory.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 3, 'We can rejoice, too, when we run into problems and trials, for we know that they are good for us--they help us learn to endure.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 4, 'And endurance develops strength of character in us, and character strengthens our confident expectation of salvation.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 5, 'And this expectation will not disappoint us. For we know how dearly God loves us, because he has given us the Holy Spirit to fill our hearts with his love.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 6, 'When we were utterly helpless, Christ came at just the right time and died for us sinners.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 7, 'Now, no one is likely to die for a good person, though someone might be willing to die for a person who is especially good.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 8, 'But God showed his great love for us by sending Christ to die for us while we were still sinners.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 9, 'And since we have been made right in God''s sight by the blood of Christ, he will certainly save us from God''s judgment.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 10, 'For since we were restored to friendship with God by the death of his Son while we were still his enemies, we will certainly be delivered from eternal punishment by his life.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 11, 'So now we can rejoice in our wonderful new relationship with God--all because of what our Lord Jesus Christ has done for us in making us friends of God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 12, 'When Adam sinned, sin entered the entire human race. Adam''s sin brought death, so death spread to everyone, for everyone sinned.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 13, 'Yes, people sinned even before the law was given. And though there was no law to break, since it had not yet been given,', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 14, 'they all died anyway--even though they did not disobey an explicit commandment of God, as Adam did. What a contrast between Adam and Christ, who was yet to come!', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 15, 'And what a difference between our sin and God''s generous gift of forgiveness. For this one man, Adam, brought death to many through his sin. But this other man, Jesus Christ, brought forgiveness to many through God''s bountiful gift.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 16, 'And the result of God''s gracious gift is very different from the result of that one man''s sin. For Adam''s sin led to condemnation, but we have the free gift of being accepted by God, even though we are guilty of many sins.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 17, 'The sin of this one man, Adam, caused death to rule over us, but all who receive God''s wonderful, gracious gift of righteousness will live in triumph over sin and death through this one man, Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 18, 'Yes, Adam''s one sin brought condemnation upon everyone, but Christ''s one act of righteousness makes all people right in God''s sight and gives them life.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 19, 'Because one person disobeyed God, many people became sinners. But because one other person obeyed God, many people will be made right in God''s sight.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 20, 'God''s law was given so that all people could see how sinful they were. But as people sinned more and more, God''s wonderful kindness became more abundant.', 'NLT'),
(8, 5, 21, 'So just as sin ruled over all people and brought them to death, now God''s wonderful kindness rules instead, giving us right standing with God and resulting in eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 1, 'Well then, should we keep on sinning so that God can show us more and more kindness and forgiveness?', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 2, 'Of course not! Since we have died to sin, how can we continue to live in it?', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 3, 'Or have you forgotten that when we became Christians and were baptized to become one with Christ Jesus, we died with him?', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 4, 'For we died and were buried with Christ by baptism. And just as Christ was raised from the dead by the glorious power of the Father, now we also may live new lives.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 5, 'Since we have been united with him in his death, we will also be raised as he was.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 6, 'Our old sinful selves were crucified with Christ so that sin might lose its power in our lives. We are no longer slaves to sin.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 7, 'For when we died with Christ we were set free from the power of sin.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 8, 'And since we died with Christ, we know we will also share his new life.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 9, 'We are sure of this because Christ rose from the dead, and he will never die again. Death no longer has any power over him.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 10, 'He died once to defeat sin, and now he lives for the glory of God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 11, 'So you should consider yourselves dead to sin and able to live for the glory of God through Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 12, 'Do not let sin control the way you live; do not give in to its lustful desires.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 13, 'Do not let any part of your body become a tool of wickedness, to be used for sinning. Instead, give yourselves completely to God since you have been given new life. And use your whole body as a tool to do what is right for the glory of God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 14, 'Sin is no longer your master, for you are no longer subject to the law, which enslaves you to sin. Instead, you are free by God''s grace.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 15, 'So since God''s grace has set us free from the law, does this mean we can go on sinning? Of course not!', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 16, 'Don''t you realize that whatever you choose to obey becomes your master? You can choose sin, which leads to death, or you can choose to obey God and receive his approval.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 17, 'Thank God! Once you were slaves of sin, but now you have obeyed with all your heart the new teaching God has given you.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 18, 'Now you are free from sin, your old master, and you have become slaves to your new master, righteousness.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 19, 'I speak this way, using the illustration of slaves and masters, because it is easy to understand. Before, you let yourselves be slaves of impurity and lawlessness. Now you must choose to be slaves of righteousness so that you will become holy.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 20, 'In those days, when you were slaves of sin, you weren''t concerned with doing what was right.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 21, 'And what was the result? It was not good, since now you are ashamed of the things you used to do, things that end in eternal doom.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 22, 'But now you are free from the power of sin and have become slaves of God. Now you do those things that lead to holiness and result in eternal life.', 'NLT'),
(8, 6, 23, 'For the wages of sin is death, but the free gift of God is eternal life through Christ Jesus our Lord.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 1, 'Now, dear brothers and sisters--you who are familiar with the law--don''t you know that the law applies only to a person who is still living?', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 2, 'Let me illustrate. When a woman marries, the law binds her to her husband as long as he is alive. But if he dies, the laws of marriage no longer apply to her.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 3, 'So while her husband is alive, she would be committing adultery if she married another man. But if her husband dies, she is free from that law and does not commit adultery when she remarries.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 4, 'So this is the point: The law no longer holds you in its power, because you died to its power when you died with Christ on the cross. And now you are united with the one who was raised from the dead. As a result, you can produce good fruit, that is, good deeds for God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 5, 'When we were controlled by our old nature, sinful desires were at work within us, and the law aroused these evil desires that produced sinful deeds, resulting in death.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 6, 'But now we have been released from the law, for we died with Christ, and we are no longer captive to its power. Now we can really serve God, not in the old way by obeying the letter of the law, but in the new way, by the Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 7, 'Well then, am I suggesting that the law of God is evil? Of course not! The law is not sinful, but it was the law that showed me my sin. I would never have known that coveting is wrong if the law had not said, "Do not covet."', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 8, 'But sin took advantage of this law and aroused all kinds of forbidden desires within me! If there were no law, sin would not have that power.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 9, 'I felt fine when I did not understand what the law demanded. But when I learned the truth, I realized I had broken the law and was a sinner, doomed to die.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 10, 'So the good law, which was supposed to show me the way of life, instead gave me the death penalty.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 11, 'Sin took advantage of the law and fooled me; it took the good law and used it to make me guilty of death.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 12, 'But still, the law itself is holy and right and good.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 13, 'But how can that be? Did the law, which is good, cause my doom? Of course not! Sin used what was good to bring about my condemnation. So we can see how terrible sin really is. It uses God''s good commandment for its own evil purposes.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 14, 'The law is good, then. The trouble is not with the law but with me, because I am sold into slavery, with sin as my master.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 15, 'I don''t understand myself at all, for I really want to do what is right, but I don''t do it. Instead, I do the very thing I hate.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 16, 'I know perfectly well that what I am doing is wrong, and my bad conscience shows that I agree that the law is good.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 17, 'But I can''t help myself, because it is sin inside me that makes me do these evil things.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 18, 'I know I am rotten through and through so far as my old sinful nature is concerned. No matter which way I turn, I can''t make myself do right. I want to, but I can''t.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 19, 'When I want to do good, I don''t. And when I try not to do wrong, I do it anyway.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 20, 'But if I am doing what I don''t want to do, I am not really the one doing it; the sin within me is doing it.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 21, 'It seems to be a fact of life that when I want to do what is right, I inevitably do what is wrong.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 22, 'I love God''s law with all my heart.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 23, 'But there is another law at work within me that is at war with my mind. This law wins the fight and makes me a slave to the sin that is still within me.', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 24, 'Oh, what a miserable person I am! Who will free me from this life that is dominated by sin?', 'NLT'),
(8, 7, 25, 'Thank God! The answer is in Jesus Christ our Lord. So you see how it is: In my mind I really want to obey God''s law, but because of my sinful nature I am a slave to sin.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 1, 'So now there is no condemnation for those who belong to Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 2, 'For the power of the life-giving Spirit has freed you through Christ Jesus from the power of sin that leads to death.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 3, 'The law of Moses could not save us, because of our sinful nature. But God put into effect a different plan to save us. He sent his own Son in a human body like ours, except that ours are sinful. God destroyed sin''s control over us by giving his Son as a sacrifice for our sins.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 4, 'He did this so that the requirement of the law would be fully accomplished for us who no longer follow our sinful nature but instead follow the Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 5, 'Those who are dominated by the sinful nature think about sinful things, but those who are controlled by the Holy Spirit think about things that please the Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 6, 'If your sinful nature controls your mind, there is death. But if the Holy Spirit controls your mind, there is life and peace.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 7, 'For the sinful nature is always hostile to God. It never did obey God''s laws, and it never will.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 8, 'That''s why those who are still under the control of their sinful nature can never please God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 9, 'But you are not controlled by your sinful nature. You are controlled by the Spirit if you have the Spirit of God living in you. (And remember that those who do not have the Spirit of Christ living in them are not Christians at all.)', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 10, 'Since Christ lives within you, even though your body will die because of sin, your spirit is alive because you have been made right with God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 11, 'The Spirit of God, who raised Jesus from the dead, lives in you. And just as he raised Christ from the dead, he will give life to your mortal body by this same Spirit living within you.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 12, 'So, dear brothers and sisters, you have no obligation whatsoever to do what your sinful nature urges you to do.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 13, 'For if you keep on following it, you will perish. But if through the power of the Holy Spirit you turn from it and its evil deeds, you will live.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 14, 'For all who are led by the Spirit of God are children of God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 15, 'So you should not be like cowering, fearful slaves. You should behave instead like God''s very own children, adopted into his family--calling him "Father, dear Father."', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 16, 'For his Holy Spirit speaks to us deep in our hearts and tells us that we are God''s children.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 17, 'And since we are his children, we will share his treasures--for everything God gives to his Son, Christ, is ours, too. But if we are to share his glory, we must also share his suffering.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 18, 'Yet what we suffer now is nothing compared to the glory he will give us later.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 19, 'For all creation is waiting eagerly for that future day when God will reveal who his children really are.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 20, 'Against its will, everything on earth was subjected to God''s curse.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 21, 'All creation anticipates the day when it will join God''s children in glorious freedom from death and decay.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 22, 'For we know that all creation has been groaning as in the pains of childbirth right up to the present time.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 23, 'And even we Christians, although we have the Holy Spirit within us as a foretaste of future glory, also groan to be released from pain and suffering. We, too, wait anxiously for that day when God will give us our full rights as his children, including the new bodies he has promised us.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 24, 'Now that we are saved, we eagerly look forward to this freedom. For if you already have something, you don''t need to hope for it.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 25, 'But if we look forward to something we don''t have yet, we must wait patiently and confidently.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 26, 'And the Holy Spirit helps us in our distress. For we don''t even know what we should pray for, nor how we should pray. But the Holy Spirit prays for us with groanings that cannot be expressed in words.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 27, 'And the Father who knows all hearts knows what the Spirit is saying, for the Spirit pleads for us believers in harmony with God''s own will.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 28, 'And we know that God causes everything to work together for the good of those who love God and are called according to his purpose for them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 29, 'For God knew his people in advance, and he chose them to become like his Son, so that his Son would be the firstborn, with many brothers and sisters.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 30, 'And having chosen them, he called them to come to him. And he gave them right standing with himself, and he promised them his glory.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 31, 'What can we say about such wonderful things as these? If God is for us, who can ever be against us?', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 32, 'Since God did not spare even his own Son but gave him up for us all, won''t God, who gave us Christ, also give us everything else?', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 33, 'Who dares accuse us whom God has chosen for his own? Will God? No! He is the one who has given us right standing with himself.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 34, 'Who then will condemn us? Will Christ Jesus? No, for he is the one who died for us and was raised to life for us and is sitting at the place of highest honor next to God, pleading for us.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 35, 'Can anything ever separate us from Christ''s love? Does it mean he no longer loves us if we have trouble or calamity, or are persecuted, or are hungry or cold or in danger or threatened with death?', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 36, '(Even the Scriptures say, "For your sake we are killed every day; we are being slaughtered like sheep." )', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 37, 'No, despite all these things, overwhelming victory is ours through Christ, who loved us.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 38, 'And I am convinced that nothing can ever separate us from his love. Death can''t, and life can''t. The angels can''t, and the demons can''t. Our fears for today, our worries about tomorrow, and even the powers of hell can''t keep God''s love away.', 'NLT'),
(8, 8, 39, 'Whether we are high above the sky or in the deepest ocean, nothing in all creation will ever be able to separate us from the love of God that is revealed in Christ Jesus our Lord.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 1, 'In the presence of Christ, I speak with utter truthfulness--I do not lie--and my conscience and the Holy Spirit confirm that what I am saying is true.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 2, 'My heart is filled with bitter sorrow and unending grief', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 3, 'for my people, my Jewish brothers and sisters. I would be willing to be forever cursed--cut off from Christ!--if that would save them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 4, 'They are the people of Israel, chosen to be God''s special children. God revealed his glory to them. He made covenants with them and gave his law to them. They have the privilege of worshiping him and receiving his wonderful promises.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 5, 'Their ancestors were great people of God, and Christ himself was a Jew as far as his human nature is concerned. And he is God, who rules over everything and is worthy of eternal praise! Amen.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 6, 'Well then, has God failed to fulfill his promise to the Jews? No, for not everyone born into a Jewish family is truly a Jew!', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 7, 'Just the fact that they are descendants of Abraham doesn''t make them truly Abraham''s children. For the Scriptures say, "Isaac is the son through whom your descendants will be counted," though Abraham had other children, too.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 8, 'This means that Abraham''s physical descendants are not necessarily children of God. It is the children of the promise who are considered to be Abraham''s children.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 9, 'For God had promised, "Next year I will return, and Sarah will have a son."', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 10, 'This son was our ancestor Isaac. When he grew up, he married Rebekah, who gave birth to twins.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 11, 'But before they were born, before they had done anything good or bad, she received a message from God. (This message proves that God chooses according to his own plan,', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 12, 'not according to our good or bad works.) She was told, "The descendants of your older son will serve the descendants of your younger son."', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 13, 'In the words of the Scriptures, "I loved Jacob, but I rejected Esau."', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 14, 'What can we say? Was God being unfair? Of course not!', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 15, 'For God said to Moses, "I will show mercy to anyone I choose, and I will show compassion to anyone I choose."', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 16, 'So receiving God''s promise is not up to us. We can''t get it by choosing it or working hard for it. God will show mercy to anyone he chooses.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 17, 'For the Scriptures say that God told Pharaoh, "I have appointed you for the very purpose of displaying my power in you, and so that my fame might spread throughout the earth."', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 18, 'So you see, God shows mercy to some just because he wants to, and he chooses to make some people refuse to listen.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 19, 'Well then, you might say, "Why does God blame people for not listening? Haven''t they simply done what he made them do?"', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 20, 'No, don''t say that. Who are you, a mere human being, to criticize God? Should the thing that was created say to the one who made it, "Why have you made me like this?"', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 21, 'When a potter makes jars out of clay, doesn''t he have a right to use the same lump of clay to make one jar for decoration and another to throw garbage into?', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 22, 'God has every right to exercise his judgment and his power, but he also has the right to be very patient with those who are the objects of his judgment and are fit only for destruction.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 23, 'He also has the right to pour out the riches of his glory upon those he prepared to be the objects of his mercy--', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 24, 'even upon us, whom he selected, both from the Jews and from the Gentiles.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 25, 'Concerning the Gentiles, God says in the prophecy of Hosea, "Those who were not my people, I will now call my people. And I will love those whom I did not love before."', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 26, 'And, "Once they were told, ''You are not my people.'' But now he will say, ''You are children of the living God.''"', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 27, 'Concerning Israel, Isaiah the prophet cried out, "Though the people of Israel are as numerous as the sand on the seashore, only a small number will be saved.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 28, 'For the Lord will carry out his sentence upon the earth quickly and with finality."', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 29, 'And Isaiah said in another place, "If the Lord Almighty had not spared a few of us, we would have been wiped out as completely as Sodom and Gomorrah."', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 30, 'Well then, what shall we say about these things? Just this: The Gentiles have been made right with God by faith, even though they were not seeking him.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 31, 'But the Jews, who tried so hard to get right with God by keeping the law, never succeeded.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 32, 'Why not? Because they were trying to get right with God by keeping the law and being good instead of by depending on faith. They stumbled over the great rock in their path.', 'NLT'),
(8, 9, 33, 'God warned them of this in the Scriptures when he said, "I am placing a stone in Jerusalem that causes people to stumble, and a rock that makes them fall. But anyone who believes in him will not be disappointed. "', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 1, 'Dear brothers and sisters, the longing of my heart and my prayer to God is that the Jewish people might be saved.', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 2, 'I know what enthusiasm they have for God, but it is misdirected zeal.', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 3, 'For they don''t understand God''s way of making people right with himself. Instead, they are clinging to their own way of getting right with God by trying to keep the law. They won''t go along with God''s way.', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 4, 'For Christ has accomplished the whole purpose of the law. All who believe in him are made right with God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 5, 'For Moses wrote that the law''s way of making a person right with God requires obedience to all of its commands.', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 6, 'But the way of getting right with God through faith says, "You don''t need to go to heaven" (to find Christ and bring him down to help you).', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 7, 'And it says, "You don''t need to go to the place of the dead" (to bring Christ back to life again).', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 8, 'Salvation that comes from trusting Christ--which is the message we preach--is already within easy reach. In fact, the Scriptures say, "The message is close at hand; it is on your lips and in your heart."', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 9, 'For if you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 10, 'For it is by believing in your heart that you are made right with God, and it is by confessing with your mouth that you are saved.', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 11, 'As the Scriptures tell us, "Anyone who believes in him will not be disappointed. "', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 12, 'Jew and Gentile are the same in this respect. They all have the same Lord, who generously gives his riches to all who ask for them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 13, 'For "Anyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved."', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 14, 'But how can they call on him to save them unless they believe in him? And how can they believe in him if they have never heard about him? And how can they hear about him unless someone tells them?', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 15, 'And how will anyone go and tell them without being sent? That is what the Scriptures mean when they say, "How beautiful are the feet of those who bring good news!"', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 16, 'But not everyone welcomes the Good News, for Isaiah the prophet said, "Lord, who has believed our message?"', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 17, 'Yet faith comes from listening to this message of good news--the Good News about Christ.', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 18, 'But what about the Jews? Have they actually heard the message? Yes, they have: "The message of God''s creation has gone out to everyone, and its words to all the world."', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 19, 'But did the people of Israel really understand? Yes, they did, for even in the time of Moses, God had said, "I will rouse your jealousy by blessing other nations. I will make you angry by blessing the foolish Gentiles."', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 20, 'And later Isaiah spoke boldly for God: "I was found by people who were not looking for me. I showed myself to those who were not asking for me."', 'NLT'),
(8, 10, 21, 'But regarding Israel, God said, "All day long I opened my arms to them, but they kept disobeying me and arguing with me."', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 1, 'I ask, then, has God rejected his people, the Jews? Of course not! Remember that I myself am a Jew, a descendant of Abraham and a member of the tribe of Benjamin.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 2, 'No, God has not rejected his own people, whom he chose from the very beginning. Do you remember what the Scriptures say about this? Elijah the prophet complained to God about the people of Israel and said,', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 3, '"Lord, they have killed your prophets and torn down your altars. I alone am left, and now they are trying to kill me, too."', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 4, 'And do you remember God''s reply? He said, "You are not the only one left. I have seven thousand others who have never bowed down to Baal!"', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 5, 'It is the same today, for not all the Jews have turned away from God. A few are being saved as a result of God''s kindness in choosing them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 6, 'And if they are saved by God''s kindness, then it is not by their good works. For in that case, God''s wonderful kindness would not be what it really is--free and undeserved.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 7, 'So this is the situation: Most of the Jews have not found the favor of God they are looking for so earnestly. A few have--the ones God has chosen--but the rest were made unresponsive.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 8, 'As the Scriptures say, "God has put them into a deep sleep. To this very day he has shut their eyes so they do not see, and closed their ears so they do not hear."', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 9, 'David spoke of this same thing when he said, "Let their bountiful table become a snare, a trap that makes them think all is well. Let their blessings cause them to stumble.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 10, 'Let their eyes go blind so they cannot see, and let their backs grow weaker and weaker."', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 11, 'Did God''s people stumble and fall beyond recovery? Of course not! His purpose was to make his salvation available to the Gentiles, and then the Jews would be jealous and want it for themselves.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 12, 'Now if the Gentiles were enriched because the Jews turned down God''s offer of salvation, think how much greater a blessing the world will share when the Jews finally accept it.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 13, 'I am saying all of this especially for you Gentiles. God has appointed me as the apostle to the Gentiles. I lay great stress on this,', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 14, 'for I want to find a way to make the Jews want what you Gentiles have, and in that way I might save some of them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 15, 'For since the Jews'' rejection meant that God offered salvation to the rest of the world, how much more wonderful their acceptance will be. It will be life for those who were dead!', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 16, 'And since Abraham and the other patriarchs were holy, their children will also be holy. For if the roots of the tree are holy, the branches will be, too.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 17, 'But some of these branches from Abraham''s tree, some of the Jews, have been broken off. And you Gentiles, who were branches from a wild olive tree, were grafted in. So now you also receive the blessing God has promised Abraham and his children, sharing in God''s rich nourishment of his special olive tree.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 18, 'But you must be careful not to brag about being grafted in to replace the branches that were broken off. Remember, you are just a branch, not the root.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 19, '"Well," you may say, "those branches were broken off to make room for me."', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 20, 'Yes, but remember--those branches, the Jews, were broken off because they didn''t believe God, and you are there because you do believe. Don''t think highly of yourself, but fear what could happen.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 21, 'For if God did not spare the branches he put there in the first place, he won''t spare you either.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 22, 'Notice how God is both kind and severe. He is severe to those who disobeyed, but kind to you as you continue to trust in his kindness. But if you stop trusting, you also will be cut off.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 23, 'And if the Jews turn from their unbelief, God will graft them back into the tree again. He has the power to do it.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 24, 'For if God was willing to take you who were, by nature, branches from a wild olive tree and graft you into his own good tree--a very unusual thing to do--he will be far more eager to graft the Jews back into the tree where they belong.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 25, 'I want you to understand this mystery, dear brothers and sisters, so that you will not feel proud and start bragging. Some of the Jews have hard hearts, but this will last only until the complete number of Gentiles comes to Christ.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 26, 'And so all Israel will be saved. Do you remember what the prophets said about this? "A Deliverer will come from Jerusalem, and he will turn Israel from all ungodliness.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 27, 'And then I will keep my covenant with them and take away their sins."', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 28, 'Many of the Jews are now enemies of the Good News. But this has been to your benefit, for God has given his gifts to you Gentiles. Yet the Jews are still his chosen people because of his promises to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 29, 'For God''s gifts and his call can never be withdrawn.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 30, 'Once, you Gentiles were rebels against God, but when the Jews refused his mercy, God was merciful to you instead.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 31, 'And now, in the same way, the Jews are the rebels, and God''s mercy has come to you. But someday they, too, will share in God''s mercy.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 32, 'For God has imprisoned all people in their own disobedience so he could have mercy on everyone.', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 33, 'Oh, what a wonderful God we have! How great are his riches and wisdom and knowledge! How impossible it is for us to understand his decisions and his methods!', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 34, 'For who can know what the Lord is thinking? Who knows enough to be his counselor?', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 35, 'And who could ever give him so much that he would have to pay it back?', 'NLT'),
(8, 11, 36, 'For everything comes from him; everything exists by his power and is intended for his glory. To him be glory evermore. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 1, 'And so, dear brothers and sisters, I plead with you to give your bodies to God. Let them be a living and holy sacrifice--the kind he will accept. When you think of what he has done for you, is this too much to ask?', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 2, 'Don''t copy the behavior and customs of this world, but let God transform you into a new person by changing the way you think. Then you will know what God wants you to do, and you will know how good and pleasing and perfect his will really is.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 3, 'As God''s messenger, I give each of you this warning: Be honest in your estimate of yourselves, measuring your value by how much faith God has given you.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 4, 'Just as our bodies have many parts and each part has a special function,', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 5, 'so it is with Christ''s body. We are all parts of his one body, and each of us has different work to do. And since we are all one body in Christ, we belong to each other, and each of us needs all the others.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 6, 'God has given each of us the ability to do certain things well. So if God has given you the ability to prophesy, speak out when you have faith that God is speaking through you.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 7, 'If your gift is that of serving others, serve them well. If you are a teacher, do a good job of teaching.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 8, 'If your gift is to encourage others, do it! If you have money, share it generously. If God has given you leadership ability, take the responsibility seriously. And if you have a gift for showing kindness to others, do it gladly.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 9, 'Don''t just pretend that you love others. Really love them. Hate what is wrong. Stand on the side of the good.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 10, 'Love each other with genuine affection, and take delight in honoring each other.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 11, 'Never be lazy in your work, but serve the Lord enthusiastically.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 12, 'Be glad for all God is planning for you. Be patient in trouble, and always be prayerful.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 13, 'When God''s children are in need, be the one to help them out. And get into the habit of inviting guests home for dinner or, if they need lodging, for the night.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 14, 'If people persecute you because you are a Christian, don''t curse them; pray that God will bless them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 15, 'When others are happy, be happy with them. If they are sad, share their sorrow.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 16, 'Live in harmony with each other. Don''t try to act important, but enjoy the company of ordinary people. And don''t think you know it all!', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 17, 'Never pay back evil for evil to anyone. Do things in such a way that everyone can see you are honorable.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 18, 'Do your part to live in peace with everyone, as much as possible.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 19, 'Dear friends, never avenge yourselves. Leave that to God. For it is written, "I will take vengeance; I will repay those who deserve it," says the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 20, 'Instead, do what the Scriptures say: "If your enemies are hungry, feed them. If they are thirsty, give them something to drink, and they will be ashamed of what they have done to you."', 'NLT'),
(8, 12, 21, 'Don''t let evil get the best of you, but conquer evil by doing good.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 1, 'Obey the government, for God is the one who put it there. All governments have been placed in power by God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 2, 'So those who refuse to obey the laws of the land are refusing to obey God, and punishment will follow.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 3, 'For the authorities do not frighten people who are doing right, but they frighten those who do wrong. So do what they say, and you will get along well.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 4, 'The authorities are sent by God to help you. But if you are doing something wrong, of course you should be afraid, for you will be punished. The authorities are established by God for that very purpose, to punish those who do wrong.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 5, 'So you must obey the government for two reasons: to keep from being punished and to keep a clear conscience.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 6, 'Pay your taxes, too, for these same reasons. For government workers need to be paid so they can keep on doing the work God intended them to do.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 7, 'Give to everyone what you owe them: Pay your taxes and import duties, and give respect and honor to all to whom it is due.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 8, 'Pay all your debts, except the debt of love for others. You can never finish paying that! If you love your neighbor, you will fulfill all the requirements of God''s law.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 9, 'For the commandments against adultery and murder and stealing and coveting--and any other commandment--are all summed up in this one commandment: "Love your neighbor as yourself."', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 10, 'Love does no wrong to anyone, so love satisfies all of God''s requirements.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 11, 'Another reason for right living is that you know how late it is; time is running out. Wake up, for the coming of our salvation is nearer now than when we first believed.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 12, 'The night is almost gone; the day of salvation will soon be here. So don''t live in darkness. Get rid of your evil deeds. Shed them like dirty clothes. Clothe yourselves with the armor of right living, as those who live in the light.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 13, 'We should be decent and true in everything we do, so that everyone can approve of our behavior. Don''t participate in wild parties and getting drunk, or in adultery and immoral living, or in fighting and jealousy.', 'NLT'),
(8, 13, 14, 'But let the Lord Jesus Christ take control of you, and don''t think of ways to indulge your evil desires.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 1, 'Accept Christians who are weak in faith, and don''t argue with them about what they think is right or wrong.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 2, 'For instance, one person believes it is all right to eat anything. But another believer who has a sensitive conscience will eat only vegetables.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 3, 'Those who think it is all right to eat anything must not look down on those who won''t. And those who won''t eat certain foods must not condemn those who do, for God has accepted them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 4, 'Who are you to condemn God''s servants? They are responsible to the Lord, so let him tell them whether they are right or wrong. The Lord''s power will help them do as they should.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 5, 'In the same way, some think one day is more holy than another day, while others think every day is alike. Each person should have a personal conviction about this matter.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 6, 'Those who have a special day for worshiping the Lord are trying to honor him. Those who eat all kinds of food do so to honor the Lord, since they give thanks to God before eating. And those who won''t eat everything also want to please the Lord and give thanks to God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 7, 'For we are not our own masters when we live or when we die.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 8, 'While we live, we live to please the Lord. And when we die, we go to be with the Lord. So in life and in death, we belong to the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 9, 'Christ died and rose again for this very purpose, so that he might be Lord of those who are alive and of those who have died.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 10, 'So why do you condemn another Christian? Why do you look down on another Christian? Remember, each of us will stand personally before the judgment seat of God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 11, 'For the Scriptures say, "''As surely as I live,'' says the Lord, ''every knee will bow to me and every tongue will confess allegiance to God.''"', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 12, 'Yes, each of us will have to give a personal account to God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 13, 'So don''t condemn each other anymore. Decide instead to live in such a way that you will not put an obstacle in another Christian''s path.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 14, 'I know and am perfectly sure on the authority of the Lord Jesus that no food, in and of itself, is wrong to eat. But if someone believes it is wrong, then for that person it is wrong.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 15, 'And if another Christian is distressed by what you eat, you are not acting in love if you eat it. Don''t let your eating ruin someone for whom Christ died.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 16, 'Then you will not be condemned for doing something you know is all right.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 17, 'For the Kingdom of God is not a matter of what we eat or drink, but of living a life of goodness and peace and joy in the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 18, 'If you serve Christ with this attitude, you will please God. And other people will approve of you, too.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 19, 'So then, let us aim for harmony in the church and try to build each other up.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 20, 'Don''t tear apart the work of God over what you eat. Remember, there is nothing wrong with these things in themselves. But it is wrong to eat anything if it makes another person stumble.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 21, 'Don''t eat meat or drink wine or do anything else if it might cause another Christian to stumble.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 22, 'You may have the faith to believe that there is nothing wrong with what you are doing, but keep it between yourself and God. Blessed are those who do not condemn themselves by doing something they know is all right.', 'NLT'),
(8, 14, 23, 'But if people have doubts about whether they should eat something, they shouldn''t eat it. They would be condemned for not acting in faith before God. If you do anything you believe is not right, you are sinning.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 1, 'We may know that these things make no difference, but we cannot just go ahead and do them to please ourselves. We must be considerate of the doubts and fears of those who think these things are wrong.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 2, 'We should please others. If we do what helps them, we will build them up in the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 3, 'For even Christ didn''t please himself. As the Scriptures say, "Those who insult you are also insulting me."', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 4, 'Such things were written in the Scriptures long ago to teach us. They give us hope and encouragement as we wait patiently for God''s promises.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 5, 'May God, who gives this patience and encouragement, help you live in complete harmony with each other--each with the attitude of Christ Jesus toward the other.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 6, 'Then all of you can join together with one voice, giving praise and glory to God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 7, 'So accept each other just as Christ has accepted you; then God will be glorified.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 8, 'Remember that Christ came as a servant to the Jews to show that God is true to the promises he made to their ancestors.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 9, 'And he came so the Gentiles might also give glory to God for his mercies to them. That is what the psalmist meant when he wrote: "I will praise you among the Gentiles; I will sing praises to your name."', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 10, 'And in another place it is written, "Rejoice, O you Gentiles, along with his people, the Jews."', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 11, 'And yet again, "Praise the Lord, all you Gentiles; praise him, all you people of the earth."', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 12, 'And the prophet Isaiah said, "The heir to David''s throne will come, and he will rule over the Gentiles. They will place their hopes on him."', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 13, 'So I pray that God, who gives you hope, will keep you happy and full of peace as you believe in him. May you overflow with hope through the power of the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 14, 'I am fully convinced, dear brothers and sisters, that you are full of goodness. You know these things so well that you are able to teach others all about them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 15, 'Even so, I have been bold enough to emphasize some of these points, knowing that all you need is this reminder from me. For I am, by God''s grace,', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 16, 'a special messenger from Christ Jesus to you Gentiles. I bring you the Good News and offer you up as a fragrant sacrifice to God so that you might be pure and pleasing to him by the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 17, 'So it is right for me to be enthusiastic about all Christ Jesus has done through me in my service to God.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 18, 'I dare not boast of anything else. I have brought the Gentiles to God by my message and by the way I lived before them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 19, 'I have won them over by the miracles done through me as signs from God--all by the power of God''s Spirit. In this way, I have fully presented the Good News of Christ all the way from Jerusalem clear over into Illyricum.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 20, 'My ambition has always been to preach the Good News where the name of Christ has never been heard, rather than where a church has already been started by someone else.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 21, 'I have been following the plan spoken of in the Scriptures, where it says, "Those who have never been told about him will see, and those who have never heard of him will understand."', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 22, 'In fact, my visit to you has been delayed so long because I have been preaching in these places.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 23, 'But now I have finished my work in these regions, and after all these long years of waiting, I am eager to visit you.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 24, 'I am planning to go to Spain, and when I do, I will stop off in Rome. And after I have enjoyed your fellowship for a little while, you can send me on my way again.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 25, 'But before I come, I must go down to Jerusalem to take a gift to the Christians there.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 26, 'For you see, the believers in Greece have eagerly taken up an offering for the Christians in Jerusalem, who are going through such hard times.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 27, 'They were very glad to do this because they feel they owe a real debt to them. Since the Gentiles received the wonderful spiritual blessings of the Good News from the Jewish Christians, they feel the least they can do in return is help them financially.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 28, 'As soon as I have delivered this money and completed this good deed of theirs, I will come to see you on my way to Spain.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 29, 'And I am sure that when I come, Christ will give me a great blessing for you.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 30, 'Dear brothers and sisters, I urge you in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ to join me in my struggle by praying to God for me. Do this because of your love for me, given to you by the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 31, 'Pray that I will be rescued from those in Judea who refuse to obey God. Pray also that the Christians there will be willing to accept the donation I am bringing them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 32, 'Then, by the will of God, I will be able to come to you with a happy heart, and we will be an encouragement to each other.', 'NLT'),
(8, 15, 33, 'And now may God, who gives us his peace, be with you all. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 1, 'Our sister Phoebe, a deacon in the church in Cenchrea, will be coming to see you soon.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 2, 'Receive her in the Lord, as one who is worthy of high honor. Help her in every way you can, for she has helped many in their needs, including me.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 3, 'Greet Priscilla and Aquila. They have been co-workers in my ministry for Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 4, 'In fact, they risked their lives for me. I am not the only one who is thankful to them; so are all the Gentile churches.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 5, 'Please give my greetings to the church that meets in their home. Greet my dear friend Epenetus. He was the very first person to become a Christian in the province of Asia.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 6, 'Give my greetings to Mary, who has worked so hard for your benefit.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 7, 'Then there are Andronicus and Junia, my relatives, who were in prison with me. They are respected among the apostles and became Christians before I did. Please give them my greetings.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 8, 'Say hello to Ampliatus, whom I love as one of the Lord''s own children,', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 9, 'and Urbanus, our co-worker in Christ, and beloved Stachys.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 10, 'Give my greetings to Apelles, a good man whom Christ approves. And give my best regards to the members of the household of Aristobulus.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 11, 'Greet Herodion, my relative. Greet the Christians in the household of Narcissus.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 12, 'Say hello to Tryphena and Tryphosa, the Lord''s workers, and to dear Persis, who has worked so hard for the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 13, 'Greet Rufus, whom the Lord picked out to be his very own; and also his dear mother, who has been a mother to me.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 14, 'And please give my greetings to Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas, and the brothers and sisters who are with them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 15, 'Give my greetings to Philologus, Julia, Nereus and his sister, and to Olympas and all the other believers who are with them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 16, 'Greet each other in Christian love. All the churches of Christ send you their greetings.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 17, 'And now I make one more appeal, my dear brothers and sisters. Watch out for people who cause divisions and upset people''s faith by teaching things that are contrary to what you have been taught. Stay away from them.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 18, 'Such people are not serving Christ our Lord; they are serving their own personal interests. By smooth talk and glowing words they deceive innocent people.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 19, 'But everyone knows that you are obedient to the Lord. This makes me very happy. I want you to see clearly what is right and to stay innocent of any wrong.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 20, 'The God of peace will soon crush Satan under your feet. May the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 21, 'Timothy, my fellow worker, and Lucius, Jason, and Sosipater, my relatives, send you their good wishes.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 22, 'I, Tertius, the one who is writing this letter for Paul, send my greetings, too, as a Christian brother.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 23, 'Gaius says hello to you. I am his guest, and the church meets here in his home. Erastus, the city treasurer, sends you his greetings, and so does Quartus, a Christian brother.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 24, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 25, 'God is able to make you strong, just as the Good News says. It is the message about Jesus Christ and his plan for you Gentiles, a plan kept secret from the beginning of time.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 26, 'But now as the prophets foretold and as the eternal God has commanded, this message is made known to all Gentiles everywhere, so that they might believe and obey Christ.', 'NLT'),
(8, 16, 27, 'To God, who alone is wise, be the glory forever through Jesus Christ. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, chosen by the will of God to be an apostle of Christ Jesus, and from our brother Sosthenes.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 2, 'We are writing to the church of God in Corinth, you who have been called by God to be his own holy people. He made you holy by means of Christ Jesus, just as he did all Christians everywhere--whoever calls upon the name of Jesus Christ, our Lord and theirs.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 3, 'May God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ give you his grace and peace.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 4, 'I can never stop thanking God for all the generous gifts he has given you, now that you belong to Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 5, 'He has enriched your church with the gifts of eloquence and every kind of knowledge.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 6, 'This shows that what I told you about Christ is true.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 7, 'Now you have every spiritual gift you need as you eagerly wait for the return of our Lord Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 8, 'He will keep you strong right up to the end, and he will keep you free from all blame on the great day when our Lord Jesus Christ returns.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 9, 'God will surely do this for you, for he always does just what he says, and he is the one who invited you into this wonderful friendship with his Son, Jesus Christ our Lord.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 10, 'Now, dear brothers and sisters, I appeal to you by the authority of the Lord Jesus Christ to stop arguing among yourselves. Let there be real harmony so there won''t be divisions in the church. I plead with you to be of one mind, united in thought and purpose.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 11, 'For some members of Chloe''s household have told me about your arguments, dear brothers and sisters.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 12, 'Some of you are saying, "I am a follower of Paul." Others are saying, "I follow Apollos," or "I follow Peter, "or "I follow only Christ."', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 13, 'Can Christ be divided into pieces? Was I, Paul, crucified for you? Were any of you baptized in the name of Paul?', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 14, 'I thank God that I did not baptize any of you except Crispus and Gaius,', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 15, 'for now no one can say they were baptized in my name.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 16, '(Oh yes, I also baptized the household of Stephanas. I don''t remember baptizing anyone else.)', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 17, 'For Christ didn''t send me to baptize, but to preach the Good News--and not with clever speeches and high-sounding ideas, for fear that the cross of Christ would lose its power.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 18, 'I know very well how foolish the message of the cross sounds to those who are on the road to destruction. But we who are being saved recognize this message as the very power of God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 19, 'As the Scriptures say, "I will destroy human wisdom and discard their most brilliant ideas."', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 20, 'So where does this leave the philosophers, the scholars, and the world''s brilliant debaters? God has made them all look foolish and has shown their wisdom to be useless nonsense.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 21, 'Since God in his wisdom saw to it that the world would never find him through human wisdom, he has used our foolish preaching to save all who believe.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 22, 'God''s way seems foolish to the Jews because they want a sign from heaven to prove it is true. And it is foolish to the Greeks because they believe only what agrees with their own wisdom.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 23, 'So when we preach that Christ was crucified, the Jews are offended, and the Gentiles say it''s all nonsense.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 24, 'But to those called by God to salvation, both Jews and Gentiles, Christ is the mighty power of God and the wonderful wisdom of God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 25, 'This "foolish" plan of God is far wiser than the wisest of human plans, and God''s weakness is far stronger than the greatest of human strength.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 26, 'Remember, dear brothers and sisters, that few of you were wise in the world''s eyes, or powerful, or wealthy when God called you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 27, 'Instead, God deliberately chose things the world considers foolish in order to shame those who think they are wise. And he chose those who are powerless to shame those who are powerful.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 28, 'God chose things despised by the world, things counted as nothing at all, and used them to bring to nothing what the world considers important,', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 29, 'so that no one can ever boast in the presence of God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 30, 'God alone made it possible for you to be in Christ Jesus. For our benefit God made Christ to be wisdom itself. He is the one who made us acceptable to God. He made us pure and holy, and he gave himself to purchase our freedom.', 'NLT'),
(47, 1, 31, 'As the Scriptures say, "The person who wishes to boast should boast only of what the Lord has done."', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 1, 'Dear brothers and sisters, when I first came to you I didn''t use lofty words and brilliant ideas to tell you God''s message.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 2, 'For I decided to concentrate only on Jesus Christ and his death on the cross.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 3, 'I came to you in weakness--timid and trembling.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 4, 'And my message and my preaching were very plain. I did not use wise and persuasive speeches, but the Holy Spirit was powerful among you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 5, 'I did this so that you might trust the power of God rather than human wisdom.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 6, 'Yet when I am among mature Christians, I do speak with words of wisdom, but not the kind of wisdom that belongs to this world, and not the kind that appeals to the rulers of this world, who are being brought to nothing.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 7, 'No, the wisdom we speak of is the secret wisdom of God, which was hidden in former times, though he made it for our benefit before the world began.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 8, 'But the rulers of this world have not understood it; if they had, they would never have crucified our glorious Lord.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 9, 'That is what the Scriptures mean when they say, "No eye has seen, no ear has heard, and no mind has imagined what God has prepared for those who love him."', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 10, 'But we know these things because God has revealed them to us by his Spirit, and his Spirit searches out everything and shows us even God''s deep secrets.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 11, 'No one can know what anyone else is really thinking except that person alone, and no one can know God''s thoughts except God''s own Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 12, 'And God has actually given us his Spirit (not the world''s spirit) so we can know the wonderful things God has freely given us.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 13, 'When we tell you this, we do not use words of human wisdom. We speak words given to us by the Spirit, using the Spirit''s words to explain spiritual truths.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 14, 'But people who aren''t Christians can''t understand these truths from God''s Spirit. It all sounds foolish to them because only those who have the Spirit can understand what the Spirit means.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 15, 'We who have the Spirit understand these things, but others can''t understand us at all.', 'NLT'),
(47, 2, 16, 'How could they? For, "Who can know what the Lord is thinking? Who can give him counsel?" But we can understand these things, for we have the mind of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 1, 'Dear brothers and sisters, when I was with you I couldn''t talk to you as I would to mature Christians. I had to talk as though you belonged to this world or as though you were infants in the Christian life.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 2, 'I had to feed you with milk and not with solid food, because you couldn''t handle anything stronger. And you still aren''t ready,', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 3, 'for you are still controlled by your own sinful desires. You are jealous of one another and quarrel with each other. Doesn''t that prove you are controlled by your own desires? You are acting like people who don''t belong to the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 4, 'When one of you says, "I am a follower of Paul," and another says, "I prefer Apollos," aren''t you acting like those who are not Christians?', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 5, 'Who is Apollos, and who is Paul, that we should be the cause of such quarrels? Why, we''re only servants. Through us God caused you to believe. Each of us did the work the Lord gave us.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 6, 'My job was to plant the seed in your hearts, and Apollos watered it, but it was God, not we, who made it grow.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 7, 'The ones who do the planting or watering aren''t important, but God is important because he is the one who makes the seed grow.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 8, 'The one who plants and the one who waters work as a team with the same purpose. Yet they will be rewarded individually, according to their own hard work.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 9, 'We work together as partners who belong to God. You are God''s field, God''s building--not ours.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 10, 'Because of God''s special favor to me, I have laid the foundation like an expert builder. Now others are building on it. But whoever is building on this foundation must be very careful.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 11, 'For no one can lay any other foundation than the one we already have--Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 12, 'Now anyone who builds on that foundation may use gold, silver, jewels, wood, hay, or straw.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 13, 'But there is going to come a time of testing at the judgment day to see what kind of work each builder has done. Everyone''s work will be put through the fire to see whether or not it keeps its value.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 14, 'If the work survives the fire, that builder will receive a reward.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 15, 'But if the work is burned up, the builder will suffer great loss. The builders themselves will be saved, but like someone escaping through a wall of flames.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 16, 'Don''t you realize that all of you together are the temple of God and that the Spirit of God lives in you?', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 17, 'God will bring ruin upon anyone who ruins this temple. For God''s temple is holy, and you Christians are that temple.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 18, 'Stop fooling yourselves. If you think you are wise by this world''s standards, you will have to become a fool so you can become wise by God''s standards.', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 19, 'For the wisdom of this world is foolishness to God. As the Scriptures say, "God catches those who think they are wise in their own cleverness."', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 20, 'And again, "The Lord knows the thoughts of the wise, that they are worthless."', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 21, 'So don''t take pride in following a particular leader. Everything belongs to you:', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 22, 'Paul and Apollos and Peter; the whole world and life and death; the present and the future. Everything belongs to you,', 'NLT'),
(47, 3, 23, 'and you belong to Christ, and Christ belongs to God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 1, 'So look at Apollos and me as mere servants of Christ who have been put in charge of explaining God''s secrets.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 2, 'Now, a person who is put in charge as a manager must be faithful.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 3, 'What about me? Have I been faithful? Well, it matters very little what you or anyone else thinks. I don''t even trust my own judgment on this point.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 4, 'My conscience is clear, but that isn''t what matters. It is the Lord himself who will examine me and decide.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 5, 'So be careful not to jump to conclusions before the Lord returns as to whether or not someone is faithful. When the Lord comes, he will bring our deepest secrets to light and will reveal our private motives. And then God will give to everyone whatever praise is due.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 6, 'Dear brothers and sisters, I have used Apollos and myself to illustrate what I''ve been saying. If you pay attention to the Scriptures, you won''t brag about one of your leaders at the expense of another.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 7, 'What makes you better than anyone else? What do you have that God hasn''t given you? And if all you have is from God, why boast as though you have accomplished something on your own?', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 8, 'You think you already have everything you need! You are already rich! Without us you have become kings! I wish you really were on your thrones already, for then we would be reigning with you!', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 9, 'But sometimes I think God has put us apostles on display, like prisoners of war at the end of a victor''s parade, condemned to die. We have become a spectacle to the entire world--to people and angels alike.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 10, 'Our dedication to Christ makes us look like fools, but you are so wise! We are weak, but you are so powerful! You are well thought of, but we are laughed at.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 11, 'To this very hour we go hungry and thirsty, without enough clothes to keep us warm. We have endured many beatings, and we have no homes of our own.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 12, 'We have worked wearily with our own hands to earn our living. We bless those who curse us. We are patient with those who abuse us.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 13, 'We respond gently when evil things are said about us. Yet we are treated like the world''s garbage, like everybody''s trash--right up to the present moment.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 14, 'I am not writing these things to shame you, but to warn you as my beloved children.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 15, 'For even if you had ten thousand others to teach you about Christ, you have only one spiritual father. For I became your father in Christ Jesus when I preached the Good News to you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 16, 'So I ask you to follow my example and do as I do.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 17, 'That is the very reason I am sending Timothy--to help you do this. For he is my beloved and trustworthy child in the Lord. He will remind you of what I teach about Christ Jesus in all the churches wherever I go.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 18, 'I know that some of you have become arrogant, thinking I will never visit you again.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 19, 'But I will come--and soon--if the Lord will let me, and then I''ll find out whether these arrogant people are just big talkers or whether they really have God''s power.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 20, 'For the Kingdom of God is not just fancy talk; it is living by God''s power.', 'NLT'),
(47, 4, 21, 'Which do you choose? Should I come with punishment and scolding, or should I come with quiet love and gentleness?', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 1, 'I can hardly believe the report about the sexual immorality going on among you, something so evil that even the pagans don''t do it. I am told that you have a man in your church who is living in sin with his father''s wife.', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 2, 'And you are so proud of yourselves! Why aren''t you mourning in sorrow and shame? And why haven''t you removed this man from your fellowship?', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 3, 'Even though I am not there with you in person, I am with you in the Spirit. Concerning the one who has done this, I have already passed judgment', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 4, 'in the name of the Lord Jesus. You are to call a meeting of the church, and I will be there in spirit, and the power of the Lord Jesus will be with you as you meet.', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 5, 'Then you must cast this man out of the church and into Satan''s hands, so that his sinful nature will be destroyed and he himself will be saved when the Lord returns.', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 6, 'How terrible that you should boast about your spirituality, and yet you let this sort of thing go on. Don''t you realize that if even one person is allowed to go on sinning, soon all will be affected?', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 7, 'Remove this wicked person from among you so that you can stay pure. Christ, our Passover Lamb, has been sacrificed for us.', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 8, 'So let us celebrate the festival, not by eating the old bread of wickedness and evil, but by eating the new bread of purity and truth.', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 9, 'When I wrote to you before, I told you not to associate with people who indulge in sexual sin.', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 10, 'But I wasn''t talking about unbelievers who indulge in sexual sin, or who are greedy or are swindlers or idol worshipers. You would have to leave this world to avoid people like that.', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 11, 'What I meant was that you are not to associate with anyone who claims to be a Christian yet indulges in sexual sin, or is greedy, or worships idols, or is abusive, or a drunkard, or a swindler. Don''t even eat with such people.', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 12, 'It isn''t my responsibility to judge outsiders, but it certainly is your job to judge those inside the church who are sinning in these ways.', 'NLT'),
(47, 5, 13, 'God will judge those on the outside; but as the Scriptures say, "You must remove the evil person from among you."', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 1, 'When you have something against another Christian, why do you file a lawsuit and ask a secular court to decide the matter, instead of taking it to other Christians to decide who is right?', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 2, 'Don''t you know that someday we Christians are going to judge the world? And since you are going to judge the world, can''t you decide these little things among yourselves?', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 3, 'Don''t you realize that we Christians will judge angels? So you should surely be able to resolve ordinary disagreements here on earth.', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 4, 'If you have legal disputes about such matters, why do you go to outside judges who are not respected by the church?', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 5, 'I am saying this to shame you. Isn''t there anyone in all the church who is wise enough to decide these arguments?', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 6, 'But instead, one Christian sues another--right in front of unbelievers!', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 7, 'To have such lawsuits at all is a real defeat for you. Why not just accept the injustice and leave it at that? Why not let yourselves be cheated?', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 8, 'But instead, you yourselves are the ones who do wrong and cheat even your own Christian brothers and sisters.', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 9, 'Don''t you know that those who do wrong will have no share in the Kingdom of God? Don''t fool yourselves. Those who indulge in sexual sin, who are idol worshipers, adulterers, male prostitutes, homosexuals,', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 10, 'thieves, greedy people, drunkards, abusers, and swindlers--none of these will have a share in the Kingdom of God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 11, 'There was a time when some of you were just like that, but now your sins have been washed away, and you have been set apart for God. You have been made right with God because of what the Lord Jesus Christ and the Spirit of our God have done for you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 12, 'You may say, "I am allowed to do anything." But I reply, "Not everything is good for you." And even though "I am allowed to do anything," I must not become a slave to anything.', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 13, 'You say, "Food is for the stomach, and the stomach is for food." This is true, though someday God will do away with both of them. But our bodies were not made for sexual immorality. They were made for the Lord, and the Lord cares about our bodies.', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 14, 'And God will raise our bodies from the dead by his marvelous power, just as he raised our Lord from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 15, 'Don''t you realize that your bodies are actually parts of Christ? Should a man take his body, which belongs to Christ, and join it to a prostitute? Never!', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 16, 'And don''t you know that if a man joins himself to a prostitute, he becomes one body with her? For the Scriptures say, "The two are united into one."', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 17, 'But the person who is joined to the Lord becomes one spirit with him.', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 18, 'Run away from sexual sin! No other sin so clearly affects the body as this one does. For sexual immorality is a sin against your own body.', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 19, 'Or don''t you know that your body is the temple of the Holy Spirit, who lives in you and was given to you by God? You do not belong to yourself,', 'NLT'),
(47, 6, 20, 'for God bought you with a high price. So you must honor God with your body.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 1, 'Now about the questions you asked in your letter. Yes, it is good to live a celibate life.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 2, 'But because there is so much sexual immorality, each man should have his own wife, and each woman should have her own husband.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 3, 'The husband should not deprive his wife of sexual intimacy, which is her right as a married woman, nor should the wife deprive her husband.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 4, 'The wife gives authority over her body to her husband, and the husband also gives authority over his body to his wife.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 5, 'So do not deprive each other of sexual relations. The only exception to this rule would be the agreement of both husband and wife to refrain from sexual intimacy for a limited time, so they can give themselves more completely to prayer. Afterward they should come together again so that Satan won''t be able to tempt them because of their lack of self-control.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 6, 'This is only my suggestion. It''s not meant to be an absolute rule.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 7, 'I wish everyone could get along without marrying, just as I do. But we are not all the same. God gives some the gift of marriage, and to others he gives the gift of singleness.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 8, 'Now I say to those who aren''t married and to widows--it''s better to stay unmarried, just as I am.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 9, 'But if they can''t control themselves, they should go ahead and marry. It''s better to marry than to burn with lust.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 10, 'Now, for those who are married I have a command that comes not from me, but from the Lord. A wife must not leave her husband.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 11, 'But if she does leave him, let her remain single or else go back to him. And the husband must not leave his wife.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 12, 'Now, I will speak to the rest of you, though I do not have a direct command from the Lord. If a Christian man has a wife who is an unbeliever and she is willing to continue living with him, he must not leave her.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 13, 'And if a Christian woman has a husband who is an unbeliever, and he is willing to continue living with her, she must not leave him.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 14, 'For the Christian wife brings holiness to her marriage, and the Christian husband brings holiness to his marriage. Otherwise, your children would not have a godly influence, but now they are set apart for him.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 15, '(But if the husband or wife who isn''t a Christian insists on leaving, let them go. In such cases the Christian husband or wife is not required to stay with them, for God wants his children to live in peace.)', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 16, 'You wives must remember that your husbands might be converted because of you. And you husbands must remember that your wives might be converted because of you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 17, 'You must accept whatever situation the Lord has put you in, and continue on as you were when God first called you. This is my rule for all the churches.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 18, 'For instance, a man who was circumcised before he became a believer should not try to reverse it. And the man who was uncircumcised when he became a believer should not be circumcised now.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 19, 'For it makes no difference whether or not a man has been circumcised. The important thing is to keep God''s commandments.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 20, 'You should continue on as you were when God called you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 21, 'Are you a slave? Don''t let that worry you--but if you get a chance to be free, take it.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 22, 'And remember, if you were a slave when the Lord called you, the Lord has now set you free from the awful power of sin. And if you were free when the Lord called you, you are now a slave of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 23, 'God purchased you at a high price. Don''t be enslaved by the world.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 24, 'So, dear brothers and sisters, whatever situation you were in when you became a believer, stay there in your new relationship with God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 25, 'Now, about the young women who are not yet married. I do not have a command from the Lord for them. But the Lord in his kindness has given me wisdom that can be trusted, and I will share it with you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 26, 'Because of the present crisis, I think it is best to remain just as you are.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 27, 'If you have a wife, do not end the marriage. If you do not have a wife, do not get married.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 28, 'But if you do get married, it is not a sin. And if a young woman gets married, it is not a sin. However, I am trying to spare you the extra problems that come with marriage.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 29, 'Now let me say this, dear brothers and sisters: The time that remains is very short, so husbands should not let marriage be their major concern.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 30, 'Happiness or sadness or wealth should not keep anyone from doing God''s work.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 31, 'Those in frequent contact with the things of the world should make good use of them without becoming attached to them, for this world and all it contains will pass away.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 32, 'In everything you do, I want you to be free from the concerns of this life. An unmarried man can spend his time doing the Lord''s work and thinking how to please him.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 33, 'But a married man can''t do that so well. He has to think about his earthly responsibilities and how to please his wife.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 34, 'His interests are divided. In the same way, a woman who is no longer married or has never been married can be more devoted to the Lord in body and in spirit, while the married woman must be concerned about her earthly responsibilities and how to please her husband.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 35, 'I am saying this for your benefit, not to place restrictions on you. I want you to do whatever will help you serve the Lord best, with as few distractions as possible.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 36, 'But if a man thinks he ought to marry his fiancee because he has trouble controlling his passions and time is passing, it is all right; it is not a sin. Let them marry.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 37, 'But if he has decided firmly not to marry and there is no urgency and he can control his passion, he does well not to marry.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 38, 'So the person who marries does well, and the person who doesn''t marry does even better.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 39, 'A wife is married to her husband as long as he lives. If her husband dies, she is free to marry whomever she wishes, but this must be a marriage acceptable to the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(47, 7, 40, 'But in my opinion it will be better for her if she doesn''t marry again, and I think I am giving you counsel from God''s Spirit when I say this.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 1, 'Now let''s talk about food that has been sacrificed to idols. You think that everyone should agree with your perfect knowledge. While knowledge may make us feel important, it is love that really builds up the church.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 2, 'Anyone who claims to know all the answers doesn''t really know very much.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 3, 'But the person who loves God is the one God knows and cares for.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 4, 'So now, what about it? Should we eat meat that has been sacrificed to idols? Well, we all know that an idol is not really a god and that there is only one God and no other.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 5, 'According to some people, there are many so-called gods and many lords, both in heaven and on earth.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 6, 'But we know that there is only one God, the Father, who created everything, and we exist for him. And there is only one Lord, Jesus Christ, through whom God made everything and through whom we have been given life.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 7, 'However, not all Christians realize this. Some are accustomed to thinking of idols as being real, so when they eat food that has been offered to idols, they think of it as the worship of real gods, and their weak consciences are violated.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 8, 'It''s true that we can''t win God''s approval by what we eat. We don''t miss out on anything if we don''t eat it, and we don''t gain anything if we do.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 9, 'But you must be careful with this freedom of yours. Do not cause a brother or sister with a weaker conscience to stumble.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 10, 'You see, this is what can happen: Weak Christians who think it is wrong to eat this food will see you eating in the temple of an idol. You know there''s nothing wrong with it, but they will be encouraged to violate their conscience by eating food that has been dedicated to the idol.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 11, 'So because of your superior knowledge, a weak Christian, for whom Christ died, will be destroyed.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 12, 'And you are sinning against Christ when you sin against other Christians by encouraging them to do something they believe is wrong.', 'NLT'),
(47, 8, 13, 'If what I eat is going to make another Christian sin, I will never eat meat again as long as I live--for I don''t want to make another Christian stumble.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 1, 'Do I not have as much freedom as anyone else? Am I not an apostle? Haven''t I seen Jesus our Lord with my own eyes? Isn''t it because of my hard work that you are in the Lord?', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 2, 'Even if others think I am not an apostle, I certainly am to you, for you are living proof that I am the Lord''s apostle.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 3, 'This is my answer to those who question my authority as an apostle.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 4, 'Don''t we have the right to live in your homes and share your meals?', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 5, 'Don''t we have the right to bring a Christian wife along with us as the other disciples and the Lord''s brothers and Peter do?', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 6, 'Or is it only Barnabas and I who have to work to support ourselves?', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 7, 'What soldier has to pay his own expenses? And have you ever heard of a farmer who harvests his crop and doesn''t have the right to eat some of it? What shepherd takes care of a flock of sheep and isn''t allowed to drink some of the milk?', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 8, 'And this isn''t merely human opinion. Doesn''t God''s law say the same thing?', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 9, 'For the law of Moses says, "Do not keep an ox from eating as it treads out the grain." Do you suppose God was thinking only about oxen when he said this?', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 10, 'Wasn''t he also speaking to us? Of course he was. Just as farm workers who plow fields and thresh the grain expect a share of the harvest, Christian workers should be paid by those they serve.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 11, 'We have planted good spiritual seed among you. Is it too much to ask, in return, for mere food and clothing?', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 12, 'If you support others who preach to you, shouldn''t we have an even greater right to be supported? Yet we have never used this right. We would rather put up with anything than put an obstacle in the way of the Good News about Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 13, 'Don''t you know that those who work in the Temple get their meals from the food brought to the Temple as offerings? And those who serve at the altar get a share of the sacrificial offerings.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 14, 'In the same way, the Lord gave orders that those who preach the Good News should be supported by those who benefit from it.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 15, 'Yet I have never used any of these rights. And I am not writing this to suggest that I would like to start now. In fact, I would rather die than lose my distinction of preaching without charge.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 16, 'For preaching the Good News is not something I can boast about. I am compelled by God to do it. How terrible for me if I didn''t do it!', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 17, 'If I were doing this of my own free will, then I would deserve payment. But God has chosen me and given me this sacred trust, and I have no choice.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 18, 'What then is my pay? It is the satisfaction I get from preaching the Good News without expense to anyone, never demanding my rights as a preacher.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 19, 'This means I am not bound to obey people just because they pay me, yet I have become a servant of everyone so that I can bring them to Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 20, 'When I am with the Jews, I become one of them so that I can bring them to Christ. When I am with those who follow the Jewish laws, I do the same, even though I am not subject to the law, so that I can bring them to Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 21, 'When I am with the Gentiles who do not have the Jewish law, I fit in with them as much as I can. In this way, I gain their confidence and bring them to Christ. But I do not discard the law of God; I obey the law of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 22, 'When I am with those who are oppressed, I share their oppression so that I might bring them to Christ. Yes, I try to find common ground with everyone so that I might bring them to Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 23, 'I do all this to spread the Good News, and in doing so I enjoy its blessings.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 24, 'Remember that in a race everyone runs, but only one person gets the prize. You also must run in such a way that you will win.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 25, 'All athletes practice strict self-control. They do it to win a prize that will fade away, but we do it for an eternal prize.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 26, 'So I run straight to the goal with purpose in every step. I am not like a boxer who misses his punches.', 'NLT'),
(47, 9, 27, 'I discipline my body like an athlete, training it to do what it should. Otherwise, I fear that after preaching to others I myself might be disqualified.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 1, 'I don''t want you to forget, dear brothers and sisters, what happened to our ancestors in the wilderness long ago. God guided all of them by sending a cloud that moved along ahead of them, and he brought them all safely through the waters of the sea on dry ground.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 2, 'As followers of Moses, they were all baptized in the cloud and the sea.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 3, 'And all of them ate the same miraculous food,', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 4, 'and all of them drank the same miraculous water. For they all drank from the miraculous rock that traveled with them, and that rock was Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 5, 'Yet after all this, God was not pleased with most of them, and he destroyed them in the wilderness.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 6, 'These events happened as a warning to us, so that we would not crave evil things as they did', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 7, 'or worship idols as some of them did. For the Scriptures say, "The people celebrated with feasting and drinking, and they indulged themselves in pagan revelry."', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 8, 'And we must not engage in sexual immorality as some of them did, causing 23,000 of them to die in one day.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 9, 'Nor should we put Christ to the test, as some of them did and then died from snakebites.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 10, 'And don''t grumble as some of them did, for that is why God sent his angel of death to destroy them.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 11, 'All these events happened to them as examples for us. They were written down to warn us, who live at the time when this age is drawing to a close.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 12, 'If you think you are standing strong, be careful, for you, too, may fall into the same sin.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 13, 'But remember that the temptations that come into your life are no different from what others experience. And God is faithful. He will keep the temptation from becoming so strong that you can''t stand up against it. When you are tempted, he will show you a way out so that you will not give in to it.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 14, 'So, my dear friends, flee from the worship of idols.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 15, 'You are reasonable people. Decide for yourselves if what I am about to say is true.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 16, 'When we bless the cup at the Lord''s Table, aren''t we sharing in the benefits of the blood of Christ? And when we break the loaf of bread, aren''t we sharing in the benefits of the body of Christ?', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 17, 'And we all eat from one loaf, showing that we are one body.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 18, 'And think about the nation of Israel; all who eat the sacrifices are united by that act.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 19, 'What am I trying to say? Am I saying that the idols to whom the pagans bring sacrifices are real gods and that these sacrifices are of some value?', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 20, 'No, not at all. What I am saying is that these sacrifices are offered to demons, not to God. And I don''t want any of you to be partners with demons.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 21, 'You cannot drink from the cup of the Lord and from the cup of demons, too. You cannot eat at the Lord''s Table and at the table of demons, too.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 22, 'What? Do you dare to rouse the Lord''s jealousy as Israel did? Do you think we are stronger than he is?', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 23, 'You say, "I am allowed to do anything"--but not everything is helpful. You say, "I am allowed to do anything"--but not everything is beneficial.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 24, 'Don''t think only of your own good. Think of other Christians and what is best for them.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 25, 'Here''s what you should do. You may eat any meat that is sold in the marketplace. Don''t ask whether or not it was offered to idols, and then your conscience won''t be bothered.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 26, 'For "the earth is the Lord''s, and everything in it."', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 27, 'If someone who isn''t a Christian asks you home for dinner, go ahead; accept the invitation if you want to. Eat whatever is offered to you and don''t ask any questions about it. Your conscience should not be bothered by this.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 28, 'But suppose someone warns you that this meat has been offered to an idol. Don''t eat it, out of consideration for the conscience of the one who told you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 29, 'It might not be a matter of conscience for you, but it is for the other person. Now, why should my freedom be limited by what someone else thinks?', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 30, 'If I can thank God for the food and enjoy it, why should I be condemned for eating it?', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 31, 'Whatever you eat or drink or whatever you do, you must do all for the glory of God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 32, 'Don''t give offense to Jews or Gentiles or the church of God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 10, 33, 'That is the plan I follow, too. I try to please everyone in everything I do. I don''t just do what I like or what is best for me, but what is best for them so they may be saved.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 1, 'And you should follow my example, just as I follow Christ''s.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 2, 'I am so glad, dear friends, that you always keep me in your thoughts and you are following the Christian teaching I passed on to you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 3, 'But there is one thing I want you to know: A man is responsible to Christ, a woman is responsible to her husband, and Christ is responsible to God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 4, 'A man dishonors Christ if he covers his head while praying or prophesying.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 5, 'But a woman dishonors her husband if she prays or prophesies without a covering on her head, for this is the same as shaving her head.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 6, 'Yes, if she refuses to wear a head covering, she should cut off all her hair. And since it is shameful for a woman to have her hair cut or her head shaved, then she should wear a covering.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 7, 'A man should not wear anything on his head when worshiping, for man is God''s glory, made in God''s own image, but woman is the glory of man.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 8, 'For the first man didn''t come from woman, but the first woman came from man.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 9, 'And man was not made for woman''s benefit, but woman was made for man.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 10, 'So a woman should wear a covering on her head as a sign of authority because the angels are watching.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 11, 'But in relationships among the Lord''s people, women are not independent of men, and men are not independent of women.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 12, 'For although the first woman came from man, all men have been born from women ever since, and everything comes from God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 13, 'What do you think about this? Is it right for a woman to pray to God in public without covering her head?', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 14, 'Isn''t it obvious that it''s disgraceful for a man to have long hair?', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 15, 'And isn''t it obvious that long hair is a woman''s pride and joy? For it has been given to her as a covering.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 16, 'But if anyone wants to argue about this, all I can say is that we have no other custom than this, and all the churches of God feel the same way about it.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 17, 'But now when I mention this next issue, I cannot praise you. For it sounds as if more harm than good is done when you meet together.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 18, 'First of all, I hear that there are divisions among you when you meet as a church, and to some extent I believe it.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 19, 'But, of course, there must be divisions among you so that those of you who are right will be recognized!', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 20, 'It''s not the Lord''s Supper you are concerned about when you come together.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 21, 'For I am told that some of you hurry to eat your own meal without sharing with others. As a result, some go hungry while others get drunk.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 22, 'What? Is this really true? Don''t you have your own homes for eating and drinking? Or do you really want to disgrace the church of God and shame the poor? What am I supposed to say about these things? Do you want me to praise you? Well, I certainly do not!', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 23, 'For this is what the Lord himself said, and I pass it on to you just as I received it. On the night when he was betrayed, the Lord Jesus took a loaf of bread,', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 24, 'and when he had given thanks, he broke it and said, "This is my body, which is given for you. Do this in remembrance of me."', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 25, 'In the same way, he took the cup of wine after supper, saying, "This cup is the new covenant between God and you, sealed by the shedding of my blood. Do this in remembrance of me as often as you drink it."', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 26, 'For every time you eat this bread and drink this cup, you are announcing the Lord''s death until he comes again.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 27, 'So if anyone eats this bread or drinks this cup of the Lord unworthily, that person is guilty of sinning against the body and the blood of the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 28, 'That is why you should examine yourself before eating the bread and drinking from the cup.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 29, 'For if you eat the bread or drink the cup unworthily, not honoring the body of Christ, you are eating and drinking God''s judgment upon yourself.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 30, 'That is why many of you are weak and sick and some have even died.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 31, 'But if we examine ourselves, we will not be examined by God and judged in this way.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 32, 'But when we are judged and disciplined by the Lord, we will not be condemned with the world.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 33, 'So, dear brothers and sisters, when you gather for the Lord''s Supper, wait for each other.', 'NLT'),
(47, 11, 34, 'If you are really hungry, eat at home so you won''t bring judgment upon yourselves when you meet together. I''ll give you instructions about the other matters after I arrive.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 1, 'And now, dear brothers and sisters, I will write about the special abilities the Holy Spirit gives to each of us, for I must correct your misunderstandings about them.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 2, 'You know that when you were still pagans you were led astray and swept along in worshiping speechless idols.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 3, 'So I want you to know how to discern what is truly from God: No one speaking by the Spirit of God can curse Jesus, and no one is able to say, "Jesus is Lord," except by the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 4, 'Now there are different kinds of spiritual gifts, but it is the same Holy Spirit who is the source of them all.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 5, 'There are different kinds of service in the church, but it is the same Lord we are serving.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 6, 'There are different ways God works in our lives, but it is the same God who does the work through all of us.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 7, 'A spiritual gift is given to each of us as a means of helping the entire church.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 8, 'To one person the Spirit gives the ability to give wise advice; to another he gives the gift of special knowledge.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 9, 'The Spirit gives special faith to another, and to someone else he gives the power to heal the sick.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 10, 'He gives one person the power to perform miracles, and to another the ability to prophesy. He gives someone else the ability to know whether it is really the Spirit of God or another spirit that is speaking. Still another person is given the ability to speak in unknown languages, and another is given the ability to interpret what is being said.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 11, 'It is the one and only Holy Spirit who distributes these gifts. He alone decides which gift each person should have.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 12, 'The human body has many parts, but the many parts make up only one body. So it is with the body of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 13, 'Some of us are Jews, some are Gentiles, some are slaves, and some are free. But we have all been baptized into Christ''s body by one Spirit, and we have all received the same Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 14, 'Yes, the body has many different parts, not just one part.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 15, 'If the foot says, "I am not a part of the body because I am not a hand," that does not make it any less a part of the body.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 16, 'And if the ear says, "I am not part of the body because I am only an ear and not an eye," would that make it any less a part of the body?', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 17, 'Suppose the whole body were an eye--then how would you hear? Or if your whole body were just one big ear, how could you smell anything?', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 18, 'But God made our bodies with many parts, and he has put each part just where he wants it.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 19, 'What a strange thing a body would be if it had only one part!', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 20, 'Yes, there are many parts, but only one body.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 21, 'The eye can never say to the hand, "I don''t need you." The head can''t say to the feet, "I don''t need you."', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 22, 'In fact, some of the parts that seem weakest and least important are really the most necessary.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 23, 'And the parts we regard as less honorable are those we clothe with the greatest care. So we carefully protect from the eyes of others those parts that should not be seen,', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 24, 'while other parts do not require this special care. So God has put the body together in such a way that extra honor and care are given to those parts that have less dignity.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 25, 'This makes for harmony among the members, so that all the members care for each other equally.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 26, 'If one part suffers, all the parts suffer with it, and if one part is honored, all the parts are glad.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 27, 'Now all of you together are Christ''s body, and each one of you is a separate and necessary part of it.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 28, 'Here is a list of some of the members that God has placed in the body of Christ: first are apostles, second are prophets, third are teachers, then those who do miracles, those who have the gift of healing, those who can help others, those who can get others to work together, those who speak in unknown languages.', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 29, 'Is everyone an apostle? Of course not. Is everyone a prophet? No. Are all teachers? Does everyone have the power to do miracles?', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 30, 'Does everyone have the gift of healing? Of course not. Does God give all of us the ability to speak in unknown languages? Can everyone interpret unknown languages? No!', 'NLT'),
(47, 12, 31, 'And in any event, you should desire the most helpful gifts. First, however, let me tell you about something else that is better than any of them!', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 1, 'If I could speak in any language in heaven or on earth but didn''t love others, I would only be making meaningless noise like a loud gong or a clanging cymbal.', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 2, 'If I had the gift of prophecy, and if I knew all the mysteries of the future and knew everything about everything, but didn''t love others, what good would I be? And if I had the gift of faith so that I could speak to a mountain and make it move, without love I would be no good to anybody.', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 3, 'If I gave everything I have to the poor and even sacrificed my body, I could boast about it; but if I didn''t love others, I would be of no value whatsoever.', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 4, 'Love is patient and kind. Love is not jealous or boastful or proud', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 5, 'or rude. Love does not demand its own way. Love is not irritable, and it keeps no record of when it has been wronged.', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 6, 'It is never glad about injustice but rejoices whenever the truth wins out.', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 7, 'Love never gives up, never loses faith, is always hopeful, and endures through every circumstance.', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 8, 'Love will last forever, but prophecy and speaking in unknown languages and special knowledge will all disappear.', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 9, 'Now we know only a little, and even the gift of prophecy reveals little!', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 10, 'But when the end comes, these special gifts will all disappear.', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 11, 'It''s like this: When I was a child, I spoke and thought and reasoned as a child does. But when I grew up, I put away childish things.', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 12, 'Now we see things imperfectly as in a poor mirror, but then we will see everything with perfect clarity. All that I know now is partial and incomplete, but then I will know everything completely, just as God knows me now.', 'NLT'),
(47, 13, 13, 'There are three things that will endure--faith, hope, and love--and the greatest of these is love.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 1, 'Let love be your highest goal, but also desire the special abilities the Spirit gives, especially the gift of prophecy.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 2, 'For if your gift is the ability to speak in tongues, you will be talking to God but not to people, since they won''t be able to understand you. You will be speaking by the power of the Spirit, but it will all be mysterious.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 3, 'But one who prophesies is helping others grow in the Lord, encouraging and comforting them.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 4, 'A person who speaks in tongues is strengthened personally in the Lord, but one who speaks a word of prophecy strengthens the entire church.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 5, 'I wish you all had the gift of speaking in tongues, but even more I wish you were all able to prophesy. For prophecy is a greater and more useful gift than speaking in tongues, unless someone interprets what you are saying so that the whole church can get some good out of it.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 6, 'Dear brothers and sisters, if I should come to you talking in an unknown language, how would that help you? But if I bring you some revelation or some special knowledge or some prophecy or some teaching--that is what will help you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 7, 'Even musical instruments like the flute or the harp, though they are lifeless, are examples of the need for speaking in plain language. For no one will recognize the melody unless the notes are played clearly.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 8, 'And if the bugler doesn''t sound a clear call, how will the soldiers know they are being called to battle?', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 9, 'And it''s the same for you. If you talk to people in a language they don''t understand, how will they know what you mean? You might as well be talking to an empty room.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 10, 'There are so many different languages in the world, and all are excellent for those who understand them,', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 11, 'but to me they mean nothing. I will not understand people who speak those languages, and they will not understand me.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 12, 'Since you are so eager to have spiritual gifts, ask God for those that will be of real help to the whole church.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 13, 'So anyone who has the gift of speaking in tongues should pray also for the gift of interpretation in order to tell people plainly what has been said.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 14, 'For if I pray in tongues, my spirit is praying, but I don''t understand what I am saying.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 15, 'Well then, what shall I do? I will do both. I will pray in the spirit, and I will pray in words I understand. I will sing in the spirit, and I will sing in words I understand.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 16, 'For if you praise God only in the spirit, how can those who don''t understand you praise God along with you? How can they join you in giving thanks when they don''t understand what you are saying?', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 17, 'You will be giving thanks very nicely, no doubt, but it doesn''t help the other people present.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 18, 'I thank God that I speak in tongues more than all of you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 19, 'But in a church meeting I would much rather speak five understandable words that will help others than ten thousand words in an unknown language.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 20, 'Dear brothers and sisters, don''t be childish in your understanding of these things. Be innocent as babies when it comes to evil, but be mature and wise in understanding matters of this kind.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 21, 'It is written in the Scriptures, "I will speak to my own people through unknown languages and through the lips of foreigners. But even then, they will not listen to me," says the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 22, 'So you see that speaking in tongues is a sign, not for believers, but for unbelievers; prophecy, however, is for the benefit of believers, not unbelievers.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 23, 'Even so, if unbelievers or people who don''t understand these things come into your meeting and hear everyone talking in an unknown language, they will think you are crazy.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 24, 'But if all of you are prophesying, and unbelievers or people who don''t understand these things come into your meeting, they will be convicted of sin, and they will be condemned by what you say.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 25, 'As they listen, their secret thoughts will be laid bare, and they will fall down on their knees and worship God, declaring, "God is really here among you."', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 26, 'Well, my brothers and sisters, let''s summarize what I am saying. When you meet, one will sing, another will teach, another will tell some special revelation God has given, one will speak in an unknown language, while another will interpret what is said. But everything that is done must be useful to all and build them up in the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 27, 'No more than two or three should speak in an unknown language. They must speak one at a time, and someone must be ready to interpret what they are saying.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 28, 'But if no one is present who can interpret, they must be silent in your church meeting and speak in tongues to God privately.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 29, 'Let two or three prophesy, and let the others evaluate what is said.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 30, 'But if someone is prophesying and another person receives a revelation from the Lord, the one who is speaking must stop.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 31, 'In this way, all who prophesy will have a turn to speak, one after the other, so that everyone will learn and be encouraged.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 32, 'Remember that people who prophesy are in control of their spirit and can wait their turn.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 33, 'For God is not a God of disorder but of peace, as in all the other churches.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 34, 'Women should be silent during the church meetings. It is not proper for them to speak. They should be submissive, just as the law says.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 35, 'If they have any questions to ask, let them ask their husbands at home, for it is improper for women to speak in church meetings.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 36, 'Do you think that the knowledge of God''s word begins and ends with you Corinthians? Well, you are mistaken!', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 37, 'If you claim to be a prophet or think you are very spiritual, you should recognize that what I am saying is a command from the Lord himself.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 38, 'But if you do not recognize this, you will not be recognized.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 39, 'So, dear brothers and sisters, be eager to prophesy, and don''t forbid speaking in tongues.', 'NLT'),
(47, 14, 40, 'But be sure that everything is done properly and in order.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 1, 'Now let me remind you, dear brothers and sisters, of the Good News I preached to you before. You welcomed it then and still do now, for your faith is built on this wonderful message.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 2, 'And it is this Good News that saves you if you firmly believe it--unless, of course, you believed something that was never true in the first place.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 3, 'I passed on to you what was most important and what had also been passed on to me--that Christ died for our sins, just as the Scriptures said.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 4, 'He was buried, and he was raised from the dead on the third day, as the Scriptures said.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 5, 'He was seen by Peter and then by the twelve apostles.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 6, 'After that, he was seen by more than five hundred of his followers at one time, most of whom are still alive, though some have died by now.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 7, 'Then he was seen by James and later by all the apostles.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 8, 'Last of all, I saw him, too, long after the others, as though I had been born at the wrong time.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 9, 'For I am the least of all the apostles, and I am not worthy to be called an apostle after the way I persecuted the church of God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 10, 'But whatever I am now, it is all because God poured out his special favor on me--and not without results. For I have worked harder than all the other apostles, yet it was not I but God who was working through me by his grace.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 11, 'So it makes no difference whether I preach or they preach. The important thing is that you believed what we preached to you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 12, 'But tell me this--since we preach that Christ rose from the dead, why are some of you saying there will be no resurrection of the dead?', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 13, 'For if there is no resurrection of the dead, then Christ has not been raised either.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 14, 'And if Christ was not raised, then all our preaching is useless, and your trust in God is useless.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 15, 'And we apostles would all be lying about God, for we have said that God raised Christ from the grave, but that can''t be true if there is no resurrection of the dead.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 16, 'If there is no resurrection of the dead, then Christ has not been raised.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 17, 'And if Christ has not been raised, then your faith is useless, and you are still under condemnation for your sins.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 18, 'In that case, all who have died believing in Christ have perished!', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 19, 'And if we have hope in Christ only for this life, we are the most miserable people in the world.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 20, 'But the fact is that Christ has been raised from the dead. He has become the first of a great harvest of those who will be raised to life again.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 21, 'So you see, just as death came into the world through a man, Adam, now the resurrection from the dead has begun through another man, Christ.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 22, 'Everyone dies because all of us are related to Adam, the first man. But all who are related to Christ, the other man, will be given new life.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 23, 'But there is an order to this resurrection: Christ was raised first; then when Christ comes back, all his people will be raised.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 24, 'After that the end will come, when he will turn the Kingdom over to God the Father, having put down all enemies of every kind.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 25, 'For Christ must reign until he humbles all his enemies beneath his feet.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 26, 'And the last enemy to be destroyed is death.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 27, 'For the Scriptures say, "God has given him authority over all things." (Of course, when it says "authority over all things," it does not include God himself, who gave Christ his authority.)', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 28, 'Then, when he has conquered all things, the Son will present himself to God, so that God, who gave his Son authority over all things, will be utterly supreme over everything everywhere.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 29, 'If the dead will not be raised, then what point is there in people being baptized for those who are dead? Why do it unless the dead will someday rise again?', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 30, 'And why should we ourselves be continually risking our lives, facing death hour by hour?', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 31, 'For I swear, dear brothers and sisters, I face death daily. This is as certain as my pride in what the Lord Jesus Christ has done in you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 32, 'And what value was there in fighting wild beasts--those men of Ephesus--if there will be no resurrection from the dead? If there is no resurrection, "Let''s feast and get drunk, for tomorrow we die!"', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 33, 'Don''t be fooled by those who say such things, for "bad company corrupts good character."', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 34, 'Come to your senses and stop sinning. For to your shame I say that some of you don''t even know God.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 35, 'But someone may ask, "How will the dead be raised? What kind of bodies will they have?"', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 36, 'What a foolish question! When you put a seed into the ground, it doesn''t grow into a plant unless it dies first.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 37, 'And what you put in the ground is not the plant that will grow, but only a dry little seed of wheat or whatever it is you are planting.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 38, 'Then God gives it a new body--just the kind he wants it to have. A different kind of plant grows from each kind of seed.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 39, 'And just as there are different kinds of seeds and plants, so also there are different kinds of flesh--whether of humans, animals, birds, or fish.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 40, 'There are bodies in the heavens, and there are bodies on earth. The glory of the heavenly bodies is different from the beauty of the earthly bodies.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 41, 'The sun has one kind of glory, while the moon and stars each have another kind. And even the stars differ from each other in their beauty and brightness.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 42, 'It is the same way for the resurrection of the dead. Our earthly bodies, which die and decay, will be different when they are resurrected, for they will never die.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 43, 'Our bodies now disappoint us, but when they are raised, they will be full of glory. They are weak now, but when they are raised, they will be full of power.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 44, 'They are natural human bodies now, but when they are raised, they will be spiritual bodies. For just as there are natural bodies, so also there are spiritual bodies.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 45, 'The Scriptures tell us, "The first man, Adam, became a living person." But the last Adam--that is, Christ--is a life-giving Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 46, 'What came first was the natural body, then the spiritual body comes later.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 47, 'Adam, the first man, was made from the dust of the earth, while Christ, the second man, came from heaven.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 48, 'Every human being has an earthly body just like Adam''s, but our heavenly bodies will be just like Christ''s.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 49, 'Just as we are now like Adam, the man of the earth, so we will someday be like Christ, the man from heaven.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 50, 'What I am saying, dear brothers and sisters, is that flesh and blood cannot inherit the Kingdom of God. These perishable bodies of ours are not able to live forever.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 51, 'But let me tell you a wonderful secret God has revealed to us. Not all of us will die, but we will all be transformed.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 52, 'It will happen in a moment, in the blinking of an eye, when the last trumpet is blown. For when the trumpet sounds, the Christians who have died will be raised with transformed bodies. And then we who are living will be transformed so that we will never die.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 53, 'For our perishable earthly bodies must be transformed into heavenly bodies that will never die.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 54, 'When this happens--when our perishable earthly bodies have been transformed into heavenly bodies that will never die--then at last the Scriptures will come true: "Death is swallowed up in victory.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 55, 'O death, where is your victory? O death, where is your sting?"', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 56, 'For sin is the sting that results in death, and the law gives sin its power.', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 57, 'How we thank God, who gives us victory over sin and death through Jesus Christ our Lord!', 'NLT'),
(47, 15, 58, 'So, my dear brothers and sisters, be strong and steady, always enthusiastic about the Lord''s work, for you know that nothing you do for the Lord is ever useless.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 1, 'Now about the money being collected for the Christians in Jerusalem: You should follow the same procedures I gave to the churches in Galatia.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 2, 'On every Lord''s Day, each of you should put aside some amount of money in relation to what you have earned and save it for this offering. Don''t wait until I get there and then try to collect it all at once.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 3, 'When I come I will write letters of recommendation for the messengers you choose to deliver your gift to Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 4, 'And if it seems appropriate for me also to go along, then we can travel together.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 5, 'I am coming to visit you after I have been to Macedonia, for I am planning to travel through Macedonia.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 6, 'It could be that I will stay awhile with you, perhaps all winter, and then you can send me on my way to the next destination.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 7, 'This time I don''t want to make just a short visit and then go right on. I want to come and stay awhile, if the Lord will let me.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 8, 'In the meantime, I will be staying here at Ephesus until the Festival of Pentecost,', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 9, 'for there is a wide-open door for a great work here, and many people are responding. But there are many who oppose me.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 10, 'When Timothy comes, treat him with respect. He is doing the Lord''s work, just as I am.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 11, 'Don''t let anyone despise him. Send him on his way with your blessings when he returns to me. I am looking forward to seeing him soon, along with the other brothers.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 12, 'Now about our brother Apollos--I urged him to join the other brothers when they visit you, but he was not willing to come right now. He will be seeing you later, when the time is right.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 13, 'Be on guard. Stand true to what you believe. Be courageous. Be strong.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 14, 'And everything you do must be done with love.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 15, 'You know that Stephanas and his household were the first to become Christians in Greece, and they are spending their lives in service to other Christians. I urge you, dear brothers and sisters,', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 16, 'to respect them fully and others like them who serve with such real devotion.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 17, 'I am so glad that Stephanas, Fortunatus, and Achaicus have come here. They have been making up for the help you weren''t here to give me.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 18, 'They have been a wonderful encouragement to me, as they have been to you, too. You must give proper honor to all who serve so well.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 19, 'The churches here in the province of Asia greet you heartily in the Lord, along with Aquila and Priscilla and all the others who gather in their home for church meetings.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 20, 'All the brothers and sisters here have asked me to greet you for them. Greet each other in Christian love.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 21, 'Here is my greeting, which I write with my own hand--PAUL.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 22, 'If anyone does not love the Lord, that person is cursed. Our Lord, come!', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 23, 'May the grace of the Lord Jesus be with you.', 'NLT'),
(47, 16, 24, 'My love to all of you in Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, appointed by God to be an apostle of Christ Jesus, and from our dear brother Timothy. We are writing to God''s church in Corinth and to all the Christians throughout Greece.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 2, 'May God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ give you his grace and peace.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 3, 'All praise to the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ. He is the source of every mercy and the God who comforts us.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 4, 'He comforts us in all our troubles so that we can comfort others. When others are troubled, we will be able to give them the same comfort God has given us.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 5, 'You can be sure that the more we suffer for Christ, the more God will shower us with his comfort through Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 6, 'So when we are weighed down with troubles, it is for your benefit and salvation! For when God comforts us, it is so that we, in turn, can be an encouragement to you. Then you can patiently endure the same things we suffer.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 7, 'We are confident that as you share in suffering, you will also share God''s comfort.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 8, 'I think you ought to know, dear brothers and sisters, about the trouble we went through in the province of Asia. We were crushed and completely overwhelmed, and we thought we would never live through it.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 9, 'In fact, we expected to die. But as a result, we learned not to rely on ourselves, but on God who can raise the dead.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 10, 'And he did deliver us from mortal danger. And we are confident that he will continue to deliver us.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 11, 'He will rescue us because you are helping by praying for us. As a result, many will give thanks to God because so many people''s prayers for our safety have been answered.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 12, 'We can say with confidence and a clear conscience that we have been honest and sincere in all our dealings. We have depended on God''s grace, not on our own earthly wisdom. That is how we have acted toward everyone, and especially toward you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 13, 'My letters have been straightforward, and there is nothing written between the lines and nothing you can''t understand. I hope someday you will fully understand us,', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 14, 'even if you don''t fully understand us now. Then on the day when our Lord Jesus comes back again, you will be proud of us in the same way we are proud of you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 15, 'Since I was so sure of your understanding and trust, I wanted to give you a double blessing.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 16, 'I wanted to stop and see you on my way to Macedonia and again on my return trip. Then you could send me on my way to Judea.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 17, 'You may be asking why I changed my plan. Hadn''t I made up my mind yet? Or am I like people of the world who say yes when they really mean no?', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 18, 'As surely as God is true, I am not that sort of person. My yes means yes', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 19, 'because Jesus Christ, the Son of God, never wavers between yes and no. He is the one whom Timothy, Silas, and I preached to you, and he is the divine Yes--God''s affirmation.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 20, 'For all of God''s promises have been fulfilled in him. That is why we say "Amen" when we give glory to God through Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 21, 'It is God who gives us, along with you, the ability to stand firm for Christ. He has commissioned us,', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 22, 'and he has identified us as his own by placing the Holy Spirit in our hearts as the first installment of everything he will give us.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 23, 'Now I call upon God as my witness that I am telling the truth. The reason I didn''t return to Corinth was to spare you from a severe rebuke.', 'NLT'),
(48, 1, 24, 'But that does not mean we want to tell you exactly how to put your faith into practice. We want to work together with you so you will be full of joy as you stand firm in your faith.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 1, 'So I said to myself, "No, I won''t do it. I won''t make them unhappy with another painful visit."', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 2, 'For if I cause you pain and make you sad, who is going to make me glad?', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 3, 'That is why I wrote as I did in my last letter, so that when I do come, I will not be made sad by the very ones who ought to give me the greatest joy. Surely you know that my happiness depends on your happiness.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 4, 'How painful it was to write that letter! Heartbroken, I cried over it. I didn''t want to hurt you, but I wanted you to know how very much I love you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 5, 'I am not overstating it when I say that the man who caused all the trouble hurt your entire church more than he hurt me.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 6, 'He was punished enough when most of you were united in your judgment against him.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 7, 'Now it is time to forgive him and comfort him. Otherwise he may become so discouraged that he won''t be able to recover.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 8, 'Now show him that you still love him.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 9, 'I wrote to you as I did to find out how far you would go in obeying me.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 10, 'When you forgive this man, I forgive him, too. And when I forgive him (for whatever is to be forgiven), I do so with Christ''s authority for your benefit,', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 11, 'so that Satan will not outsmart us. For we are very familiar with his evil schemes.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 12, 'Well, when I came to the city of Troas to preach the Good News of Christ, the Lord gave me tremendous opportunities.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 13, 'But I couldn''t rest because my dear brother Titus hadn''t yet arrived with a report from you. So I said good-bye and went on to Macedonia to find him.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 14, 'But thanks be to God, who made us his captives and leads us along in Christ''s triumphal procession. Now wherever we go he uses us to tell others about the Lord and to spread the Good News like a sweet perfume.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 15, 'Our lives are a fragrance presented by Christ to God. But this fragrance is perceived differently by those being saved and by those perishing.', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 16, 'To those who are perishing we are a fearful smell of death and doom. But to those who are being saved we are a life-giving perfume. And who is adequate for such a task as this?', 'NLT'),
(48, 2, 17, 'You see, we are not like those hucksters--and there are many of them--who preach just to make money. We preach God''s message with sincerity and with Christ''s authority. And we know that the God who sent us is watching us.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 1, 'Are we beginning again to tell you how good we are? Some people need to bring letters of recommendation with them or ask you to write letters of recommendation for them.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 2, 'But the only letter of recommendation we need is you yourselves! Your lives are a letter written in our hearts, and everyone can read it and recognize our good work among you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 3, 'Clearly, you are a letter from Christ prepared by us. It is written not with pen and ink, but with the Spirit of the living God. It is carved not on stone, but on human hearts.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 4, 'We are confident of all this because of our great trust in God through Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 5, 'It is not that we think we can do anything of lasting value by ourselves. Our only power and success come from God.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 6, 'He is the one who has enabled us to represent his new covenant. This is a covenant, not of written laws, but of the Spirit. The old way ends in death; in the new way, the Holy Spirit gives life.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 7, 'That old system of law etched in stone led to death, yet it began with such glory that the people of Israel could not bear to look at Moses'' face. For his face shone with the glory of God, even though the brightness was already fading away.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 8, 'Shouldn''t we expect far greater glory when the Holy Spirit is giving life?', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 9, 'If the old covenant, which brings condemnation, was glorious, how much more glorious is the new covenant, which makes us right with God!', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 10, 'In fact, that first glory was not glorious at all compared with the overwhelming glory of the new covenant.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 11, 'So if the old covenant, which has been set aside, was full of glory, then the new covenant, which remains forever, has far greater glory.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 12, 'Since this new covenant gives us such confidence, we can be very bold.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 13, 'We are not like Moses, who put a veil over his face so the people of Israel would not see the glory fading away.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 14, 'But the people''s minds were hardened, and even to this day whenever the old covenant is being read, a veil covers their minds so they cannot understand the truth. And this veil can be removed only by believing in Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 15, 'Yes, even today when they read Moses'' writings, their hearts are covered with that veil, and they do not understand.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 16, 'But whenever anyone turns to the Lord, then the veil is taken away.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 17, 'Now, the Lord is the Spirit, and wherever the Spirit of the Lord is, he gives freedom.', 'NLT'),
(48, 3, 18, 'And all of us have had that veil removed so that we can be mirrors that brightly reflect the glory of the Lord. And as the Spirit of the Lord works within us, we become more and more like him and reflect his glory even more.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 1, 'And so, since God in his mercy has given us this wonderful ministry, we never give up.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 2, 'We reject all shameful and underhanded methods. We do not try to trick anyone, and we do not distort the word of God. We tell the truth before God, and all who are honest know that.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 3, 'If the Good News we preach is veiled from anyone, it is a sign that they are perishing.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 4, 'Satan, the god of this evil world, has blinded the minds of those who don''t believe, so they are unable to see the glorious light of the Good News that is shining upon them. They don''t understand the message we preach about the glory of Christ, who is the exact likeness of God.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 5, 'We don''t go around preaching about ourselves; we preach Christ Jesus, the Lord. All we say about ourselves is that we are your servants because of what Jesus has done for us.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 6, 'For God, who said, "Let there be light in the darkness," has made us understand that this light is the brightness of the glory of God that is seen in the face of Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 7, 'But this precious treasure--this light and power that now shine within us--is held in perishable containers, that is, in our weak bodies. So everyone can see that our glorious power is from God and is not our own.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 8, 'We are pressed on every side by troubles, but we are not crushed and broken. We are perplexed, but we don''t give up and quit.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 9, 'We are hunted down, but God never abandons us. We get knocked down, but we get up again and keep going.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 10, 'Through suffering, these bodies of ours constantly share in the death of Jesus so that the life of Jesus may also be seen in our bodies.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 11, 'Yes, we live under constant danger of death because we serve Jesus, so that the life of Jesus will be obvious in our dying bodies.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 12, 'So we live in the face of death, but it has resulted in eternal life for you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 13, 'But we continue to preach because we have the same kind of faith the psalmist had when he said, "I believed in God, and so I speak."', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 14, 'We know that the same God who raised our Lord Jesus will also raise us with Jesus and present us to himself along with you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 15, 'All of these things are for your benefit. And as God''s grace brings more and more people to Christ, there will be great thanksgiving, and God will receive more and more glory.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 16, 'That is why we never give up. Though our bodies are dying, our spirits are being renewed every day.', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 17, 'For our present troubles are quite small and won''t last very long. Yet they produce for us an immeasurably great glory that will last forever!', 'NLT'),
(48, 4, 18, 'So we don''t look at the troubles we can see right now; rather, we look forward to what we have not yet seen. For the troubles we see will soon be over, but the joys to come will last forever.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 1, 'For we know that when this earthly tent we live in is taken down--when we die and leave these bodies--we will have a home in heaven, an eternal body made for us by God himself and not by human hands.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 2, 'We grow weary in our present bodies, and we long for the day when we will put on our heavenly bodies like new clothing.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 3, 'For we will not be spirits without bodies, but we will put on new heavenly bodies.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 4, 'Our dying bodies make us groan and sigh, but it''s not that we want to die and have no bodies at all. We want to slip into our new bodies so that these dying bodies will be swallowed up by everlasting life.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 5, 'God himself has prepared us for this, and as a guarantee he has given us his Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 6, 'So we are always confident, even though we know that as long as we live in these bodies we are not at home with the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 7, 'That is why we live by believing and not by seeing.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 8, 'Yes, we are fully confident, and we would rather be away from these bodies, for then we will be at home with the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 9, 'So our aim is to please him always, whether we are here in this body or away from this body.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 10, 'For we must all stand before Christ to be judged. We will each receive whatever we deserve for the good or evil we have done in our bodies.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 11, 'It is because we know this solemn fear of the Lord that we work so hard to persuade others. God knows we are sincere, and I hope you know this, too.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 12, 'Are we trying to pat ourselves on the back again? No, we are giving you a reason to be proud of us, so you can answer those who brag about having a spectacular ministry rather than having a sincere heart before God.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 13, 'If it seems that we are crazy, it is to bring glory to God. And if we are in our right minds, it is for your benefit.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 14, 'Whatever we do, it is because Christ''s love controls us. Since we believe that Christ died for everyone, we also believe that we have all died to the old life we used to live.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 15, 'He died for everyone so that those who receive his new life will no longer live to please themselves. Instead, they will live to please Christ, who died and was raised for them.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 16, 'So we have stopped evaluating others by what the world thinks about them. Once I mistakenly thought of Christ that way, as though he were merely a human being. How differently I think about him now!', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 17, 'What this means is that those who become Christians become new persons. They are not the same anymore, for the old life is gone. A new life has begun!', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 18, 'All this newness of life is from God, who brought us back to himself through what Christ did. And God has given us the task of reconciling people to him.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 19, 'For God was in Christ, reconciling the world to himself, no longer counting people''s sins against them. This is the wonderful message he has given us to tell others.', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 20, 'We are Christ''s ambassadors, and God is using us to speak to you. We urge you, as though Christ himself were here pleading with you, "Be reconciled to God!"', 'NLT'),
(48, 5, 21, 'For God made Christ, who never sinned, to be the offering for our sin, so that we could be made right with God through Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 1, 'As God''s partners, we beg you not to reject this marvelous message of God''s great kindness.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 2, 'For God says, "At just the right time, I heard you. On the day of salvation, I helped you." Indeed, God is ready to help you right now. Today is the day of salvation.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 3, 'We try to live in such a way that no one will be hindered from finding the Lord by the way we act, and so no one can find fault with our ministry.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 4, 'In everything we do we try to show that we are true ministers of God. We patiently endure troubles and hardships and calamities of every kind.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 5, 'We have been beaten, been put in jail, faced angry mobs, worked to exhaustion, endured sleepless nights, and gone without food.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 6, 'We have proved ourselves by our purity, our understanding, our patience, our kindness, our sincere love, and the power of the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 7, 'We have faithfully preached the truth. God''s power has been working in us. We have righteousness as our weapon, both to attack and to defend ourselves.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 8, 'We serve God whether people honor us or despise us, whether they slander us or praise us. We are honest, but they call us impostors.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 9, 'We are well known, but we are treated as unknown. We live close to death, but here we are, still alive. We have been beaten within an inch of our lives.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 10, 'Our hearts ache, but we always have joy. We are poor, but we give spiritual riches to others. We own nothing, and yet we have everything.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 11, 'Oh, dear Corinthian friends! We have spoken honestly with you. Our hearts are open to you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 12, 'If there is a problem between us, it is not because of a lack of love on our part, but because you have withheld your love from us.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 13, 'I am talking now as I would to my own children. Open your hearts to us!', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 14, 'Don''t team up with those who are unbelievers. How can goodness be a partner with wickedness? How can light live with darkness?', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 15, 'What harmony can there be between Christ and the Devil? How can a believer be a partner with an unbeliever?', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 16, 'And what union can there be between God''s temple and idols? For we are the temple of the living God. As God said: "I will live in them and walk among them. I will be their God, and they will be my people.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 17, 'Therefore, come out from them and separate yourselves from them, says the Lord. Don''t touch their filthy things, and I will welcome you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 6, 18, 'And I will be your Father, and you will be my sons and daughters, says the Lord Almighty. "', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 1, 'Because we have these promises, dear friends, let us cleanse ourselves from everything that can defile our body or spirit. And let us work toward complete purity because we fear God.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 2, 'Please open your hearts to us. We have not done wrong to anyone. We have not led anyone astray. We have not taken advantage of anyone.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 3, 'I''m not saying this to condemn you, for I said before that you are in our hearts forever. We live or die together with you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 4, 'I have the highest confidence in you, and my pride in you is great. You have greatly encouraged me; you have made me happy despite all our troubles.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 5, 'When we arrived in Macedonia there was no rest for us. Outside there was conflict from every direction, and inside there was fear.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 6, 'But God, who encourages those who are discouraged, encouraged us by the arrival of Titus.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 7, 'His presence was a joy, but so was the news he brought of the encouragement he received from you. When he told me how much you were looking forward to my visit, and how sorry you were about what had happened, and how loyal your love is for me, I was filled with joy!', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 8, 'I am no longer sorry that I sent that letter to you, though I was sorry for a time, for I know that it was painful to you for a little while.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 9, 'Now I am glad I sent it, not because it hurt you, but because the pain caused you to have remorse and change your ways. It was the kind of sorrow God wants his people to have, so you were not harmed by us in any way.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 10, 'For God can use sorrow in our lives to help us turn away from sin and seek salvation. We will never regret that kind of sorrow. But sorrow without repentance is the kind that results in death.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 11, 'Just see what this godly sorrow produced in you! Such earnestness, such concern to clear yourselves, such indignation, such alarm, such longing to see me, such zeal, and such a readiness to punish the wrongdoer. You showed that you have done everything you could to make things right.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 12, 'My purpose was not to write about who did the wrong or who was wronged. I wrote to you so that in the sight of God you could show how much you really do care for us.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 13, 'We have been encouraged by this. In addition to our own encouragement, we were especially delighted to see how happy Titus was at the way you welcomed him and set his mind at ease.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 14, 'I had told him how proud I was of you--and you didn''t disappoint me. I have always told you the truth, and now my boasting to Titus has also proved true!', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 15, 'Now he cares for you more than ever when he remembers the way you listened to him and welcomed him with such respect and deep concern.', 'NLT'),
(48, 7, 16, 'I am very happy now because I have complete confidence in you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 1, 'Now I want to tell you, dear brothers and sisters, what God in his kindness has done for the churches in Macedonia.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 2, 'Though they have been going through much trouble and hard times, their wonderful joy and deep poverty have overflowed in rich generosity.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 3, 'For I can testify that they gave not only what they could afford but far more. And they did it of their own free will.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 4, 'They begged us again and again for the gracious privilege of sharing in the gift for the Christians in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 5, 'Best of all, they went beyond our highest hopes, for their first action was to dedicate themselves to the Lord and to us for whatever directions God might give them.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 6, 'So we have urged Titus, who encouraged your giving in the first place, to return to you and encourage you to complete your share in this ministry of giving.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 7, 'Since you excel in so many ways--you have so much faith, such gifted speakers, such knowledge, such enthusiasm, and such love for us--now I want you to excel also in this gracious ministry of giving.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 8, 'I am not saying you must do it, even though the other churches are eager to do it. This is one way to prove your love is real.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 9, 'You know how full of love and kindness our Lord Jesus Christ was. Though he was very rich, yet for your sakes he became poor, so that by his poverty he could make you rich.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 10, 'I suggest that you finish what you started a year ago, for you were the first to propose this idea, and you were the first to begin doing something about it.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 11, 'Now you should carry this project through to completion just as enthusiastically as you began it. Give whatever you can according to what you have.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 12, 'If you are really eager to give, it isn''t important how much you are able to give. God wants you to give what you have, not what you don''t have.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 13, 'Of course, I don''t mean you should give so much that you suffer from having too little. I only mean that there should be some equality.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 14, 'Right now you have plenty and can help them. Then at some other time they can share with you when you need it. In this way, everyone''s needs will be met.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 15, 'Do you remember what the Scriptures say about this? "Those who gathered a lot had nothing left over, and those who gathered only a little had enough."', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 16, 'I am thankful to God that he has given Titus the same enthusiasm for you that I have.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 17, 'He welcomed our request that he visit you again. In fact, he himself was eager to go and see you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 18, 'We are also sending another brother with Titus. He is highly praised in all the churches as a preacher of the Good News.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 19, 'He was appointed by the churches to accompany us as we take the offering to Jerusalem--a service that glorifies the Lord and shows our eagerness to help.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 20, 'By traveling together we will guard against any suspicion, for we are anxious that no one should find fault with the way we are handling this generous gift.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 21, 'We are careful to be honorable before the Lord, but we also want everyone else to know we are honorable.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 22, 'And we are also sending with them another brother who has been thoroughly tested and has shown how earnest he is on many occasions. He is now even more enthusiastic because of his increased confidence in you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 23, 'If anyone asks about Titus, say that he is my partner who works with me to help you. And these brothers are representatives of the churches. They are splendid examples of those who bring glory to Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 8, 24, 'So show them your love, and prove to all the churches that our boasting about you is justified.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 1, 'I really don''t need to write to you about this gift for the Christians in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 2, 'For I know how eager you are to help, and I have been boasting to our friends in Macedonia that you Christians in Greece were ready to send an offering a year ago. In fact, it was your enthusiasm that stirred up many of them to begin helping.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 3, 'But I am sending these brothers just to be sure that you really are ready, as I told them you would be, with your money all collected. I don''t want it to turn out that I was wrong in my boasting about you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 4, 'I would be humiliated--and so would you--if some Macedonian Christians came with me, only to find that you still weren''t ready after all I had told them!', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 5, 'So I thought I should send these brothers ahead of me to make sure the gift you promised is ready. But I want it to be a willing gift, not one given under pressure.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 6, 'Remember this--a farmer who plants only a few seeds will get a small crop. But the one who plants generously will get a generous crop.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 7, 'You must each make up your own mind as to how much you should give. Don''t give reluctantly or in response to pressure. For God loves the person who gives cheerfully.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 8, 'And God will generously provide all you need. Then you will always have everything you need and plenty left over to share with others.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 9, 'As the Scriptures say, "Godly people give generously to the poor. Their good deeds will never be forgotten."', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 10, 'For God is the one who gives seed to the farmer and then bread to eat. In the same way, he will give you many opportunities to do good, and he will produce a great harvest of generosity in you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 11, 'Yes, you will be enriched so that you can give even more generously. And when we take your gifts to those who need them, they will break out in thanksgiving to God.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 12, 'So two good things will happen--the needs of the Christians in Jerusalem will be met, and they will joyfully express their thanksgiving to God.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 13, 'You will be glorifying God through your generous gifts. For your generosity to them will prove that you are obedient to the Good News of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 14, 'And they will pray for you with deep affection because of the wonderful grace of God shown through you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 9, 15, 'Thank God for his Son--a gift too wonderful for words!', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 1, 'Now I, Paul, plead with you. I plead with the gentleness and kindness that Christ himself would use, even though some of you say I am bold in my letters but timid in person.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 2, 'I hope it won''t be necessary, but when I come I may have to be very bold with those who think we act from purely human motives.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 3, 'We are human, but we don''t wage war with human plans and methods.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 4, 'We use God''s mighty weapons, not mere worldly weapons, to knock down the Devil''s strongholds.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 5, 'With these weapons we break down every proud argument that keeps people from knowing God. With these weapons we conquer their rebellious ideas, and we teach them to obey Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 6, 'And we will punish those who remained disobedient after the rest of you became loyal and obedient.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 7, 'The trouble with you is that you make your decisions on the basis of appearance. You must recognize that we belong to Christ just as much as those who proudly declare that they belong to Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 8, 'I may seem to be boasting too much about the authority given to us by the Lord. But this authority is to build you up, not to tear you down. And I will not be put to shame by having my work among you destroyed.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 9, 'Now this is not just an attempt to frighten you by my letters.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 10, 'For some say, "Don''t worry about Paul. His letters are demanding and forceful, but in person he is weak, and his speeches are really bad!"', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 11, 'The ones who say this must realize that we will be just as demanding and forceful in person as we are in our letters.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 12, 'Oh, don''t worry; I wouldn''t dare say that I am as wonderful as these other men who tell you how important they are! But they are only comparing themselves with each other, and measuring themselves by themselves. What foolishness!', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 13, 'But we will not boast of authority we do not have. Our goal is to stay within the boundaries of God''s plan for us, and this plan includes our working there with you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 14, 'We are not going too far when we claim authority over you, for we were the first to travel all the way to you with the Good News of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 15, 'Nor do we claim credit for the work someone else has done. Instead, we hope that your faith will grow and that our work among you will be greatly enlarged.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 16, 'Then we will be able to go and preach the Good News in other places that are far beyond you, where no one else is working. Then there will be no question about being in someone else''s territory.', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 17, 'As the Scriptures say, "The person who wishes to boast should boast only of what the Lord has done."', 'NLT'),
(48, 10, 18, 'When people boast about themselves, it doesn''t count for much. But when the Lord commends someone, that''s different!', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 1, 'I hope you will be patient with me as I keep on talking like a fool. Please bear with me.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 2, 'I am jealous for you with the jealousy of God himself. For I promised you as a pure bride to one husband, Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 3, 'But I fear that somehow you will be led away from your pure and simple devotion to Christ, just as Eve was deceived by the serpent.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 4, 'You seem to believe whatever anyone tells you, even if they preach about a different Jesus than the one we preach, or a different Spirit than the one you received, or a different kind of gospel than the one you believed.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 5, 'But I don''t think I am inferior to these "super apostles."', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 6, 'I may not be a trained speaker, but I know what I am talking about. I think you realize this by now, for we have proved it again and again.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 7, 'Did I do wrong when I humbled myself and honored you by preaching God''s Good News to you without expecting anything in return?', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 8, 'I "robbed" other churches by accepting their contributions so I could serve you at no cost.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 9, 'And when I was with you and didn''t have enough to live on, I did not ask you to help me. For the brothers who came from Macedonia brought me another gift. I have never yet asked you for any support, and I never will.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 10, 'As surely as the truth of Christ is in me, I will never stop boasting about this all over Greece.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 11, 'Why? Because I don''t love you? God knows I do.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 12, 'But I will continue doing this to cut the ground out from under the feet of those who boast that their work is just like ours.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 13, 'These people are false apostles. They have fooled you by disguising themselves as apostles of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 14, 'But I am not surprised! Even Satan can disguise himself as an angel of light.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 15, 'So it is no wonder his servants can also do it by pretending to be godly ministers. In the end they will get every bit of punishment their wicked deeds deserve.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 16, 'Once again, don''t think that I have lost my wits to talk like this. But even if you do, listen to me, as you would to a foolish person, while I also boast a little.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 17, 'Such bragging is not something the Lord wants, but I am acting like a fool.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 18, 'And since others boast about their human achievements, I will, too.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 19, 'After all, you, who think you are so wise, enjoy listening to fools!', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 20, 'You put up with it when they make you their slaves, take everything you have, take advantage of you, put on airs, and slap you in the face.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 21, 'I''m ashamed to say that we were not strong enough to do that! But whatever they dare to boast about--I''m talking like a fool again--I can boast about it, too.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 22, 'They say they are Hebrews, do they? So am I. And they say they are Israelites? So am I. And they are descendants of Abraham? So am I.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 23, 'They say they serve Christ? I know I sound like a madman, but I have served him far more! I have worked harder, been put in jail more often, been whipped times without number, and faced death again and again.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 24, 'Five different times the Jews gave me thirty-nine lashes.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 25, 'Three times I was beaten with rods. Once I was stoned. Three times I was shipwrecked. Once I spent a whole night and a day adrift at sea.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 26, 'I have traveled many weary miles. I have faced danger from flooded rivers and from robbers. I have faced danger from my own people, the Jews, as well as from the Gentiles. I have faced danger in the cities, in the deserts, and on the stormy seas. And I have faced danger from men who claim to be Christians but are not.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 27, 'I have lived with weariness and pain and sleepless nights. Often I have been hungry and thirsty and have gone without food. Often I have shivered with cold, without enough clothing to keep me warm.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 28, 'Then, besides all this, I have the daily burden of how the churches are getting along.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 29, 'Who is weak without my feeling that weakness? Who is led astray, and I do not burn with anger?', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 30, 'If I must boast, I would rather boast about the things that show how weak I am.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 31, 'God, the Father of our Lord Jesus, who is to be praised forever, knows I tell the truth.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 32, 'When I was in Damascus, the governor under King Aretas kept guards at the city gates to catch me.', 'NLT'),
(48, 11, 33, 'But I was lowered in a basket through a window in the city wall, and that''s how I got away!', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 1, 'This boasting is all so foolish, but let me go on. Let me tell about the visions and revelations I received from the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 2, 'I was caught up into the third heaven fourteen years ago.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 3, 'Whether my body was there or just my spirit, I don''t know; only God knows.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 4, 'But I do know that I was caught up into paradise and heard things so astounding that they cannot be told.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 5, 'That experience is something worth boasting about, but I am not going to do it. I am going to boast only about my weaknesses.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 6, 'I have plenty to boast about and would be no fool in doing it, because I would be telling the truth. But I won''t do it. I don''t want anyone to think more highly of me than what they can actually see in my life and my message,', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 7, 'even though I have received wonderful revelations from God. But to keep me from getting puffed up, I was given a thorn in my flesh, a messenger from Satan to torment me and keep me from getting proud.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 8, 'Three different times I begged the Lord to take it away.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 9, 'Each time he said, "My gracious favor is all you need. My power works best in your weakness." So now I am glad to boast about my weaknesses, so that the power of Christ may work through me.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 10, 'Since I know it is all for Christ''s good, I am quite content with my weaknesses and with insults, hardships, persecutions, and calamities. For when I am weak, then I am strong.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 11, 'You have made me act like a fool--boasting like this. You ought to be writing commendations for me, for I am not at all inferior to these "super apostles," even though I am nothing at all.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 12, 'When I was with you, I certainly gave you every proof that I am truly an apostle, sent to you by God himself. For I patiently did many signs and wonders and miracles among you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 13, 'The only thing I didn''t do, which I do in the other churches, was to become a burden to you. Please forgive me for this wrong!', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 14, 'Now I am coming to you for the third time, and I will not be a burden to you. I don''t want what you have; I want you. And anyway, little children don''t pay for their parents'' food. It''s the other way around; parents supply food for their children.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 15, 'I will gladly spend myself and all I have for your spiritual good, even though it seems that the more I love you, the less you love me.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 16, 'Some of you admit I was not a burden to you. But they still think I was sneaky and took advantage of you by trickery.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 17, 'But how? Did any of the men I sent to you take advantage of you?', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 18, 'When I urged Titus to visit you and sent our other brother with him, did Titus take advantage of you? No, of course not! For we both have the same Spirit and walk in each other''s steps, doing things the same way.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 19, 'Perhaps you think we are saying all this just to defend ourselves. That isn''t it at all. We tell you this as Christ''s servants, and we know that God is listening. Everything we do, dear friends, is for your benefit.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 20, 'For I am afraid that when I come to visit you I won''t like what I find, and then you won''t like my response. I am afraid that I will find quarreling, jealousy, outbursts of anger, selfishness, backstabbing, gossip, conceit, and disorderly behavior.', 'NLT'),
(48, 12, 21, 'Yes, I am afraid that when I come, God will humble me again because of you. And I will have to grieve because many of you who sinned earlier have not repented of your impurity, sexual immorality, and eagerness for lustful pleasure.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 1, 'This is the third time I am coming to visit you. As the Scriptures say, "The facts of every case must be established by the testimony of two or three witnesses."', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 2, 'I have already warned those who had been sinning when I was there on my second visit. Now I again warn them and all others, just as I did before, that this next time I will not spare them.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 3, 'I will give you all the proof you want that Christ speaks through me. Christ is not weak in his dealings with you; he is a mighty power among you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 4, 'Although he died on the cross in weakness, he now lives by the mighty power of God. We, too, are weak, but we live in him and have God''s power--the power we use in dealing with you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 5, 'Examine yourselves to see if your faith is really genuine. Test yourselves. If you cannot tell that Jesus Christ is among you, it means you have failed the test.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 6, 'I hope you recognize that we have passed the test and are approved by God.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 7, 'We pray to God that you will not do anything wrong. We pray this, not to show that our ministry to you has been successful, but because we want you to do right even if we ourselves seem to have failed.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 8, 'Our responsibility is never to oppose the truth, but to stand for the truth at all times.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 9, 'We are glad to be weak, if you are really strong. What we pray for is your restoration to maturity.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 10, 'I am writing this to you before I come, hoping that I won''t need to deal harshly with you when I do come. For I want to use the authority the Lord has given me to build you up, not to tear you down.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 11, 'Dear brothers and sisters, I close my letter with these last words: Rejoice. Change your ways. Encourage each other. Live in harmony and peace. Then the God of love and peace will be with you.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 12, 'Greet each other in Christian love. All the Christians here send you their greetings.', 'NLT'),
(48, 13, 13, 'May the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, the love of God, and the fellowship of the Holy Spirit be with you all.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, an apostle. I was not appointed by any group or by human authority. My call is from Jesus Christ himself and from God the Father, who raised Jesus from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 2, 'All the brothers and sisters here join me in sending greetings to the churches of Galatia.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 3, 'May grace and peace be yours from God our Father and from the Lord Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 4, 'He died for our sins, just as God our Father planned, in order to rescue us from this evil world in which we live.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 5, 'That is why all glory belongs to God through all the ages of eternity. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 6, 'I am shocked that you are turning away so soon from God, who in his love and mercy called you to share the eternal life he gives through Christ. You are already following a different way', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 7, 'that pretends to be the Good News but is not the Good News at all. You are being fooled by those who twist and change the truth concerning Christ.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 8, 'Let God''s curse fall on anyone, including myself, who preaches any other message than the one we told you about. Even if an angel comes from heaven and preaches any other message, let him be forever cursed.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 9, 'I will say it again: If anyone preaches any other gospel than the one you welcomed, let God''s curse fall upon that person.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 10, 'Obviously, I''m not trying to be a people pleaser! No, I am trying to please God. If I were still trying to please people, I would not be Christ''s servant.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 11, 'Dear brothers and sisters, I solemnly assure you that the Good News of salvation which I preach is not based on mere human reasoning or logic.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 12, 'For my message came by a direct revelation from Jesus Christ himself. No one else taught me.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 13, 'You know what I was like when I followed the Jewish religion--how I violently persecuted the Christians. I did my best to get rid of them.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 14, 'I was one of the most religious Jews of my own age, and I tried as hard as possible to follow all the old traditions of my religion.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 15, 'But then something happened! For it pleased God in his kindness to choose me and call me, even before I was born! What undeserved mercy!', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 16, 'Then he revealed his Son to me so that I could proclaim the Good News about Jesus to the Gentiles. When all this happened to me, I did not rush out to consult with anyone else;', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 17, 'nor did I go up to Jerusalem to consult with those who were apostles before I was. No, I went away into Arabia and later returned to the city of Damascus.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 18, 'It was not until three years later that I finally went to Jerusalem for a visit with Peter and stayed there with him for fifteen days.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 19, 'And the only other apostle I met at that time was James, our Lord''s brother.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 20, 'You must believe what I am saying, for I declare before God that I am not lying.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 21, 'Then after this visit, I went north into the provinces of Syria and Cilicia.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 22, 'And still the Christians in the churches in Judea didn''t know me personally.', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 23, 'All they knew was that people were saying, "The one who used to persecute us now preaches the very faith he tried to destroy!"', 'NLT'),
(49, 1, 24, 'And they gave glory to God because of me.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 1, 'Then fourteen years later I went back to Jerusalem again, this time with Barnabas; and Titus came along, too.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 2, 'I went there because God revealed to me that I should go. While I was there I talked privately with the leaders of the church. I wanted them to understand what I had been preaching to the Gentiles. I wanted to make sure they did not disagree, or my ministry would have been useless.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 3, 'And they did agree. They did not even demand that my companion Titus be circumcised, though he was a Gentile.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 4, 'Even that question wouldn''t have come up except for some so-called Christians there--false ones, really--who came to spy on us and see our freedom in Christ Jesus. They wanted to force us, like slaves, to follow their Jewish regulations.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 5, 'But we refused to listen to them for a single moment. We wanted to preserve the truth of the Good News for you.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 6, 'And the leaders of the church who were there had nothing to add to what I was preaching. (By the way, their reputation as great leaders made no difference to me, for God has no favorites.)', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 7, 'They saw that God had given me the responsibility of preaching the Good News to the Gentiles, just as he had given Peter the responsibility of preaching to the Jews.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 8, 'For the same God who worked through Peter for the benefit of the Jews worked through me for the benefit of the Gentiles.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 9, 'In fact, James, Peter, and John, who were known as pillars of the church, recognized the gift God had given me, and they accepted Barnabas and me as their co-workers. They encouraged us to keep preaching to the Gentiles, while they continued their work with the Jews.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 10, 'The only thing they suggested was that we remember to help the poor, and I have certainly been eager to do that.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 11, 'But when Peter came to Antioch, I had to oppose him publicly, speaking strongly against what he was doing, for it was very wrong.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 12, 'When he first arrived, he ate with the Gentile Christians, who don''t bother with circumcision. But afterward, when some Jewish friends of James came, Peter wouldn''t eat with the Gentiles anymore because he was afraid of what these legalists would say.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 13, 'Then the other Jewish Christians followed Peter''s hypocrisy, and even Barnabas was influenced to join them in their hypocrisy.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 14, 'When I saw that they were not following the truth of the Good News, I said to Peter in front of all the others, "Since you, a Jew by birth, have discarded the Jewish laws and are living like a Gentile, why are you trying to make these Gentiles obey the Jewish laws you abandoned?', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 15, 'You and I are Jews by birth, not ''sinners'' like the Gentiles.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 16, 'And yet we Jewish Christians know that we become right with God, not by doing what the law commands, but by faith in Jesus Christ. So we have believed in Christ Jesus, that we might be accepted by God because of our faith in Christ--and not because we have obeyed the law. For no one will ever be saved by obeying the law."', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 17, 'But what if we seek to be made right with God through faith in Christ and then find out that we are still sinners? Has Christ led us into sin? Of course not!', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 18, 'Rather, I make myself guilty if I rebuild the old system I already tore down.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 19, 'For when I tried to keep the law, I realized I could never earn God''s approval. So I died to the law so that I might live for God. I have been crucified with Christ.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 20, 'I myself no longer live, but Christ lives in me. So I live my life in this earthly body by trusting in the Son of God, who loved me and gave himself for me.', 'NLT'),
(49, 2, 21, 'I am not one of those who treats the grace of God as meaningless. For if we could be saved by keeping the law, then there was no need for Christ to die.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 1, 'Oh, foolish Galatians! What magician has cast an evil spell on you? For you used to see the meaning of Jesus Christ''s death as clearly as though I had shown you a signboard with a picture of Christ dying on the cross.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 2, 'Let me ask you this one question: Did you receive the Holy Spirit by keeping the law? Of course not, for the Holy Spirit came upon you only after you believed the message you heard about Christ.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 3, 'Have you lost your senses? After starting your Christian lives in the Spirit, why are you now trying to become perfect by your own human effort?', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 4, 'You have suffered so much for the Good News. Surely it was not in vain, was it? Are you now going to just throw it all away?', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 5, 'I ask you again, does God give you the Holy Spirit and work miracles among you because you obey the law of Moses? Of course not! It is because you believe the message you heard about Christ.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 6, 'In the same way, "Abraham believed God, so God declared him righteous because of his faith."', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 7, 'The real children of Abraham, then, are all those who put their faith in God.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 8, 'What''s more, the Scriptures looked forward to this time when God would accept the Gentiles, too, on the basis of their faith. God promised this good news to Abraham long ago when he said, "All nations will be blessed through you."', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 9, 'And so it is: All who put their faith in Christ share the same blessing Abraham received because of his faith.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 10, 'But those who depend on the law to make them right with God are under his curse, for the Scriptures say, "Cursed is everyone who does not observe and obey all these commands that are written in God''s Book of the Law."', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 11, 'Consequently, it is clear that no one can ever be right with God by trying to keep the law. For the Scriptures say, "It is through faith that a righteous person has life."', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 12, 'How different from this way of faith is the way of law, which says, "If you wish to find life by obeying the law, you must obey all of its commands."', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 13, 'But Christ has rescued us from the curse pronounced by the law. When he was hung on the cross, he took upon himself the curse for our wrongdoing. For it is written in the Scriptures, "Cursed is everyone who is hung on a tree."', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 14, 'Through the work of Christ Jesus, God has blessed the Gentiles with the same blessing he promised to Abraham, and we Christians receive the promised Holy Spirit through faith.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 15, 'Dear brothers and sisters, here''s an example from everyday life. Just as no one can set aside or amend an irrevocable agreement, so it is in this case.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 16, 'God gave the promise to Abraham and his child. And notice that it doesn''t say the promise was to his children, as if it meant many descendants. But the promise was to his child--and that, of course, means Christ.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 17, 'This is what I am trying to say: The agreement God made with Abraham could not be canceled 430 years later when God gave the law to Moses. God would be breaking his promise.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 18, 'For if the inheritance could be received only by keeping the law, then it would not be the result of accepting God''s promise. But God gave it to Abraham as a promise.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 19, 'Well then, why was the law given? It was given to show people how guilty they are. But this system of law was to last only until the coming of the child to whom God''s promise was made. And there is this further difference. God gave his laws to angels to give to Moses, who was the mediator between God and the people.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 20, 'Now a mediator is needed if two people enter into an agreement, but God acted on his own when he made his promise to Abraham.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 21, 'Well then, is there a conflict between God''s law and God''s promises? Absolutely not! If the law could have given us new life, we could have been made right with God by obeying it.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 22, 'But the Scriptures have declared that we are all prisoners of sin, so the only way to receive God''s promise is to believe in Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 23, 'Until faith in Christ was shown to us as the way of becoming right with God, we were guarded by the law. We were kept in protective custody, so to speak, until we could put our faith in the coming Savior.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 24, 'Let me put it another way. The law was our guardian and teacher to lead us until Christ came. So now, through faith in Christ, we are made right with God.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 25, 'But now that faith in Christ has come, we no longer need the law as our guardian.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 26, 'So you are all children of God through faith in Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 27, 'And all who have been united with Christ in baptism have been made like him.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 28, 'There is no longer Jew or Gentile, slave or free, male or female. For you are all Christians--you are one in Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(49, 3, 29, 'And now that you belong to Christ, you are the true children of Abraham. You are his heirs, and now all the promises God gave to him belong to you.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 1, 'Think of it this way. If a father dies and leaves great wealth for his young children, those children are not much better off than slaves until they grow up, even though they actually own everything their father had.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 2, 'They have to obey their guardians until they reach whatever age their father set.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 3, 'And that''s the way it was with us before Christ came. We were slaves to the spiritual powers of this world.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 4, 'But when the right time came, God sent his Son, born of a woman, subject to the law.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 5, 'God sent him to buy freedom for us who were slaves to the law, so that he could adopt us as his very own children.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 6, 'And because you Gentiles have become his children, God has sent the Spirit of his Son into your hearts, and now you can call God your dear Father.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 7, 'Now you are no longer a slave but God''s own child. And since you are his child, everything he has belongs to you.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 8, 'Before you Gentiles knew God, you were slaves to so-called gods that do not even exist.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 9, 'And now that you have found God (or should I say, now that God has found you), why do you want to go back again and become slaves once more to the weak and useless spiritual powers of this world?', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 10, 'You are trying to find favor with God by what you do or don''t do on certain days or months or seasons or years.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 11, 'I fear for you. I am afraid that all my hard work for you was worth nothing.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 12, 'Dear brothers and sisters, I plead with you to live as I do in freedom from these things, for I have become like you Gentiles were--free from the law. You did not mistreat me when I first preached to you.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 13, 'Surely you remember that I was sick when I first brought you the Good News of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 14, 'But even though my sickness was revolting to you, you did not reject me and turn me away. No, you took me in and cared for me as though I were an angel from God or even Christ Jesus himself.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 15, 'Where is that joyful spirit we felt together then? In those days, I know you would gladly have taken out your own eyes and given them to me if it had been possible.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 16, 'Have I now become your enemy because I am telling you the truth?', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 17, 'Those false teachers who are so anxious to win your favor are not doing it for your good. They are trying to shut you off from me so that you will pay more attention to them.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 18, 'Now it''s wonderful if you are eager to do good, and especially when I am not with you.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 19, 'But oh, my dear children! I feel as if I am going through labor pains for you again, and they will continue until Christ is fully developed in your lives.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 20, 'How I wish I were there with you right now, so that I could be more gentle with you. But at this distance I frankly don''t know what else to do.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 21, 'Listen to me, you who want to live under the law. Do you know what the law really says?', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 22, 'The Scriptures say that Abraham had two sons, one from his slave-wife and one from his freeborn wife.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 23, 'The son of the slave-wife was born in a human attempt to bring about the fulfillment of God''s promise. But the son of the freeborn wife was born as God''s own fulfillment of his promise.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 24, 'Now these two women serve as an illustration of God''s two covenants. Hagar, the slave-wife, represents Mount Sinai where people first became enslaved to the law.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 25, 'And now Jerusalem is just like Mount Sinai in Arabia, because she and her children live in slavery.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 26, 'But Sarah, the free woman, represents the heavenly Jerusalem. And she is our mother.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 27, 'That is what Isaiah meant when he prophesied, "Rejoice, O childless woman! Break forth into loud and joyful song, even though you never gave birth to a child. For the woman who could bear no children now has more than all the other women!"', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 28, 'And you, dear brothers and sisters, are children of the promise, just like Isaac.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 29, 'And we who are born of the Holy Spirit are persecuted by those who want us to keep the law, just as Isaac, the child of promise, was persecuted by Ishmael, the son of the slave-wife.', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 30, 'But what do the Scriptures say about that? "Get rid of the slave and her son, for the son of the slave woman will not share the family inheritance with the free woman''s son."', 'NLT'),
(49, 4, 31, 'So, dear brothers and sisters, we are not children of the slave woman, obligated to the law. We are children of the free woman, acceptable to God because of our faith.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 1, 'So Christ has really set us free. Now make sure that you stay free, and don''t get tied up again in slavery to the law.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 2, 'Listen! I, Paul, tell you this: If you are counting on circumcision to make you right with God, then Christ cannot help you.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 3, 'I''ll say it again. If you are trying to find favor with God by being circumcised, you must obey all of the regulations in the whole law of Moses.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 4, 'For if you are trying to make yourselves right with God by keeping the law, you have been cut off from Christ! You have fallen away from God''s grace.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 5, 'But we who live by the Spirit eagerly wait to receive everything promised to us who are right with God through faith.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 6, 'For when we place our faith in Christ Jesus, it makes no difference to God whether we are circumcised or not circumcised. What is important is faith expressing itself in love.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 7, 'You were getting along so well. Who has interfered with you to hold you back from following the truth?', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 8, 'It certainly isn''t God, for he is the one who called you to freedom.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 9, 'But it takes only one wrong person among you to infect all the others--a little yeast spreads quickly through the whole batch of dough!', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 10, 'I am trusting the Lord to bring you back to believing as I do about these things. God will judge that person, whoever it is, who has been troubling and confusing you.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 11, 'Dear brothers and sisters, if I were still preaching that you must be circumcised--as some say I do--why would the Jews persecute me? The fact that I am still being persecuted proves that I am still preaching salvation through the cross of Christ alone.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 12, 'I only wish that those troublemakers who want to mutilate you by circumcision would mutilate themselves.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 13, 'For you have been called to live in freedom--not freedom to satisfy your sinful nature, but freedom to serve one another in love.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 14, 'For the whole law can be summed up in this one command: "Love your neighbor as yourself."', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 15, 'But if instead of showing love among yourselves you are always biting and devouring one another, watch out! Beware of destroying one another.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 16, 'So I advise you to live according to your new life in the Holy Spirit. Then you won''t be doing what your sinful nature craves.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 17, 'The old sinful nature loves to do evil, which is just opposite from what the Holy Spirit wants. And the Spirit gives us desires that are opposite from what the sinful nature desires. These two forces are constantly fighting each other, and your choices are never free from this conflict.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 18, 'But when you are directed by the Holy Spirit, you are no longer subject to the law.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 19, 'When you follow the desires of your sinful nature, your lives will produce these evil results: sexual immorality, impure thoughts, eagerness for lustful pleasure,', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 20, 'idolatry, participation in demonic activities, hostility, quarreling, jealousy, outbursts of anger, selfish ambition, divisions, the feeling that everyone is wrong except those in your own little group,', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 21, 'envy, drunkenness, wild parties, and other kinds of sin. Let me tell you again, as I have before, that anyone living that sort of life will not inherit the Kingdom of God.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 22, 'But when the Holy Spirit controls our lives, he will produce this kind of fruit in us: love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness,', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 23, 'gentleness, and self-control. Here there is no conflict with the law.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 24, 'Those who belong to Christ Jesus have nailed the passions and desires of their sinful nature to his cross and crucified them there.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 25, 'If we are living now by the Holy Spirit, let us follow the Holy Spirit''s leading in every part of our lives.', 'NLT'),
(49, 5, 26, 'Let us not become conceited, or irritate one another, or be jealous of one another.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 1, 'Dear brothers and sisters, if another Christian is overcome by some sin, you who are godly should gently and humbly help that person back onto the right path. And be careful not to fall into the same temptation yourself.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 2, 'Share each other''s troubles and problems, and in this way obey the law of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 3, 'If you think you are too important to help someone in need, you are only fooling yourself. You are really a nobody.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 4, 'Be sure to do what you should, for then you will enjoy the personal satisfaction of having done your work well, and you won''t need to compare yourself to anyone else.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 5, 'For we are each responsible for our own conduct.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 6, 'Those who are taught the word of God should help their teachers by paying them.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 7, 'Don''t be misled. Remember that you can''t ignore God and get away with it. You will always reap what you sow!', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 8, 'Those who live only to satisfy their own sinful desires will harvest the consequences of decay and death. But those who live to please the Spirit will harvest everlasting life from the Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 9, 'So don''t get tired of doing what is good. Don''t get discouraged and give up, for we will reap a harvest of blessing at the appropriate time.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 10, 'Whenever we have the opportunity, we should do good to everyone, especially to our Christian brothers and sisters.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 11, 'Notice what large letters I use as I write these closing words in my own handwriting.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 12, 'Those who are trying to force you to be circumcised are doing it for just one reason. They don''t want to be persecuted for teaching that the cross of Christ alone can save.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 13, 'And even those who advocate circumcision don''t really keep the whole law. They only want you to be circumcised so they can brag about it and claim you as their disciples.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 14, 'As for me, God forbid that I should boast about anything except the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ. Because of that cross, my interest in this world died long ago, and the world''s interest in me is also long dead.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 15, 'It doesn''t make any difference now whether we have been circumcised or not. What counts is whether we really have been changed into new and different people.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 16, 'May God''s mercy and peace be upon all those who live by this principle. They are the new people of God.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 17, 'From now on, don''t let anyone trouble me with these things. For I bear on my body the scars that show I belong to Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(49, 6, 18, 'My dear brothers and sisters, may the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, chosen by God to be an apostle of Christ Jesus. It is written to God''s holy people in Ephesus, who are faithful followers of Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 2, 'May grace and peace be yours, sent to you from God our Father and Jesus Christ our Lord.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 3, 'How we praise God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who has blessed us with every spiritual blessing in the heavenly realms because we belong to Christ.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 4, 'Long ago, even before he made the world, God loved us and chose us in Christ to be holy and without fault in his eyes.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 5, 'His unchanging plan has always been to adopt us into his own family by bringing us to himself through Jesus Christ. And this gave him great pleasure.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 6, 'So we praise God for the wonderful kindness he has poured out on us because we belong to his dearly loved Son.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 7, 'He is so rich in kindness that he purchased our freedom through the blood of his Son, and our sins are forgiven.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 8, 'He has showered his kindness on us, along with all wisdom and understanding.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 9, 'God''s secret plan has now been revealed to us; it is a plan centered on Christ, designed long ago according to his good pleasure.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 10, 'And this is his plan: At the right time he will bring everything together under the authority of Christ--everything in heaven and on earth.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 11, 'Furthermore, because of Christ, we have received an inheritance from God, for he chose us from the beginning, and all things happen just as he decided long ago.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 12, 'God''s purpose was that we who were the first to trust in Christ should praise our glorious God.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 13, 'And now you also have heard the truth, the Good News that God saves you. And when you believed in Christ, he identified you as his own by giving you the Holy Spirit, whom he promised long ago.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 14, 'The Spirit is God''s guarantee that he will give us everything he promised and that he has purchased us to be his own people. This is just one more reason for us to praise our glorious God.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 15, 'Ever since I first heard of your strong faith in the Lord Jesus and your love for Christians everywhere,', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 16, 'I have never stopped thanking God for you. I pray for you constantly,', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 17, 'asking God, the glorious Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, to give you spiritual wisdom and understanding, so that you might grow in your knowledge of God.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 18, 'I pray that your hearts will be flooded with light so that you can understand the wonderful future he has promised to those he called. I want you to realize what a rich and glorious inheritance he has given to his people.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 19, 'I pray that you will begin to understand the incredible greatness of his power for us who believe him. This is the same mighty power', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 20, 'that raised Christ from the dead and seated him in the place of honor at God''s right hand in the heavenly realms.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 21, 'Now he is far above any ruler or authority or power or leader or anything else in this world or in the world to come.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 22, 'And God has put all things under the authority of Christ, and he gave him this authority for the benefit of the church.', 'NLT'),
(50, 1, 23, 'And the church is his body; it is filled by Christ, who fills everything everywhere with his presence.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 1, 'Once you were dead, doomed forever because of your many sins.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 2, 'You used to live just like the rest of the world, full of sin, obeying Satan, the mighty prince of the power of the air. He is the spirit at work in the hearts of those who refuse to obey God.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 3, 'All of us used to live that way, following the passions and desires of our evil nature. We were born with an evil nature, and we were under God''s anger just like everyone else.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 4, 'But God is so rich in mercy, and he loved us so very much,', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 5, 'that even while we were dead because of our sins, he gave us life when he raised Christ from the dead. (It is only by God''s special favor that you have been saved!)', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 6, 'For he raised us from the dead along with Christ, and we are seated with him in the heavenly realms--all because we are one with Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 7, 'And so God can always point to us as examples of the incredible wealth of his favor and kindness toward us, as shown in all he has done for us through Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 8, 'God saved you by his special favor when you believed. And you can''t take credit for this; it is a gift from God.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 9, 'Salvation is not a reward for the good things we have done, so none of us can boast about it.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 10, 'For we are God''s masterpiece. He has created us anew in Christ Jesus, so that we can do the good things he planned for us long ago.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 11, 'Don''t forget that you Gentiles used to be outsiders by birth. You were called "the uncircumcised ones" by the Jews, who were proud of their circumcision, even though it affected only their bodies and not their hearts.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 12, 'In those days you were living apart from Christ. You were excluded from God''s people, Israel, and you did not know the promises God had made to them. You lived in this world without God and without hope.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 13, 'But now you belong to Christ Jesus. Though you once were far away from God, now you have been brought near to him because of the blood of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 14, 'For Christ himself has made peace between us Jews and you Gentiles by making us all one people. He has broken down the wall of hostility that used to separate us.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 15, 'By his death he ended the whole system of Jewish law that excluded the Gentiles. His purpose was to make peace between Jews and Gentiles by creating in himself one new person from the two groups.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 16, 'Together as one body, Christ reconciled both groups to God by means of his death, and our hostility toward each other was put to death.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 17, 'He has brought this Good News of peace to you Gentiles who were far away from him, and to us Jews who were near.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 18, 'Now all of us, both Jews and Gentiles, may come to the Father through the same Holy Spirit because of what Christ has done for us.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 19, 'So now you Gentiles are no longer strangers and foreigners. You are citizens along with all of God''s holy people. You are members of God''s family.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 20, 'We are his house, built on the foundation of the apostles and the prophets. And the cornerstone is Christ Jesus himself.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 21, 'We who believe are carefully joined together, becoming a holy temple for the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(50, 2, 22, 'Through him you Gentiles are also joined together as part of this dwelling where God lives by his Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 1, 'I, Paul, am a prisoner of Christ Jesus because of my preaching to you Gentiles.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 2, 'As you already know, God has given me this special ministry of announcing his favor to you Gentiles.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 3, 'As I briefly mentioned earlier in this letter, God himself revealed his secret plan to me.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 4, 'As you read what I have written, you will understand what I know about this plan regarding Christ.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 5, 'God did not reveal it to previous generations, but now he has revealed it by the Holy Spirit to his holy apostles and prophets.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 6, 'And this is the secret plan: The Gentiles have an equal share with the Jews in all the riches inherited by God''s children. Both groups have believed the Good News, and both are part of the same body and enjoy together the promise of blessings through Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 7, 'By God''s special favor and mighty power, I have been given the wonderful privilege of serving him by spreading this Good News.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 8, 'Just think! Though I did nothing to deserve it, and though I am the least deserving Christian there is, I was chosen for this special joy of telling the Gentiles about the endless treasures available to them in Christ.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 9, 'I was chosen to explain to everyone this plan that God, the Creator of all things, had kept secret from the beginning.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 10, 'God''s purpose was to show his wisdom in all its rich variety to all the rulers and authorities in the heavenly realms. They will see this when Jews and Gentiles are joined together in his church.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 11, 'This was his plan from all eternity, and it has now been carried out through Christ Jesus our Lord.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 12, 'Because of Christ and our faith in him, we can now come fearlessly into God''s presence, assured of his glad welcome.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 13, 'So please don''t despair because of what they are doing to me here. It is for you that I am suffering, so you should feel honored and encouraged.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 14, 'When I think of the wisdom and scope of God''s plan, I fall to my knees and pray to the Father,', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 15, 'the Creator of everything in heaven and on earth.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 16, 'I pray that from his glorious, unlimited resources he will give you mighty inner strength through his Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 17, 'And I pray that Christ will be more and more at home in your hearts as you trust in him. May your roots go down deep into the soil of God''s marvelous love.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 18, 'And may you have the power to understand, as all God''s people should, how wide, how long, how high, and how deep his love really is.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 19, 'May you experience the love of Christ, though it is so great you will never fully understand it. Then you will be filled with the fullness of life and power that comes from God.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 20, 'Now glory be to God! By his mighty power at work within us, he is able to accomplish infinitely more than we would ever dare to ask or hope.', 'NLT'),
(50, 3, 21, 'May he be given glory in the church and in Christ Jesus forever and ever through endless ages. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 1, 'Therefore I, a prisoner for serving the Lord, beg you to lead a life worthy of your calling, for you have been called by God.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 2, 'Be humble and gentle. Be patient with each other, making allowance for each other''s faults because of your love.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 3, 'Always keep yourselves united in the Holy Spirit, and bind yourselves together with peace.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 4, 'We are all one body, we have the same Spirit, and we have all been called to the same glorious future.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 5, 'There is only one Lord, one faith, one baptism,', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 6, 'and there is only one God and Father, who is over us all and in us all and living through us all.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 7, 'However, he has given each one of us a special gift according to the generosity of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 8, 'That is why the Scriptures say, "When he ascended to the heights, he led a crowd of captives and gave gifts to his people."', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 9, 'Notice that it says "he ascended." This means that Christ first came down to the lowly world in which we live.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 10, 'The same one who came down is the one who ascended higher than all the heavens, so that his rule might fill the entire universe.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 11, 'He is the one who gave these gifts to the church: the apostles, the prophets, the evangelists, and the pastors and teachers.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 12, 'Their responsibility is to equip God''s people to do his work and build up the church, the body of Christ,', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 13, 'until we come to such unity in our faith and knowledge of God''s Son that we will be mature and full grown in the Lord, measuring up to the full stature of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 14, 'Then we will no longer be like children, forever changing our minds about what we believe because someone has told us something different or because someone has cleverly lied to us and made the lie sound like the truth.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 15, 'Instead, we will hold to the truth in love, becoming more and more in every way like Christ, who is the head of his body, the church.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 16, 'Under his direction, the whole body is fitted together perfectly. As each part does its own special work, it helps the other parts grow, so that the whole body is healthy and growing and full of love.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 17, 'With the Lord''s authority let me say this: Live no longer as the ungodly do, for they are hopelessly confused.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 18, 'Their closed minds are full of darkness; they are far away from the life of God because they have shut their minds and hardened their hearts against him.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 19, 'They don''t care anymore about right and wrong, and they have given themselves over to immoral ways. Their lives are filled with all kinds of impurity and greed.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 20, 'But that isn''t what you were taught when you learned about Christ.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 21, 'Since you have heard all about him and have learned the truth that is in Jesus,', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 22, 'throw off your old evil nature and your former way of life, which is rotten through and through, full of lust and deception.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 23, 'Instead, there must be a spiritual renewal of your thoughts and attitudes.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 24, 'You must display a new nature because you are a new person, created in God''s likeness--righteous, holy, and true.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 25, 'So put away all falsehood and "tell your neighbor the truth" because we belong to each other.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 26, 'And "don''t sin by letting anger gain control over you." Don''t let the sun go down while you are still angry,', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 27, 'for anger gives a mighty foothold to the Devil.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 28, 'If you are a thief, stop stealing. Begin using your hands for honest work, and then give generously to others in need.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 29, 'Don''t use foul or abusive language. Let everything you say be good and helpful, so that your words will be an encouragement to those who hear them.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 30, 'And do not bring sorrow to God''s Holy Spirit by the way you live. Remember, he is the one who has identified you as his own, guaranteeing that you will be saved on the day of redemption.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 31, 'Get rid of all bitterness, rage, anger, harsh words, and slander, as well as all types of malicious behavior.', 'NLT'),
(50, 4, 32, 'Instead, be kind to each other, tenderhearted, forgiving one another, just as God through Christ has forgiven you.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 1, 'Follow God''s example in everything you do, because you are his dear children.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 2, 'Live a life filled with love for others, following the example of Christ, who loved you and gave himself as a sacrifice to take away your sins. And God was pleased, because that sacrifice was like sweet perfume to him.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 3, 'Let there be no sexual immorality, impurity, or greed among you. Such sins have no place among God''s people.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 4, 'Obscene stories, foolish talk, and coarse jokes--these are not for you. Instead, let there be thankfulness to God.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 5, 'You can be sure that no immoral, impure, or greedy person will inherit the Kingdom of Christ and of God. For a greedy person is really an idolater who worships the things of this world.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 6, 'Don''t be fooled by those who try to excuse these sins, for the terrible anger of God comes upon all those who disobey him.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 7, 'Don''t participate in the things these people do.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 8, 'For though your hearts were once full of darkness, now you are full of light from the Lord, and your behavior should show it!', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 9, 'For this light within you produces only what is good and right and true.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 10, 'Try to find out what is pleasing to the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 11, 'Take no part in the worthless deeds of evil and darkness; instead, rebuke and expose them.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 12, 'It is shameful even to talk about the things that ungodly people do in secret.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 13, 'But when the light shines on them, it becomes clear how evil these things are.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 14, 'And where your light shines, it will expose their evil deeds. This is why it is said, "Awake, O sleeper, rise up from the dead, and Christ will give you light."', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 15, 'So be careful how you live, not as fools but as those who are wise.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 16, 'Make the most of every opportunity for doing good in these evil days.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 17, 'Don''t act thoughtlessly, but try to understand what the Lord wants you to do.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 18, 'Don''t be drunk with wine, because that will ruin your life. Instead, let the Holy Spirit fill and control you.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 19, 'Then you will sing psalms and hymns and spiritual songs among yourselves, making music to the Lord in your hearts.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 20, 'And you will always give thanks for everything to God the Father in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 21, 'And further, you will submit to one another out of reverence for Christ.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 22, 'You wives will submit to your husbands as you do to the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 23, 'For a husband is the head of his wife as Christ is the head of his body, the church; he gave his life to be her Savior.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 24, 'As the church submits to Christ, so you wives must submit to your husbands in everything.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 25, 'And you husbands must love your wives with the same love Christ showed the church. He gave up his life for her', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 26, 'to make her holy and clean, washed by baptism and God''s word.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 27, 'He did this to present her to himself as a glorious church without a spot or wrinkle or any other blemish. Instead, she will be holy and without fault.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 28, 'In the same way, husbands ought to love their wives as they love their own bodies. For a man is actually loving himself when he loves his wife.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 29, 'No one hates his own body but lovingly cares for it, just as Christ cares for his body, which is the church.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 30, 'And we are his body.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 31, 'As the Scriptures say, "A man leaves his father and mother and is joined to his wife, and the two are united into one."', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 32, 'This is a great mystery, but it is an illustration of the way Christ and the church are one.', 'NLT'),
(50, 5, 33, 'So again I say, each man must love his wife as he loves himself, and the wife must respect her husband.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 1, 'Children, obey your parents because you belong to the Lord, for this is the right thing to do.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 2, '"Honor your father and mother." This is the first of the Ten Commandments that ends with a promise.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 3, 'And this is the promise: If you honor your father and mother, "you will live a long life, full of blessing."', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 4, 'And now a word to you fathers. Don''t make your children angry by the way you treat them. Rather, bring them up with the discipline and instruction approved by the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 5, 'Slaves, obey your earthly masters with deep respect and fear. Serve them sincerely as you would serve Christ.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 6, 'Work hard, but not just to please your masters when they are watching. As slaves of Christ, do the will of God with all your heart.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 7, 'Work with enthusiasm, as though you were working for the Lord rather than for people.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 8, 'Remember that the Lord will reward each one of us for the good we do, whether we are slaves or free.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 9, 'And in the same way, you masters must treat your slaves right. Don''t threaten them; remember, you both have the same Master in heaven, and he has no favorites.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 10, 'A final word: Be strong with the Lord''s mighty power.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 11, 'Put on all of God''s armor so that you will be able to stand firm against all strategies and tricks of the Devil.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 12, 'For we are not fighting against people made of flesh and blood, but against the evil rulers and authorities of the unseen world, against those mighty powers of darkness who rule this world, and against wicked spirits in the heavenly realms.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 13, 'Use every piece of God''s armor to resist the enemy in the time of evil, so that after the battle you will still be standing firm.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 14, 'Stand your ground, putting on the sturdy belt of truth and the body armor of God''s righteousness.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 15, 'For shoes, put on the peace that comes from the Good News, so that you will be fully prepared.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 16, 'In every battle you will need faith as your shield to stop the fiery arrows aimed at you by Satan.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 17, 'Put on salvation as your helmet, and take the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 18, 'Pray at all times and on every occasion in the power of the Holy Spirit. Stay alert and be persistent in your prayers for all Christians everywhere.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 19, 'And pray for me, too. Ask God to give me the right words as I boldly explain God''s secret plan that the Good News is for the Gentiles, too.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 20, 'I am in chains now for preaching this message as God''s ambassador. But pray that I will keep on speaking boldly for him, as I should.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 21, 'Tychicus, a much loved brother and faithful helper in the Lord''s work, will tell you all about how I am getting along.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 22, 'I am sending him to you for just this purpose. He will let you know how we are, and he will encourage you.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 23, 'May God give you peace, dear brothers and sisters, and love with faith, from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(50, 6, 24, 'May God''s grace be upon all who love our Lord Jesus Christ with an undying love.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul and Timothy, slaves of Christ Jesus. It is written to all of God''s people in Philippi, who believe in Christ Jesus, and to the elders and deacons.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 2, 'May God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ give you grace and peace.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 3, 'Every time I think of you, I give thanks to my God.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 4, 'I always pray for you, and I make my requests with a heart full of joy', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 5, 'because you have been my partners in spreading the Good News about Christ from the time you first heard it until now.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 6, 'And I am sure that God, who began the good work within you, will continue his work until it is finally finished on that day when Christ Jesus comes back again.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 7, 'It is right that I should feel as I do about all of you, for you have a very special place in my heart. We have shared together the blessings of God, both when I was in prison and when I was out, defending the truth and telling others the Good News.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 8, 'God knows how much I love you and long for you with the tender compassion of Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 9, 'I pray that your love for each other will overflow more and more, and that you will keep on growing in your knowledge and understanding.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 10, 'For I want you to understand what really matters, so that you may live pure and blameless lives until Christ returns.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 11, 'May you always be filled with the fruit of your salvation--those good things that are produced in your life by Jesus Christ--for this will bring much glory and praise to God.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 12, 'And I want you to know, dear brothers and sisters, that everything that has happened to me here has helped to spread the Good News.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 13, 'For everyone here, including all the soldiers in the palace guard, knows that I am in chains because of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 14, 'And because of my imprisonment, many of the Christians here have gained confidence and become more bold in telling others about Christ.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 15, 'Some are preaching out of jealousy and rivalry. But others preach about Christ with pure motives.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 16, 'They preach because they love me, for they know the Lord brought me here to defend the Good News.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 17, 'Those others do not have pure motives as they preach about Christ. They preach with selfish ambition, not sincerely, intending to make my chains more painful to me.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 18, 'But whether or not their motives are pure, the fact remains that the message about Christ is being preached, so I rejoice. And I will continue to rejoice.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 19, 'For I know that as you pray for me and as the Spirit of Jesus Christ helps me, this will all turn out for my deliverance.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 20, 'For I live in eager expectation and hope that I will never do anything that causes me shame, but that I will always be bold for Christ, as I have been in the past, and that my life will always honor Christ, whether I live or I die.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 21, 'For to me, living is for Christ, and dying is even better.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 22, 'Yet if I live, that means fruitful service for Christ. I really don''t know which is better.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 23, 'I''m torn between two desires: Sometimes I want to live, and sometimes I long to go and be with Christ. That would be far better for me,', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 24, 'but it is better for you that I live.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 25, 'I am convinced of this, so I will continue with you so that you will grow and experience the joy of your faith.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 26, 'Then when I return to you, you will have even more reason to boast about what Christ Jesus has done for me.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 27, 'But whatever happens to me, you must live in a manner worthy of the Good News about Christ, as citizens of heaven. Then, whether I come and see you again or only hear about you, I will know that you are standing side by side, fighting together for the Good News.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 28, 'Don''t be intimidated by your enemies. This will be a sign to them that they are going to be destroyed, but that you are going to be saved, even by God himself.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 29, 'For you have been given not only the privilege of trusting in Christ but also the privilege of suffering for him.', 'NLT'),
(51, 1, 30, 'We are in this fight together. You have seen me suffer for him in the past, and you know that I am still in the midst of this great struggle.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 1, 'Is there any encouragement from belonging to Christ? Any comfort from his love? Any fellowship together in the Spirit? Are your hearts tender and sympathetic?', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 2, 'Then make me truly happy by agreeing wholeheartedly with each other, loving one another, and working together with one heart and purpose.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 3, 'Don''t be selfish; don''t live to make a good impression on others. Be humble, thinking of others as better than yourself.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 4, 'Don''t think only about your own affairs, but be interested in others, too, and what they are doing.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 5, 'Your attitude should be the same that Christ Jesus had.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 6, 'Though he was God, he did not demand and cling to his rights as God.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 7, 'He made himself nothing; he took the humble position of a slave and appeared in human form.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 8, 'And in human form he obediently humbled himself even further by dying a criminal''s death on a cross.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 9, 'Because of this, God raised him up to the heights of heaven and gave him a name that is above every other name,', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 10, 'so that at the name of Jesus every knee will bow, in heaven and on earth and under the earth,', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 11, 'and every tongue will confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the glory of God the Father.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 12, 'Dearest friends, you were always so careful to follow my instructions when I was with you. And now that I am away you must be even more careful to put into action God''s saving work in your lives, obeying God with deep reverence and fear.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 13, 'For God is working in you, giving you the desire to obey him and the power to do what pleases him.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 14, 'In everything you do, stay away from complaining and arguing,', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 15, 'so that no one can speak a word of blame against you. You are to live clean, innocent lives as children of God in a dark world full of crooked and perverse people. Let your lives shine brightly before them.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 16, 'Hold tightly to the word of life, so that when Christ returns, I will be proud that I did not lose the race and that my work was not useless.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 17, 'But even if my life is to be poured out like a drink offering to complete the sacrifice of your faithful service (that is, if I am to die for you), I will rejoice, and I want to share my joy with all of you.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 18, 'And you should be happy about this and rejoice with me.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 19, 'If the Lord Jesus is willing, I hope to send Timothy to you soon. Then when he comes back, he can cheer me up by telling me how you are getting along.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 20, 'I have no one else like Timothy, who genuinely cares about your welfare.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 21, 'All the others care only for themselves and not for what matters to Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 22, 'But you know how Timothy has proved himself. Like a son with his father, he has helped me in preaching the Good News.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 23, 'I hope to send him to you just as soon as I find out what is going to happen to me here.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 24, 'And I have confidence from the Lord that I myself will come to see you soon.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 25, 'Meanwhile, I thought I should send Epaphroditus back to you. He is a true brother, a faithful worker, and a courageous soldier. And he was your messenger to help me in my need.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 26, 'Now I am sending him home again, for he has been longing to see you, and he was very distressed that you heard he was ill.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 27, 'And he surely was ill; in fact, he almost died. But God had mercy on him--and also on me, so that I would not have such unbearable sorrow.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 28, 'So I am all the more anxious to send him back to you, for I know you will be glad to see him, and that will lighten all my cares.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 29, 'Welcome him with Christian love and with great joy, and be sure to honor people like him.', 'NLT'),
(51, 2, 30, 'For he risked his life for the work of Christ, and he was at the point of death while trying to do for me the things you couldn''t do because you were far away.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 1, 'Whatever happens, dear brothers and sisters, may the Lord give you joy. I never get tired of telling you this. I am doing this for your own good.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 2, 'Watch out for those dogs, those wicked men and their evil deeds, those mutilators who say you must be circumcised to be saved.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 3, 'For we who worship God in the Spirit are the only ones who are truly circumcised. We put no confidence in human effort. Instead, we boast about what Christ Jesus has done for us.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 4, 'Yet I could have confidence in myself if anyone could. If others have reason for confidence in their own efforts, I have even more!', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 5, 'For I was circumcised when I was eight days old, having been born into a pure-blooded Jewish family that is a branch of the tribe of Benjamin. So I am a real Jew if there ever was one! What''s more, I was a member of the Pharisees, who demand the strictest obedience to the Jewish law.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 6, 'And zealous? Yes, in fact, I harshly persecuted the church. And I obeyed the Jewish law so carefully that I was never accused of any fault.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 7, 'I once thought all these things were so very important, but now I consider them worthless because of what Christ has done.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 8, 'Yes, everything else is worthless when compared with the priceless gain of knowing Christ Jesus my Lord. I have discarded everything else, counting it all as garbage, so that I may have Christ', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 9, 'and become one with him. I no longer count on my own goodness or my ability to obey God''s law, but I trust Christ to save me. For God''s way of making us right with himself depends on faith.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 10, 'As a result, I can really know Christ and experience the mighty power that raised him from the dead. I can learn what it means to suffer with him, sharing in his death,', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 11, 'so that, somehow, I can experience the resurrection from the dead!', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 12, 'I don''t mean to say that I have already achieved these things or that I have already reached perfection! But I keep working toward that day when I will finally be all that Christ Jesus saved me for and wants me to be.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 13, 'No, dear brothers and sisters, I am still not all I should be, but I am focusing all my energies on this one thing: Forgetting the past and looking forward to what lies ahead,', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 14, 'I strain to reach the end of the race and receive the prize for which God, through Christ Jesus, is calling us up to heaven.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 15, 'I hope all of you who are mature Christians will agree on these things. If you disagree on some point, I believe God will make it plain to you.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 16, 'But we must be sure to obey the truth we have learned already.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 17, 'Dear brothers and sisters, pattern your lives after mine, and learn from those who follow our example.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 18, 'For I have told you often before, and I say it again with tears in my eyes, that there are many whose conduct shows they are really enemies of the cross of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 19, 'Their future is eternal destruction. Their god is their appetite, they brag about shameful things, and all they think about is this life here on earth.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 20, 'But we are citizens of heaven, where the Lord Jesus Christ lives. And we are eagerly waiting for him to return as our Savior.', 'NLT'),
(51, 3, 21, 'He will take these weak mortal bodies of ours and change them into glorious bodies like his own, using the same mighty power that he will use to conquer everything, everywhere.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 1, 'Dear brothers and sisters, I love you and long to see you, for you are my joy and the reward for my work. So please stay true to the Lord, my dear friends.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 2, 'And now I want to plead with those two women, Euodia and Syntyche. Please, because you belong to the Lord, settle your disagreement.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 3, 'And I ask you, my true teammate, to help these women, for they worked hard with me in telling others the Good News. And they worked with Clement and the rest of my co-workers, whose names are written in the Book of Life.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 4, 'Always be full of joy in the Lord. I say it again--rejoice!', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 5, 'Let everyone see that you are considerate in all you do. Remember, the Lord is coming soon.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 6, 'Don''t worry about anything; instead, pray about everything. Tell God what you need, and thank him for all he has done.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 7, 'If you do this, you will experience God''s peace, which is far more wonderful than the human mind can understand. His peace will guard your hearts and minds as you live in Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 8, 'And now, dear brothers and sisters, let me say one more thing as I close this letter. Fix your thoughts on what is true and honorable and right. Think about things that are pure and lovely and admirable. Think about things that are excellent and worthy of praise.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 9, 'Keep putting into practice all you learned from me and heard from me and saw me doing, and the God of peace will be with you.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 10, 'How grateful I am, and how I praise the Lord that you are concerned about me again. I know you have always been concerned for me, but for a while you didn''t have the chance to help me.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 11, 'Not that I was ever in need, for I have learned how to get along happily whether I have much or little.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 12, 'I know how to live on almost nothing or with everything. I have learned the secret of living in every situation, whether it is with a full stomach or empty, with plenty or little.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 13, 'For I can do everything with the help of Christ who gives me the strength I need.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 14, 'But even so, you have done well to share with me in my present difficulty.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 15, 'As you know, you Philippians were the only ones who gave me financial help when I brought you the Good News and then traveled on from Macedonia. No other church did this.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 16, 'Even when I was in Thessalonica you sent help more than once.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 17, 'I don''t say this because I want a gift from you. What I want is for you to receive a well-earned reward because of your kindness.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 18, 'At the moment I have all I need--more than I need! I am generously supplied with the gifts you sent me with Epaphroditus. They are a sweet-smelling sacrifice that is acceptable to God and pleases him.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 19, 'And this same God who takes care of me will supply all your needs from his glorious riches, which have been given to us in Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 20, 'Now glory be to God our Father forever and ever. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 21, 'Give my greetings to all the Christians there. The brothers who are with me here send you their greetings.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 22, 'And all the other Christians send their greetings, too, especially those who work in Caesar''s palace.', 'NLT'),
(51, 4, 23, 'May the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, chosen by God to be an apostle of Christ Jesus, and from our brother Timothy.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 2, 'It is written to God''s holy people in the city of Colosse, who are faithful brothers and sisters in Christ. May God our Father give you grace and peace.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 3, 'We always pray for you, and we give thanks to God the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ,', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 4, 'for we have heard that you trust in Christ Jesus and that you love all of God''s people.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 5, 'You do this because you are looking forward to the joys of heaven--as you have been ever since you first heard the truth of the Good News.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 6, 'This same Good News that came to you is going out all over the world. It is changing lives everywhere, just as it changed yours that very first day you heard and understood the truth about God''s great kindness to sinners.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 7, 'Epaphras, our much loved co-worker, was the one who brought you the Good News. He is Christ''s faithful servant, and he is helping us in your place.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 8, 'He is the one who told us about the great love for others that the Holy Spirit has given you.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 9, 'So we have continued praying for you ever since we first heard about you. We ask God to give you a complete understanding of what he wants to do in your lives, and we ask him to make you wise with spiritual wisdom.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 10, 'Then the way you live will always honor and please the Lord, and you will continually do good, kind things for others. All the while, you will learn to know God better and better.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 11, 'We also pray that you will be strengthened with his glorious power so that you will have all the patience and endurance you need. May you be filled with joy,', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 12, 'always thanking the Father, who has enabled you to share the inheritance that belongs to God''s holy people, who live in the light.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 13, 'For he has rescued us from the one who rules in the kingdom of darkness, and he has brought us into the Kingdom of his dear Son.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 14, 'God has purchased our freedom with his blood and has forgiven all our sins.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 15, 'Christ is the visible image of the invisible God. He existed before God made anything at all and is supreme over all creation.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 16, 'Christ is the one through whom God created everything in heaven and earth. He made the things we can see and the things we can''t see--kings, kingdoms, rulers, and authorities. Everything has been created through him and for him.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 17, 'He existed before everything else began, and he holds all creation together.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 18, 'Christ is the head of the church, which is his body. He is the first of all who will rise from the dead, so he is first in everything.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 19, 'For God in all his fullness was pleased to live in Christ,', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 20, 'and by him God reconciled everything to himself. He made peace with everything in heaven and on earth by means of his blood on the cross.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 21, 'This includes you who were once so far away from God. You were his enemies, separated from him by your evil thoughts and actions,', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 22, 'yet now he has brought you back as his friends. He has done this through his death on the cross in his own human body. As a result, he has brought you into the very presence of God, and you are holy and blameless as you stand before him without a single fault.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 23, 'But you must continue to believe this truth and stand in it firmly. Don''t drift away from the assurance you received when you heard the Good News. The Good News has been preached all over the world, and I, Paul, have been appointed by God to proclaim it.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 24, 'I am glad when I suffer for you in my body, for I am completing what remains of Christ''s sufferings for his body, the church.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 25, 'God has given me the responsibility of serving his church by proclaiming his message in all its fullness to you Gentiles.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 26, 'This message was kept secret for centuries and generations past, but now it has been revealed to his own holy people.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 27, 'For it has pleased God to tell his people that the riches and glory of Christ are for you Gentiles, too. For this is the secret: Christ lives in you, and this is your assurance that you will share in his glory.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 28, 'So everywhere we go, we tell everyone about Christ. We warn them and teach them with all the wisdom God has given us, for we want to present them to God, perfect in their relationship to Christ.', 'NLT'),
(52, 1, 29, 'I work very hard at this, as I depend on Christ''s mighty power that works within me.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 1, 'I want you to know how much I have agonized for you and for the church at Laodicea, and for many other friends who have never known me personally.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 2, 'My goal is that they will be encouraged and knit together by strong ties of love. I want them to have full confidence because they have complete understanding of God''s secret plan, which is Christ himself.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 3, 'In him lie hidden all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 4, 'I am telling you this so that no one will be able to deceive you with persuasive arguments.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 5, 'For though I am far away from you, my heart is with you. And I am very happy because you are living as you should and because of your strong faith in Christ.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 6, 'And now, just as you accepted Christ Jesus as your Lord, you must continue to live in obedience to him.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 7, 'Let your roots grow down into him and draw up nourishment from him, so you will grow in faith, strong and vigorous in the truth you were taught. Let your lives overflow with thanksgiving for all he has done.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 8, 'Don''t let anyone lead you astray with empty philosophy and high-sounding nonsense that come from human thinking and from the evil powers of this world, and not from Christ.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 9, 'For in Christ the fullness of God lives in a human body,', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 10, 'and you are complete through your union with Christ. He is the Lord over every ruler and authority in the universe.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 11, 'When you came to Christ, you were "circumcised," but not by a physical procedure. It was a spiritual procedure--the cutting away of your sinful nature.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 12, 'For you were buried with Christ when you were baptized. And with him you were raised to a new life because you trusted the mighty power of God, who raised Christ from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 13, 'You were dead because of your sins and because your sinful nature was not yet cut away. Then God made you alive with Christ. He forgave all our sins.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 14, 'He canceled the record that contained the charges against us. He took it and destroyed it by nailing it to Christ''s cross.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 15, 'In this way, God disarmed the evil rulers and authorities. He shamed them publicly by his victory over them on the cross of Christ.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 16, 'So don''t let anyone condemn you for what you eat or drink, or for not celebrating certain holy days or new-moon ceremonies or Sabbaths.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 17, 'For these rules were only shadows of the real thing, Christ himself.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 18, 'Don''t let anyone condemn you by insisting on self-denial. And don''t let anyone say you must worship angels, even though they say they have had visions about this. These people claim to be so humble, but their sinful minds have made them proud.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 19, 'But they are not connected to Christ, the head of the body. For we are joined together in his body by his strong sinews, and we grow only as we get our nourishment and strength from God.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 20, 'You have died with Christ, and he has set you free from the evil powers of this world. So why do you keep on following rules of the world, such as,', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 21, '"Don''t handle, don''t eat, don''t touch."', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 22, 'Such rules are mere human teaching about things that are gone as soon as we use them.', 'NLT'),
(52, 2, 23, 'These rules may seem wise because they require strong devotion, humility, and severe bodily discipline. But they have no effect when it comes to conquering a person''s evil thoughts and desires.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 1, 'Since you have been raised to new life with Christ, set your sights on the realities of heaven, where Christ sits at God''s right hand in the place of honor and power.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 2, 'Let heaven fill your thoughts. Do not think only about things down here on earth.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 3, 'For you died when Christ died, and your real life is hidden with Christ in God.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 4, 'And when Christ, who is your real life, is revealed to the whole world, you will share in all his glory.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 5, 'So put to death the sinful, earthly things lurking within you. Have nothing to do with sexual sin, impurity, lust, and shameful desires. Don''t be greedy for the good things of this life, for that is idolatry.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 6, 'God''s terrible anger will come upon those who do such things.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 7, 'You used to do them when your life was still part of this world.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 8, 'But now is the time to get rid of anger, rage, malicious behavior, slander, and dirty language.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 9, 'Don''t lie to each other, for you have stripped off your old evil nature and all its wicked deeds.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 10, 'In its place you have clothed yourselves with a brand-new nature that is continually being renewed as you learn more and more about Christ, who created this new nature within you.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 11, 'In this new life, it doesn''t matter if you are a Jew or a Gentile, circumcised or uncircumcised, barbaric, uncivilized, slave, or free. Christ is all that matters, and he lives in all of us.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 12, 'Since God chose you to be the holy people whom he loves, you must clothe yourselves with tenderhearted mercy, kindness, humility, gentleness, and patience.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 13, 'You must make allowance for each other''s faults and forgive the person who offends you. Remember, the Lord forgave you, so you must forgive others.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 14, 'And the most important piece of clothing you must wear is love. Love is what binds us all together in perfect harmony.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 15, 'And let the peace that comes from Christ rule in your hearts. For as members of one body you are all called to live in peace. And always be thankful.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 16, 'Let the words of Christ, in all their richness, live in your hearts and make you wise. Use his words to teach and counsel each other. Sing psalms and hymns and spiritual songs to God with thankful hearts.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 17, 'And whatever you do or say, let it be as a representative of the Lord Jesus, all the while giving thanks through him to God the Father.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 18, 'You wives must submit to your husbands, as is fitting for those who belong to the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 19, 'And you husbands must love your wives and never treat them harshly.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 20, 'You children must always obey your parents, for this is what pleases the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 21, 'Fathers, don''t aggravate your children. If you do, they will become discouraged and quit trying.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 22, 'You slaves must obey your earthly masters in everything you do. Try to please them all the time, not just when they are watching you. Obey them willingly because of your reverent fear of the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 23, 'Work hard and cheerfully at whatever you do, as though you were working for the Lord rather than for people.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 24, 'Remember that the Lord will give you an inheritance as your reward, and the Master you are serving is Christ.', 'NLT'),
(52, 3, 25, 'But if you do what is wrong, you will be paid back for the wrong you have done. For God has no favorites who can get away with evil.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 1, 'You slave owners must be just and fair to your slaves. Remember that you also have a Master--in heaven.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 2, 'Devote yourselves to prayer with an alert mind and a thankful heart.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 3, 'Don''t forget to pray for us, too, that God will give us many opportunities to preach about his secret plan--that Christ is also for you Gentiles. That is why I am here in chains.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 4, 'Pray that I will proclaim this message as clearly as I should.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 5, 'Live wisely among those who are not Christians, and make the most of every opportunity.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 6, 'Let your conversation be gracious and effective so that you will have the right answer for everyone.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 7, 'Tychicus, a much loved brother, will tell you how I am getting along. He is a faithful helper who serves the Lord with me.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 8, 'I have sent him on this special trip to let you know how we are doing and to encourage you.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 9, 'I am also sending Onesimus, a faithful and much loved brother, one of your own people. He and Tychicus will give you all the latest news.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 10, 'Aristarchus, who is in prison with me, sends you his greetings, and so does Mark, Barnabas''s cousin. And as you were instructed before, make Mark welcome if he comes your way.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 11, 'Jesus (the one we call Justus) also sends his greetings. These are the only Jewish Christians among my co-workers; they are working with me here for the Kingdom of God. And what a comfort they have been!', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 12, 'Epaphras, from your city, a servant of Christ Jesus, sends you his greetings. He always prays earnestly for you, asking God to make you strong and perfect, fully confident of the whole will of God.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 13, 'I can assure you that he has agonized for you and also for the Christians in Laodicea and Hierapolis.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 14, 'Dear Doctor Luke sends his greetings, and so does Demas.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 15, 'Please give my greetings to our Christian brothers and sisters at Laodicea, and to Nympha and those who meet in her house.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 16, 'After you have read this letter, pass it on to the church at Laodicea so they can read it, too. And you should read the letter I wrote to them.', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 17, 'And say to Archippus, "Be sure to carry out the work the Lord gave you."', 'NLT'),
(52, 4, 18, 'Here is my greeting in my own handwriting--PAUL. Remember my chains. May the grace of God be with you.', 'NLT'),
(53, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, Silas, and Timothy. It is written to the church in Thessalonica, you who belong to God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. May his grace and peace be yours.', 'NLT'),
(53, 1, 2, 'We always thank God for all of you and pray for you constantly.', 'NLT'),
(53, 1, 3, 'As we talk to our God and Father about you, we think of your faithful work, your loving deeds, and your continual anticipation of the return of our Lord Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(53, 1, 4, 'We know that God loves you, dear brothers and sisters, and that he chose you to be his own people.', 'NLT'),
(53, 1, 5, 'For when we brought you the Good News, it was not only with words but also with power, for the Holy Spirit gave you full assurance that what we said was true. And you know that the way we lived among you was further proof of the truth of our message.', 'NLT'),
(53, 1, 6, 'So you received the message with joy from the Holy Spirit in spite of the severe suffering it brought you. In this way, you imitated both us and the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(53, 1, 7, 'As a result, you yourselves became an example to all the Christians in Greece.', 'NLT'),
(53, 1, 8, 'And now the word of the Lord is ringing out from you to people everywhere, even beyond Greece, for wherever we go we find people telling us about your faith in God. We don''t need to tell them about it,', 'NLT'),
(53, 1, 9, 'for they themselves keep talking about the wonderful welcome you gave us and how you turned away from idols to serve the true and living God.', 'NLT'),
(53, 1, 10, 'And they speak of how you are looking forward to the coming of God''s Son from heaven--Jesus, whom God raised from the dead. He is the one who has rescued us from the terrors of the coming judgment.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 1, 'You yourselves know, dear brothers and sisters, that our visit to you was not a failure.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 2, 'You know how badly we had been treated at Philippi just before we came to you and how much we suffered there. Yet our God gave us the courage to declare his Good News to you boldly, even though we were surrounded by many who opposed us.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 3, 'So you can see that we were not preaching with any deceit or impure purposes or trickery.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 4, 'For we speak as messengers who have been approved by God to be entrusted with the Good News. Our purpose is to please God, not people. He is the one who examines the motives of our hearts.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 5, 'Never once did we try to win you with flattery, as you very well know. And God is our witness that we were not just pretending to be your friends so you would give us money!', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 6, 'As for praise, we have never asked for it from you or anyone else.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 7, 'As apostles of Christ we certainly had a right to make some demands of you, but we were as gentle among you as a mother feeding and caring for her own children.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 8, 'We loved you so much that we gave you not only God''s Good News but our own lives, too.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 9, 'Don''t you remember, dear brothers and sisters, how hard we worked among you? Night and day we toiled to earn a living so that our expenses would not be a burden to anyone there as we preached God''s Good News among you.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 10, 'You yourselves are our witnesses--and so is God--that we were pure and honest and faultless toward all of you believers.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 11, 'And you know that we treated each of you as a father treats his own children.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 12, 'We pleaded with you, encouraged you, and urged you to live your lives in a way that God would consider worthy. For he called you into his Kingdom to share his glory.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 13, 'And we will never stop thanking God that when we preached his message to you, you didn''t think of the words we spoke as being just our own. You accepted what we said as the very word of God--which, of course, it was. And this word continues to work in you who believe.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 14, 'And then, dear brothers and sisters, you suffered persecution from your own countrymen. In this way, you imitated the believers in God''s churches in Judea who, because of their belief in Christ Jesus, suffered from their own people, the Jews.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 15, 'For some of the Jews had killed their own prophets, and some even killed the Lord Jesus. Now they have persecuted us and driven us out. They displease God and oppose everyone', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 16, 'by trying to keep us from preaching the Good News to the Gentiles, for fear some might be saved. By doing this, they continue to pile up their sins. But the anger of God has caught up with them at last.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 17, 'Dear brothers and sisters, after we were separated from you for a little while (though our hearts never left you), we tried very hard to come back because of our intense longing to see you again.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 18, 'We wanted very much to come, and I, Paul, tried again and again, but Satan prevented us.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 19, 'After all, what gives us hope and joy, and what is our proud reward and crown? It is you! Yes, you will bring us much joy as we stand together before our Lord Jesus when he comes back again.', 'NLT'),
(53, 2, 20, 'For you are our pride and joy.', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 1, 'Finally, when we could stand it no longer, we decided that I should stay alone in Athens,', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 2, 'and we sent Timothy to visit you. He is our co-worker for God and our brother in proclaiming the Good News of Christ. We sent him to strengthen you, to encourage you in your faith,', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 3, 'and to keep you from becoming disturbed by the troubles you were going through. But, of course, you know that such troubles are going to happen to us Christians.', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 4, 'Even while we were with you, we warned you that troubles would soon come--and they did, as you well know.', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 5, 'That is why, when I could bear it no longer, I sent Timothy to find out whether your faith was still strong. I was afraid that the Tempter had gotten the best of you and that all our work had been useless.', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 6, 'Now Timothy has just returned, bringing the good news that your faith and love are as strong as ever. He reports that you remember our visit with joy and that you want to see us just as much as we want to see you.', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 7, 'So we have been greatly comforted, dear brothers and sisters, in all of our own crushing troubles and suffering, because you have remained strong in your faith.', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 8, 'It gives us new life, knowing you remain strong in the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 9, 'How we thank God for you! Because of you we have great joy in the presence of God.', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 10, 'Night and day we pray earnestly for you, asking God to let us see you again to fill up anything that may still be missing in your faith.', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 11, 'May God himself, our Father, and our Lord Jesus make it possible for us to come to you very soon.', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 12, 'And may the Lord make your love grow and overflow to each other and to everyone else, just as our love overflows toward you.', 'NLT'),
(53, 3, 13, 'As a result, Christ will make your hearts strong, blameless, and holy when you stand before God our Father on that day when our Lord Jesus comes with all those who belong to him.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 1, 'Finally, dear brothers and sisters, we urge you in the name of the Lord Jesus to live in a way that pleases God, as we have taught you. You are doing this already, and we encourage you to do so more and more.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 2, 'For you remember what we taught you in the name of the Lord Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 3, 'God wants you to be holy, so you should keep clear of all sexual sin.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 4, 'Then each of you will control your body and live in holiness and honor--', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 5, 'not in lustful passion as the pagans do, in their ignorance of God and his ways.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 6, 'Never cheat a Christian brother in this matter by taking his wife, for the Lord avenges all such sins, as we have solemnly warned you before.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 7, 'God has called us to be holy, not to live impure lives.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 8, 'Anyone who refuses to live by these rules is not disobeying human rules but is rejecting God, who gives his Holy Spirit to you.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 9, 'But I don''t need to write to you about the Christian love that should be shown among God''s people. For God himself has taught you to love one another.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 10, 'Indeed, your love is already strong toward all the Christians in all of Macedonia. Even so, dear brothers and sisters, we beg you to love them more and more.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 11, 'This should be your ambition: to live a quiet life, minding your own business and working with your hands, just as we commanded you before.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 12, 'As a result, people who are not Christians will respect the way you live, and you will not need to depend on others to meet your financial needs.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 13, 'And now, brothers and sisters, I want you to know what will happen to the Christians who have died so you will not be full of sorrow like people who have no hope.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 14, 'For since we believe that Jesus died and was raised to life again, we also believe that when Jesus comes, God will bring back with Jesus all the Christians who have died.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 15, 'I can tell you this directly from the Lord: We who are still living when the Lord returns will not rise to meet him ahead of those who are in their graves.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 16, 'For the Lord himself will come down from heaven with a commanding shout, with the call of the archangel, and with the trumpet call of God. First, all the Christians who have died will rise from their graves.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 17, 'Then, together with them, we who are still alive and remain on the earth will be caught up in the clouds to meet the Lord in the air and remain with him forever.', 'NLT'),
(53, 4, 18, 'So comfort and encourage each other with these words.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 1, 'I really don''t need to write to you about how and when all this will happen, dear brothers and sisters.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 2, 'For you know quite well that the day of the Lord will come unexpectedly, like a thief in the night.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 3, 'When people are saying, "All is well; everything is peaceful and secure," then disaster will fall upon them as suddenly as a woman''s birth pains begin when her child is about to be born. And there will be no escape.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 4, 'But you aren''t in the dark about these things, dear brothers and sisters, and you won''t be surprised when the day of the Lord comes like a thief.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 5, 'For you are all children of the light and of the day; we don''t belong to darkness and night.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 6, 'So be on your guard, not asleep like the others. Stay alert and be sober.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 7, 'Night is the time for sleep and the time when people get drunk.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 8, 'But let us who live in the light think clearly, protected by the body armor of faith and love, and wearing as our helmet the confidence of our salvation.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 9, 'For God decided to save us through our Lord Jesus Christ, not to pour out his anger on us.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 10, 'He died for us so that we can live with him forever, whether we are dead or alive at the time of his return.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 11, 'So encourage each other and build each other up, just as you are already doing.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 12, 'Dear brothers and sisters, honor those who are your leaders in the Lord''s work. They work hard among you and warn you against all that is wrong.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 13, 'Think highly of them and give them your wholehearted love because of their work. And remember to live peaceably with each other.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 14, 'Brothers and sisters, we urge you to warn those who are lazy. Encourage those who are timid. Take tender care of those who are weak. Be patient with everyone.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 15, 'See that no one pays back evil for evil, but always try to do good to each other and to everyone else.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 16, 'Always be joyful.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 17, 'Keep on praying.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 18, 'No matter what happens, always be thankful, for this is God''s will for you who belong to Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 19, 'Do not stifle the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 20, 'Do not scoff at prophecies,', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 21, 'but test everything that is said. Hold on to what is good.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 22, 'Keep away from every kind of evil.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 23, 'Now may the God of peace make you holy in every way, and may your whole spirit and soul and body be kept blameless until that day when our Lord Jesus Christ comes again.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 24, 'God, who calls you, is faithful; he will do this.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 25, 'Dear brothers and sisters, pray for us.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 26, 'Greet all the brothers and sisters in Christian love.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 27, 'I command you in the name of the Lord to read this letter to all the brothers and sisters.', 'NLT'),
(53, 5, 28, 'And may the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with all of you.', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, Silas, and Timothy. It is written to the church in Thessalonica, you who belong to God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 2, 'May God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ give you grace and peace.', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 3, 'Dear brothers and sisters, we always thank God for you, as is right, for we are thankful that your faith is flourishing and you are all growing in love for each other.', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 4, 'We proudly tell God''s other churches about your endurance and faithfulness in all the persecutions and hardships you are suffering.', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 5, 'But God will use this persecution to show his justice. For he will make you worthy of his Kingdom, for which you are suffering,', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 6, 'and in his justice he will punish those who persecute you.', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 7, 'And God will provide rest for you who are being persecuted and also for us when the Lord Jesus appears from heaven. He will come with his mighty angels,', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 8, 'in flaming fire, bringing judgment on those who don''t know God and on those who refuse to obey the Good News of our Lord Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 9, 'They will be punished with everlasting destruction, forever separated from the Lord and from his glorious power', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 10, 'when he comes to receive glory and praise from his holy people. And you will be among those praising him on that day, for you believed what we testified about him.', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 11, 'And so we keep on praying for you, that our God will make you worthy of the life to which he called you. And we pray that God, by his power, will fulfill all your good intentions and faithful deeds.', 'NLT'),
(54, 1, 12, 'Then everyone will give honor to the name of our Lord Jesus because of you, and you will be honored along with him. This is all made possible because of the undeserved favor of our God and Lord, Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 1, 'And now, brothers and sisters, let us tell you about the coming again of our Lord Jesus Christ and how we will be gathered together to meet him.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 2, 'Please don''t be so easily shaken and troubled by those who say that the day of the Lord has already begun. Even if they claim to have had a vision, a revelation, or a letter supposedly from us, don''t believe them.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 3, 'Don''t be fooled by what they say. For that day will not come until there is a great rebellion against God and the man of lawlessness is revealed--the one who brings destruction.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 4, 'He will exalt himself and defy every god there is and tear down every object of adoration and worship. He will position himself in the temple of God, claiming that he himself is God.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 5, 'Don''t you remember that I told you this when I was with you?', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 6, 'And you know what is holding him back, for he can be revealed only when his time comes.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 7, 'For this lawlessness is already at work secretly, and it will remain secret until the one who is holding it back steps out of the way.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 8, 'Then the man of lawlessness will be revealed, whom the Lord Jesus will consume with the breath of his mouth and destroy by the splendor of his coming.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 9, 'This evil man will come to do the work of Satan with counterfeit power and signs and miracles.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 10, 'He will use every kind of wicked deception to fool those who are on their way to destruction because they refuse to believe the truth that would save them.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 11, 'So God will send great deception upon them, and they will believe all these lies.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 12, 'Then they will be condemned for not believing the truth and for enjoying the evil they do.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 13, 'As for us, we always thank God for you, dear brothers and sisters loved by the Lord. We are thankful that God chose you to be among the first to experience salvation, a salvation that came through the Spirit who makes you holy and by your belief in the truth.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 14, 'He called you to salvation when we told you the Good News; now you can share in the glory of our Lord Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 15, 'With all these things in mind, dear brothers and sisters, stand firm and keep a strong grip on everything we taught you both in person and by letter.', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 16, 'May our Lord Jesus Christ and God our Father, who loved us and in his special favor gave us everlasting comfort and good hope,', 'NLT'),
(54, 2, 17, 'comfort your hearts and give you strength in every good thing you do and say.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 1, 'Finally, dear brothers and sisters, I ask you to pray for us. Pray first that the Lord''s message will spread rapidly and be honored wherever it goes, just as when it came to you.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 2, 'Pray, too, that we will be saved from wicked and evil people, for not everyone believes in the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 3, 'But the Lord is faithful; he will make you strong and guard you from the evil one.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 4, 'And we are confident in the Lord that you are practicing the things we commanded you, and that you always will.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 5, 'May the Lord bring you into an ever deeper understanding of the love of God and the endurance that comes from Christ.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 6, 'And now, dear brothers and sisters, we give you this command with the authority of our Lord Jesus Christ: Stay away from any Christian who lives in idleness and doesn''t follow the tradition of hard work we gave you.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 7, 'For you know that you ought to follow our example. We were never lazy when we were with you.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 8, 'We never accepted food from anyone without paying for it. We worked hard day and night so that we would not be a burden to any of you.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 9, 'It wasn''t that we didn''t have the right to ask you to feed us, but we wanted to give you an example to follow.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 10, 'Even while we were with you, we gave you this rule: "Whoever does not work should not eat."', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 11, 'Yet we hear that some of you are living idle lives, refusing to work and wasting time meddling in other people''s business.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 12, 'In the name of the Lord Jesus Christ, we appeal to such people--no, we command them: Settle down and get to work. Earn your own living.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 13, 'And I say to the rest of you, dear brothers and sisters, never get tired of doing good.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 14, 'Take note of those who refuse to obey what we say in this letter. Stay away from them so they will be ashamed.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 15, 'Don''t think of them as enemies, but speak to them as you would to a Christian who needs to be warned.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 16, 'May the Lord of peace himself always give you his peace no matter what happens. The Lord be with you all.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 17, 'Now here is my greeting, which I write with my own hand--PAUL. I do this at the end of all my letters to prove that they really are from me.', 'NLT'),
(54, 3, 18, 'May the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus, appointed by the command of God our Savior and by Christ Jesus our hope.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 2, 'It is written to Timothy, my true child in the faith. May God our Father and Christ Jesus our Lord give you grace, mercy, and peace.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 3, 'When I left for Macedonia, I urged you to stay there in Ephesus and stop those who are teaching wrong doctrine.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 4, 'Don''t let people waste time in endless speculation over myths and spiritual pedigrees. For these things only cause arguments; they don''t help people live a life of faith in God.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 5, 'The purpose of my instruction is that all the Christians there would be filled with love that comes from a pure heart, a clear conscience, and sincere faith.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 6, 'But some teachers have missed this whole point. They have turned away from these things and spend their time arguing and talking foolishness.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 7, 'They want to be known as teachers of the law of Moses, but they don''t know what they are talking about, even though they seem so confident.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 8, 'We know these laws are good when they are used as God intended.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 9, 'But they were not made for people who do what is right. They are for people who are disobedient and rebellious, who are ungodly and sinful, who consider nothing sacred and defile what is holy, who murder their father or mother or other people.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 10, 'These laws are for people who are sexually immoral, for homosexuals and slave traders, for liars and oath breakers, and for those who do anything else that contradicts the right teaching', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 11, 'that comes from the glorious Good News entrusted to me by our blessed God.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 12, 'How thankful I am to Christ Jesus our Lord for considering me trustworthy and appointing me to serve him,', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 13, 'even though I used to scoff at the name of Christ. I hunted down his people, harming them in every way I could. But God had mercy on me because I did it in ignorance and unbelief.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 14, 'Oh, how kind and gracious the Lord was! He filled me completely with faith and the love of Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 15, 'This is a true saying, and everyone should believe it: Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners--and I was the worst of them all.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 16, 'But that is why God had mercy on me, so that Christ Jesus could use me as a prime example of his great patience with even the worst sinners. Then others will realize that they, too, can believe in him and receive eternal life.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 17, 'Glory and honor to God forever and ever. He is the eternal King, the unseen one who never dies; he alone is God. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 18, 'Timothy, my son, here are my instructions for you, based on the prophetic words spoken about you earlier. May they give you the confidence to fight well in the Lord''s battles.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 19, 'Cling tightly to your faith in Christ, and always keep your conscience clear. For some people have deliberately violated their consciences; as a result, their faith has been shipwrecked.', 'NLT'),
(55, 1, 20, 'Hymenaeus and Alexander are two examples of this. I turned them over to Satan so they would learn not to blaspheme God.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 1, 'I urge you, first of all, to pray for all people. As you make your requests, plead for God''s mercy upon them, and give thanks.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 2, 'Pray this way for kings and all others who are in authority, so that we can live in peace and quietness, in godliness and dignity.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 3, 'This is good and pleases God our Savior,', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 4, 'for he wants everyone to be saved and to understand the truth.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 5, 'For there is only one God and one Mediator who can reconcile God and people. He is the man Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 6, 'He gave his life to purchase freedom for everyone. This is the message that God gave to the world at the proper time.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 7, 'And I have been chosen--this is the absolute truth--as a preacher and apostle to teach the Gentiles about faith and truth.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 8, 'So wherever you assemble, I want men to pray with holy hands lifted up to God, free from anger and controversy.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 9, 'And I want women to be modest in their appearance. They should wear decent and appropriate clothing and not draw attention to themselves by the way they fix their hair or by wearing gold or pearls or expensive clothes.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 10, 'For women who claim to be devoted to God should make themselves attractive by the good things they do.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 11, 'Women should listen and learn quietly and submissively.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 12, 'I do not let women teach men or have authority over them. Let them listen quietly.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 13, 'For God made Adam first, and afterward he made Eve.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 14, 'And it was the woman, not Adam, who was deceived by Satan, and sin was the result.', 'NLT'),
(55, 2, 15, 'But women will be saved through childbearing and by continuing to live in faith, love, holiness, and modesty.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 1, 'It is a true saying that if someone wants to be an elder, he desires an honorable responsibility.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 2, 'For an elder must be a man whose life cannot be spoken against. He must be faithful to his wife. He must exhibit self-control, live wisely, and have a good reputation. He must enjoy having guests in his home and must be able to teach.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 3, 'He must not be a heavy drinker or be violent. He must be gentle, peace loving, and not one who loves money.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 4, 'He must manage his own family well, with children who respect and obey him.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 5, 'For if a man cannot manage his own household, how can he take care of God''s church?', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 6, 'An elder must not be a new Christian, because he might be proud of being chosen so soon, and the Devil will use that pride to make him fall.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 7, 'Also, people outside the church must speak well of him so that he will not fall into the Devil''s trap and be disgraced.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 8, 'In the same way, deacons must be people who are respected and have integrity. They must not be heavy drinkers and must not be greedy for money.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 9, 'They must be committed to the revealed truths of the Christian faith and must live with a clear conscience.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 10, 'Before they are appointed as deacons, they should be given other responsibilities in the church as a test of their character and ability. If they do well, then they may serve as deacons.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 11, 'In the same way, their wives must be respected and must not speak evil of others. They must exercise self-control and be faithful in everything they do.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 12, 'A deacon must be faithful to his wife, and he must manage his children and household well.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 13, 'Those who do well as deacons will be rewarded with respect from others and will have increased confidence in their faith in Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 14, 'I am writing these things to you now, even though I hope to be with you soon,', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 15, 'so that if I can''t come for a while, you will know how people must conduct themselves in the household of God. This is the church of the living God, which is the pillar and support of the truth.', 'NLT'),
(55, 3, 16, 'Without question, this is the great mystery of our faith: Christ appeared in the flesh and was shown to be righteous by the Spirit. He was seen by angels and was announced to the nations. He was believed on in the world and was taken up into heaven.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 1, 'Now the Holy Spirit tells us clearly that in the last times some will turn away from what we believe; they will follow lying spirits and teachings that come from demons.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 2, 'These teachers are hypocrites and liars. They pretend to be religious, but their consciences are dead.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 3, 'They will say it is wrong to be married and wrong to eat certain foods. But God created those foods to be eaten with thanksgiving by people who know and believe the truth.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 4, 'Since everything God created is good, we should not reject any of it. We may receive it gladly, with thankful hearts.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 5, 'For we know it is made holy by the word of God and prayer.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 6, 'If you explain this to the brothers and sisters, you will be doing your duty as a worthy servant of Christ Jesus, one who is fed by the message of faith and the true teaching you have followed.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 7, 'Do not waste time arguing over godless ideas and old wives'' tales. Spend your time and energy in training yourself for spiritual fitness.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 8, 'Physical exercise has some value, but spiritual exercise is much more important, for it promises a reward in both this life and the next.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 9, 'This is true, and everyone should accept it.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 10, 'We work hard and suffer much in order that people will believe the truth, for our hope is in the living God, who is the Savior of all people, and particularly of those who believe.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 11, 'Teach these things and insist that everyone learn them.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 12, 'Don''t let anyone think less of you because you are young. Be an example to all believers in what you teach, in the way you live, in your love, your faith, and your purity.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 13, 'Until I get there, focus on reading the Scriptures to the church, encouraging the believers, and teaching them.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 14, 'Do not neglect the spiritual gift you received through the prophecies spoken to you when the elders of the church laid their hands on you.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 15, 'Give your complete attention to these matters. Throw yourself into your tasks so that everyone will see your progress.', 'NLT'),
(55, 4, 16, 'Keep a close watch on yourself and on your teaching. Stay true to what is right, and God will save you and those who hear you.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 1, 'Never speak harshly to an older man, but appeal to him respectfully as though he were your own father. Talk to the younger men as you would to your own brothers.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 2, 'Treat the older women as you would your mother, and treat the younger women with all purity as your own sisters.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 3, 'The church should care for any widow who has no one else to care for her.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 4, 'But if she has children or grandchildren, their first responsibility is to show godliness at home and repay their parents by taking care of them. This is something that pleases God very much.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 5, 'But a woman who is a true widow, one who is truly alone in this world, has placed her hope in God. Night and day she asks God for help and spends much time in prayer.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 6, 'But the widow who lives only for pleasure is spiritually dead.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 7, 'Give these instructions to the church so that the widows you support will not be criticized.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 8, 'But those who won''t care for their own relatives, especially those living in the same household, have denied what we believe. Such people are worse than unbelievers.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 9, 'A widow who is put on the list for support must be a woman who is at least sixty years old and was faithful to her husband.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 10, 'She must be well respected by everyone because of the good she has done. Has she brought up her children well? Has she been kind to strangers? Has she served other Christians humbly? Has she helped those who are in trouble? Has she always been ready to do good?', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 11, 'The younger widows should not be on the list, because their physical desires will overpower their devotion to Christ and they will want to remarry.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 12, 'Then they would be guilty of breaking their previous pledge.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 13, 'Besides, they are likely to become lazy and spend their time gossiping from house to house, getting into other people''s business and saying things they shouldn''t.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 14, 'So I advise these younger widows to marry again, have children, and take care of their own homes. Then the enemy will not be able to say anything against them.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 15, 'For I am afraid that some of them have already gone astray and now follow Satan.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 16, 'If a Christian woman has relatives who are widows, she must take care of them and not put the responsibility on the church. Then the church can care for widows who are truly alone.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 17, 'Elders who do their work well should be paid well, especially those who work hard at both preaching and teaching.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 18, 'For the Scripture says, "Do not keep an ox from eating as it treads out the grain." And in another place, "Those who work deserve their pay!"', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 19, 'Do not listen to complaints against an elder unless there are two or three witnesses to accuse him.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 20, 'Anyone who sins should be rebuked in front of the whole church so that others will have a proper fear of God.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 21, 'I solemnly command you in the presence of God and Christ Jesus and the holy angels to obey these instructions without taking sides or showing special favor to anyone.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 22, 'Never be in a hurry about appointing an elder. Do not participate in the sins of others. Keep yourself pure.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 23, 'Don''t drink only water. You ought to drink a little wine for the sake of your stomach because you are sick so often.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 24, 'Remember that some people lead sinful lives, and everyone knows they will be judged. But there are others whose sin will not be revealed until later.', 'NLT'),
(55, 5, 25, 'In the same way, everyone knows how much good some people do, but there are others whose good deeds won''t be known until later.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 1, 'Christians who are slaves should give their masters full respect so that the name of God and his teaching will not be shamed.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 2, 'If your master is a Christian, that is no excuse for being disrespectful. You should work all the harder because you are helping another believer by your efforts. Teach these truths, Timothy, and encourage everyone to obey them.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 3, 'Some false teachers may deny these things, but these are the sound, wholesome teachings of the Lord Jesus Christ, and they are the foundation for a godly life.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 4, 'Anyone who teaches anything different is both conceited and ignorant. Such a person has an unhealthy desire to quibble over the meaning of words. This stirs up arguments ending in jealousy, fighting, slander, and evil suspicions.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 5, 'These people always cause trouble. Their minds are corrupt, and they don''t tell the truth. To them religion is just a way to get rich.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 6, 'Yet true religion with contentment is great wealth.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 7, 'After all, we didn''t bring anything with us when we came into the world, and we certainly cannot carry anything with us when we die.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 8, 'So if we have enough food and clothing, let us be content.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 9, 'But people who long to be rich fall into temptation and are trapped by many foolish and harmful desires that plunge them into ruin and destruction.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 10, 'For the love of money is at the root of all kinds of evil. And some people, craving money, have wandered from the faith and pierced themselves with many sorrows.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 11, 'But you, Timothy, belong to God; so run from all these evil things, and follow what is right and good. Pursue a godly life, along with faith, love, perseverance, and gentleness.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 12, 'Fight the good fight for what we believe. Hold tightly to the eternal life that God has given you, which you have confessed so well before many witnesses.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 13, 'And I command you before God, who gives life to all, and before Christ Jesus, who gave a good testimony before Pontius Pilate,', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 14, 'that you obey his commands with all purity. Then no one can find fault with you from now until our Lord Jesus Christ returns.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 15, 'For at the right time Christ will be revealed from heaven by the blessed and only almighty God, the King of kings and Lord of lords.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 16, 'He alone can never die, and he lives in light so brilliant that no human can approach him. No one has ever seen him, nor ever will. To him be honor and power forever. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 17, 'Tell those who are rich in this world not to be proud and not to trust in their money, which will soon be gone. But their trust should be in the living God, who richly gives us all we need for our enjoyment.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 18, 'Tell them to use their money to do good. They should be rich in good works and should give generously to those in need, always being ready to share with others whatever God has given them.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 19, 'By doing this they will be storing up their treasure as a good foundation for the future so that they may take hold of real life.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 20, 'Timothy, guard what God has entrusted to you. Avoid godless, foolish discussions with those who oppose you with their so-called knowledge.', 'NLT'),
(55, 6, 21, 'Some people have wandered from the faith by following such foolishness. May God''s grace be with you all.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by God''s will, sent out to tell others about the life he has promised through faith in Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 2, 'It is written to Timothy, my dear son. May God our Father and Christ Jesus our Lord give you grace, mercy, and peace.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 3, 'Timothy, I thank God for you. He is the God I serve with a clear conscience, just as my ancestors did. Night and day I constantly remember you in my prayers.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 4, 'I long to see you again, for I remember your tears as we parted. And I will be filled with joy when we are together again.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 5, 'I know that you sincerely trust the Lord, for you have the faith of your mother, Eunice, and your grandmother, Lois.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 6, 'This is why I remind you to fan into flames the spiritual gift God gave you when I laid my hands on you.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 7, 'For God has not given us a spirit of fear and timidity, but of power, love, and self-discipline.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 8, 'So you must never be ashamed to tell others about our Lord. And don''t be ashamed of me, either, even though I''m in prison for Christ. With the strength God gives you, be ready to suffer with me for the proclamation of the Good News.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 9, 'It is God who saved us and chose us to live a holy life. He did this not because we deserved it, but because that was his plan long before the world began--to show his love and kindness to us through Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 10, 'And now he has made all of this plain to us by the coming of Christ Jesus, our Savior, who broke the power of death and showed us the way to everlasting life through the Good News.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 11, 'And God chose me to be a preacher, an apostle, and a teacher of this Good News.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 12, 'And that is why I am suffering here in prison. But I am not ashamed of it, for I know the one in whom I trust, and I am sure that he is able to guard what I have entrusted to him until the day of his return.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 13, 'Hold on to the pattern of right teaching you learned from me. And remember to live in the faith and love that you have in Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 14, 'With the help of the Holy Spirit who lives within us, carefully guard what has been entrusted to you.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 15, 'As you know, all the Christians who came here from the province of Asia have deserted me; even Phygelus and Hermogenes are gone.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 16, 'May the Lord show special kindness to Onesiphorus and all his family because he often visited and encouraged me. He was never ashamed of me because I was in prison.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 17, 'When he came to Rome, he searched everywhere until he found me.', 'NLT'),
(56, 1, 18, 'May the Lord show him special kindness on the day of Christ''s return. And you know how much he helped me at Ephesus.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 1, 'Timothy, my dear son, be strong with the special favor God gives you in Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 2, 'You have heard me teach many things that have been confirmed by many reliable witnesses. Teach these great truths to trustworthy people who are able to pass them on to others.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 3, 'Endure suffering along with me, as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 4, 'And as Christ''s soldier, do not let yourself become tied up in the affairs of this life, for then you cannot satisfy the one who has enlisted you in his army.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 5, 'Follow the Lord''s rules for doing his work, just as an athlete either follows the rules or is disqualified and wins no prize.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 6, 'Hardworking farmers are the first to enjoy the fruit of their labor.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 7, 'Think about what I am saying. The Lord will give you understanding in all these things.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 8, 'Never forget that Jesus Christ was a man born into King David''s family and that he was raised from the dead. This is the Good News I preach.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 9, 'And because I preach this Good News, I am suffering and have been chained like a criminal. But the word of God cannot be chained.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 10, 'I am willing to endure anything if it will bring salvation and eternal glory in Christ Jesus to those God has chosen.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 11, 'This is a true saying: If we die with him, we will also live with him.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 12, 'If we endure hardship, we will reign with him. If we deny him, he will deny us.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 13, 'If we are unfaithful, he remains faithful, for he cannot deny himself.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 14, 'Remind everyone of these things, and command them in God''s name to stop fighting over words. Such arguments are useless, and they can ruin those who hear them.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 15, 'Work hard so God can approve you. Be a good worker, one who does not need to be ashamed and who correctly explains the word of truth.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 16, 'Avoid godless, foolish discussions that lead to more and more ungodliness.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 17, 'This kind of talk spreads like cancer. Hymenaeus and Philetus are examples of this.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 18, 'They have left the path of truth, preaching the lie that the resurrection of the dead has already occurred; and they have undermined the faith of some.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 19, 'But God''s truth stands firm like a foundation stone with this inscription: "The Lord knows those who are his," and "Those who claim they belong to the Lord must turn away from all wickedness."', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 20, 'In a wealthy home some utensils are made of gold and silver, and some are made of wood and clay. The expensive utensils are used for special occasions, and the cheap ones are for everyday use.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 21, 'If you keep yourself pure, you will be a utensil God can use for his purpose. Your life will be clean, and you will be ready for the Master to use you for every good work.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 22, 'Run from anything that stimulates youthful lust. Follow anything that makes you want to do right. Pursue faith and love and peace, and enjoy the companionship of those who call on the Lord with pure hearts.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 23, 'Again I say, don''t get involved in foolish, ignorant arguments that only start fights.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 24, 'The Lord''s servants must not quarrel but must be kind to everyone. They must be able to teach effectively and be patient with difficult people.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 25, 'They should gently teach those who oppose the truth. Perhaps God will change those people''s hearts, and they will believe the truth.', 'NLT'),
(56, 2, 26, 'Then they will come to their senses and escape from the Devil''s trap. For they have been held captive by him to do whatever he wants.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 1, 'You should also know this, Timothy, that in the last days there will be very difficult times.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 2, 'For people will love only themselves and their money. They will be boastful and proud, scoffing at God, disobedient to their parents, and ungrateful. They will consider nothing sacred.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 3, 'They will be unloving and unforgiving; they will slander others and have no self-control; they will be cruel and have no interest in what is good.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 4, 'They will betray their friends, be reckless, be puffed up with pride, and love pleasure rather than God.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 5, 'They will act as if they are religious, but they will reject the power that could make them godly. You must stay away from people like that.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 6, 'They are the kind who work their way into people''s homes and win the confidence of vulnerable women who are burdened with the guilt of sin and controlled by many desires.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 7, 'Such women are forever following new teachings, but they never understand the truth.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 8, 'And these teachers fight the truth just as Jannes and Jambres fought against Moses. Their minds are depraved, and their faith is counterfeit.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 9, 'But they won''t get away with this for long. Someday everyone will recognize what fools they are, just as happened with Jannes and Jambres.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 10, 'But you know what I teach, Timothy, and how I live, and what my purpose in life is. You know my faith and how long I have suffered. You know my love and my patient endurance.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 11, 'You know how much persecution and suffering I have endured. You know all about how I was persecuted in Antioch, Iconium, and Lystra--but the Lord delivered me from all of it.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 12, 'Yes, and everyone who wants to live a godly life in Christ Jesus will suffer persecution.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 13, 'But evil people and impostors will flourish. They will go on deceiving others, and they themselves will be deceived.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 14, 'But you must remain faithful to the things you have been taught. You know they are true, for you know you can trust those who taught you.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 15, 'You have been taught the holy Scriptures from childhood, and they have given you the wisdom to receive the salvation that comes by trusting in Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 16, 'All Scripture is inspired by God and is useful to teach us what is true and to make us realize what is wrong in our lives. It straightens us out and teaches us to do what is right.', 'NLT'),
(56, 3, 17, 'It is God''s way of preparing us in every way, fully equipped for every good thing God wants us to do.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 1, 'And so I solemnly urge you before God and before Christ Jesus--who will someday judge the living and the dead when he appears to set up his Kingdom:', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 2, 'Preach the word of God. Be persistent, whether the time is favorable or not. Patiently correct, rebuke, and encourage your people with good teaching.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 3, 'For a time is coming when people will no longer listen to right teaching. They will follow their own desires and will look for teachers who will tell them whatever they want to hear.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 4, 'They will reject the truth and follow strange myths.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 5, 'But you should keep a clear mind in every situation. Don''t be afraid of suffering for the Lord. Work at bringing others to Christ. Complete the ministry God has given you.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 6, 'As for me, my life has already been poured out as an offering to God. The time of my death is near.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 7, 'I have fought a good fight, I have finished the race, and I have remained faithful.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 8, 'And now the prize awaits me--the crown of righteousness that the Lord, the righteous Judge, will give me on that great day of his return. And the prize is not just for me but for all who eagerly look forward to his glorious return.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 9, 'Please come as soon as you can.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 10, 'Demas has deserted me because he loves the things of this life and has gone to Thessalonica. Crescens has gone to Galatia, and Titus has gone to Dalmatia.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 11, 'Only Luke is with me. Bring Mark with you when you come, for he will be helpful to me.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 12, 'I sent Tychicus to Ephesus.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 13, 'When you come, be sure to bring the coat I left with Carpus at Troas. Also bring my books, and especially my papers.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 14, 'Alexander the coppersmith has done me much harm, but the Lord will judge him for what he has done.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 15, 'Be careful of him, for he fought against everything we said.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 16, 'The first time I was brought before the judge, no one was with me. Everyone had abandoned me. I hope it will not be counted against them.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 17, 'But the Lord stood with me and gave me strength, that I might preach the Good News in all its fullness for all the Gentiles to hear. And he saved me from certain death.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 18, 'Yes, and the Lord will deliver me from every evil attack and will bring me safely to his heavenly Kingdom. To God be the glory forever and ever. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 19, 'Give my greetings to Priscilla and Aquila and those living at the household of Onesiphorus.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 20, 'Erastus stayed at Corinth, and I left Trophimus sick at Miletus.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 21, 'Hurry so you can get here before winter. Eubulus sends you greetings, and so do Pudens, Linus, Claudia, and all the brothers and sisters.', 'NLT'),
(56, 4, 22, 'May the Lord be with your spirit. Grace be with you all.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, a slave of God and an apostle of Jesus Christ. I have been sent to bring faith to those God has chosen and to teach them to know the truth that shows them how to live godly lives.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 2, 'This truth gives them the confidence of eternal life, which God promised them before the world began--and he cannot lie.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 3, 'And now at the right time he has revealed this Good News, and we announce it to everyone. It is by the command of God our Savior that I have been trusted to do this work for him.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 4, 'This letter is written to Titus, my true child in the faith that we share. May God the Father and Christ Jesus our Savior give you grace and peace.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 5, 'I left you on the island of Crete so you could complete our work there and appoint elders in each town as I instructed you.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 6, 'An elder must be well thought of for his good life. He must be faithful to his wife, and his children must be believers who are not wild or rebellious.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 7, 'An elder must live a blameless life because he is God''s minister. He must not be arrogant or quick-tempered; he must not be a heavy drinker, violent, or greedy for money.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 8, 'He must enjoy having guests in his home and must love all that is good. He must live wisely and be fair. He must live a devout and disciplined life.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 9, 'He must have a strong and steadfast belief in the trustworthy message he was taught; then he will be able to encourage others with right teaching and show those who oppose it where they are wrong.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 10, 'For there are many who rebel against right teaching; they engage in useless talk and deceive people. This is especially true of those who insist on circumcision for salvation.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 11, 'They must be silenced. By their wrong teaching, they have already turned whole families away from the truth. Such teachers only want your money.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 12, 'One of their own men, a prophet from Crete, has said about them, "The people of Crete are all liars; they are cruel animals and lazy gluttons."', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 13, 'This is true. So rebuke them as sternly as necessary to make them strong in the faith.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 14, 'They must stop listening to Jewish myths and the commands of people who have turned their backs on the truth.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 15, 'Everything is pure to those whose hearts are pure. But nothing is pure to those who are corrupt and unbelieving, because their minds and consciences are defiled.', 'NLT'),
(57, 1, 16, 'Such people claim they know God, but they deny him by the way they live. They are despicable and disobedient, worthless for doing anything good.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 1, 'But as for you, promote the kind of living that reflects right teaching.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 2, 'Teach the older men to exercise self-control, to be worthy of respect, and to live wisely. They must have strong faith and be filled with love and patience.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 3, 'Similarly, teach the older women to live in a way that is appropriate for someone serving the Lord. They must not go around speaking evil of others and must not be heavy drinkers. Instead, they should teach others what is good.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 4, 'These older women must train the younger women to love their husbands and their children,', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 5, 'to live wisely and be pure, to take care of their homes, to do good, and to be submissive to their husbands. Then they will not bring shame on the word of God.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 6, 'In the same way, encourage the young men to live wisely in all they do.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 7, 'And you yourself must be an example to them by doing good deeds of every kind. Let everything you do reflect the integrity and seriousness of your teaching.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 8, 'Let your teaching be so correct that it can''t be criticized. Then those who want to argue will be ashamed because they won''t have anything bad to say about us.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 9, 'Slaves must obey their masters and do their best to please them. They must not talk back', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 10, 'or steal, but they must show themselves to be entirely trustworthy and good. Then they will make the teaching about God our Savior attractive in every way.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 11, 'For the grace of God has been revealed, bringing salvation to all people.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 12, 'And we are instructed to turn from godless living and sinful pleasures. We should live in this evil world with self-control, right conduct, and devotion to God,', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 13, 'while we look forward to that wonderful event when the glory of our great God and Savior, Jesus Christ, will be revealed.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 14, 'He gave his life to free us from every kind of sin, to cleanse us, and to make us his very own people, totally committed to doing what is right.', 'NLT'),
(57, 2, 15, 'You must teach these things and encourage your people to do them, correcting them when necessary. You have the authority to do this, so don''t let anyone ignore you or disregard what you say.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 1, 'Remind your people to submit to the government and its officers. They should be obedient, always ready to do what is good.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 2, 'They must not speak evil of anyone, and they must avoid quarreling. Instead, they should be gentle and show true humility to everyone.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 3, 'Once we, too, were foolish and disobedient. We were misled by others and became slaves to many wicked desires and evil pleasures. Our lives were full of evil and envy. We hated others, and they hated us.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 4, 'But then God our Savior showed us his kindness and love.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 5, 'He saved us, not because of the good things we did, but because of his mercy. He washed away our sins and gave us a new life through the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 6, 'He generously poured out the Spirit upon us because of what Jesus Christ our Savior did.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 7, 'He declared us not guilty because of his great kindness. And now we know that we will inherit eternal life.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 8, 'These things I have told you are all true. I want you to insist on them so that everyone who trusts in God will be careful to do good deeds all the time. These things are good and beneficial for everyone.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 9, 'Do not get involved in foolish discussions about spiritual pedigrees or in quarrels and fights about obedience to Jewish laws. These kinds of things are useless and a waste of time.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 10, 'If anyone is causing divisions among you, give a first and second warning. After that, have nothing more to do with that person.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 11, 'For people like that have turned away from the truth. They are sinning, and they condemn themselves.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 12, 'I am planning to send either Artemas or Tychicus to you. As soon as one of them arrives, do your best to meet me at Nicopolis as quickly as you can, for I have decided to stay there for the winter.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 13, 'Do everything you can to help Zenas the lawyer and Apollos with their trip. See that they are given everything they need.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 14, 'For our people should not have unproductive lives. They must learn to do good by helping others who have urgent needs.', 'NLT'),
(57, 3, 15, 'Everybody here sends greetings. Please give my greetings to all of the believers who love us. May God''s grace be with you all.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 1, 'This letter is from Paul, in prison for preaching the Good News about Christ Jesus, and from our brother Timothy. It is written to Philemon, our much loved co-worker,', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 2, 'and to our sister Apphia and to Archippus, a fellow soldier of the cross. I am also writing to the church that meets in your house.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 3, 'May God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ give you grace and peace.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 4, 'I always thank God when I pray for you, Philemon,', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 5, 'because I keep hearing of your trust in the Lord Jesus and your love for all of God''s people.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 6, 'You are generous because of your faith. And I am praying that you will really put your generosity to work, for in so doing you will come to an understanding of all the good things we can do for Christ.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 7, 'I myself have gained much joy and comfort from your love, my brother, because your kindness has so often refreshed the hearts of God''s people.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 8, 'That is why I am boldly asking a favor of you. I could demand it in the name of Christ because it is the right thing for you to do,', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 9, 'but because of our love, I prefer just to ask you. So take this as a request from your friend Paul, an old man, now in prison for the sake of Christ Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 10, 'My plea is that you show kindness to Onesimus. I think of him as my own son because he became a believer as a result of my ministry here in prison.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 11, 'Onesimus hasn''t been of much use to you in the past, but now he is very useful to both of us.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 12, 'I am sending him back to you, and with him comes my own heart.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 13, 'I really wanted to keep him here with me while I am in these chains for preaching the Good News, and he would have helped me on your behalf.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 14, 'But I didn''t want to do anything without your consent. And I didn''t want you to help because you were forced to do it but because you wanted to.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 15, 'Perhaps you could think of it this way: Onesimus ran away for a little while so you could have him back forever.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 16, 'He is no longer just a slave; he is a beloved brother, especially to me. Now he will mean much more to you, both as a slave and as a brother in the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 17, 'So if you consider me your partner, give him the same welcome you would give me if I were coming.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 18, 'If he has harmed you in any way or stolen anything from you, charge me for it.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 19, 'I, Paul, write this in my own handwriting: "I will repay it." And I won''t mention that you owe me your very soul!', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 20, 'Yes, dear brother, please do me this favor for the Lord''s sake. Give me this encouragement in Christ.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 21, 'I am confident as I write this letter that you will do what I ask and even more!', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 22, 'Please keep a guest room ready for me, for I am hoping that God will answer your prayers and let me return to you soon.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 23, 'Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, sends you his greetings.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 24, 'So do Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my co-workers.', 'NLT'),
(58, 1, 25, 'The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 1, 'Long ago God spoke many times and in many ways to our ancestors through the prophets.', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 2, 'But now in these final days, he has spoken to us through his Son. God promised everything to the Son as an inheritance, and through the Son he made the universe and everything in it.', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 3, 'The Son reflects God''s own glory, and everything about him represents God exactly. He sustains the universe by the mighty power of his command. After he died to cleanse us from the stain of sin, he sat down in the place of honor at the right hand of the majestic God of heaven.', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 4, 'This shows that God''s Son is far greater than the angels, just as the name God gave him is far greater than their names.', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 5, 'For God never said to any angel what he said to Jesus: "You are my Son. Today I have become your Father. "And again God said, "I will be his Father, and he will be my Son."', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 6, 'And then, when he presented his honored Son to the world, God said, "Let all the angels of God worship him."', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 7, 'God calls his angels "messengers swift as the wind, and servants made of flaming fire."', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 8, 'But to his Son he says, "Your throne, O God, endures forever and ever. Your royal power is expressed in righteousness.', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 9, 'You love what is right and hate what is wrong. Therefore God, your God, has anointed you, pouring out the oil of joy on you more than on anyone else."', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 10, 'And, "Lord, in the beginning you laid the foundation of the earth, and the heavens are the work of your hands.', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 11, 'Even they will perish, but you remain forever. They will wear out like old clothing.', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 12, 'You will roll them up like an old coat. They will fade away like old clothing. But you are always the same; you will never grow old."', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 13, 'And God never said to an angel, as he did to his Son, "Sit in honor at my right hand until I humble your enemies, making them a footstool under your feet."', 'NLT'),
(59, 1, 14, 'But angels are only servants. They are spirits sent from God to care for those who will receive salvation.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 1, 'So we must listen very carefully to the truth we have heard, or we may drift away from it.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 2, 'The message God delivered through angels has always proved true, and the people were punished for every violation of the law and every act of disobedience.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 3, 'What makes us think that we can escape if we are indifferent to this great salvation that was announced by the Lord Jesus himself? It was passed on to us by those who heard him speak,', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 4, 'and God verified the message by signs and wonders and various miracles and by giving gifts of the Holy Spirit whenever he chose to do so.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 5, 'And furthermore, the future world we are talking about will not be controlled by angels.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 6, 'For somewhere in the Scriptures it says, "What is man that you should think of him, and the son of man that you should care for him?', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 7, 'For a little while you made him lower than the angels, and you crowned him with glory and honor.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 8, 'You gave him authority over all things." Now when it says "all things," it means nothing is left out. But we have not yet seen all of this happen.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 9, 'What we do see is Jesus, who "for a little while was made lower than the angels" and now is "crowned with glory and honor" because he suffered death for us. Yes, by God''s grace, Jesus tasted death for everyone in all the world.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 10, 'And it was only right that God--who made everything and for whom everything was made--should bring his many children into glory. Through the suffering of Jesus, God made him a perfect leader, one fit to bring them into their salvation.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 11, 'So now Jesus and the ones he makes holy have the same Father. That is why Jesus is not ashamed to call them his brothers and sisters.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 12, 'For he said to God, "I will declare the wonder of your name to my brothers and sisters. I will praise you among all your people."', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 13, 'He also said, "I will put my trust in him." And in the same context he said, "Here I am--together with the children God has given me."', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 14, 'Because God''s children are human beings--made of flesh and blood--Jesus also became flesh and blood by being born in human form. For only as a human being could he die, and only by dying could he break the power of the Devil, who had the power of death.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 15, 'Only in this way could he deliver those who have lived all their lives as slaves to the fear of dying.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 16, 'We all know that Jesus came to help the descendants of Abraham, not to help the angels.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 17, 'Therefore, it was necessary for Jesus to be in every respect like us, his brothers and sisters, so that he could be our merciful and faithful High Priest before God. He then could offer a sacrifice that would take away the sins of the people.', 'NLT'),
(59, 2, 18, 'Since he himself has gone through suffering and temptation, he is able to help us when we are being tempted.', 'NLT'),
(59, 3, 1, 'And so, dear brothers and sisters who belong to God and are bound for heaven, think about this Jesus whom we declare to be God''s Messenger and High Priest.', 'NLT'),
(59, 3, 2, 'For he was faithful to God, who appointed him, just as Moses served faithfully and was entrusted with God''s entire house.', 'NLT'),
(59, 3, 3, 'But Jesus deserves far more glory than Moses, just as a person who builds a fine house deserves more praise than the house itself.', 'NLT'),
(59, 3, 4, 'For every house has a builder, but God is the one who made everything.', 'NLT'),
(59, 3, 5, 'Moses was certainly faithful in God''s house, but only as a servant. His work was an illustration of the truths God would reveal later.', 'NLT');
